u'width': 2364, u'html_attributions': [u'Meredith Zink'], u'height': 2803}], u'types': [u'bar', u'restaurant', u'food', u'point_of_interest', u'establishment'], u'icon': u'https://maps.gstatic.com/mapfiles/place_api/icons/restaurant-71.png', u'name': u'M. Wells Steakhouse', u'geometry': {u'location': {u'lat': 40.7485158, u'lng': -73.9422488}, u'viewport': {u'northeast': {u'lat': 40.7486463, u'lng': -73.94215699999998}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.7484723, u'lng': -73.94252420000001}}}, u'adr_address': u'43-15 Crescent St, Long Island City, NY 11101, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 718-786-9060', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-s4jONdXmgf8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAXE/ALaH0aoinOo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Every single aspect of my experience eating here was excellent. The staff was extremely knowledgeable, there were different people with different specialties who answered my questions. They fostered a comfortable enough rapport with us that I asked more questions than I would normally have. As a result I not only enjoyed an amazing meal from start to finish, but I actually learned about a few different things. The atmosphere is a little on the hipper side, but that doesn't deter at all from the experience. In my opinion their recent Michelin star is well deserved. I ate at Bouley a few weeks prior and I found M. Wells to be superior in terms of service and food.', u'author_name': u'Adam D', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102835541953073318692', u'time': 1458508514}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-hL_QGreRwwQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGoc/Kk9cBhd1rIo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Not quite perfect, but nearly so. Been here too many times to count, and it's always, always great. The Manhattan is among the best I've had. The oysters are usually spot-on. Even the sides here are good! But ultimately, you come for the meat. And MOST of the times, that meat is superb. We've had a meat dish or two that were merely above average, particularly in their early days -- I attribute this to the difficulty of cooking with fire. But all other times, they have knocked it out of the park. Our most recent visit, the venison porterhouse was out of this world good. So was a side of spring vegetables. So was the pasta. The food is heavy, so calibrate appropriately. (Don't think of the bone marrow onion soup as "merely" an appetizer, for instance. For light eaters, it can be a meal in itself.) Go here, now.', u'author_name': u'Johnny Tan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102728581437805238916', u'time': 1461648169}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-FQXKCRlwsSw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAs/IAP4A9dsVJo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'M Wells was our favorite new steakhouse this year. Was. Our first three visits here made us forget about the old school NY steakhouses very fast. The location is great. The ambiance is just unexpected and awesome. Ultra cool vibe for me. The appetizers were very good but way over shadowed buy the sides and main dish. The greens were sautéed and seasoned to perfection. The poutine was crazy good. The french fries were perfect then you add the gravy and the cheese curd and I thought that would be the best side dish I had ever eaten at a steakhouse until I ate the pomme aligot. Pomme aligot is from another planet. An insane mixture of potatoes and cheese with a taste and texture is almost undescribable. DELICIOUS! Ended up getting two orders every time we went. The Côte de boeuf Ribeye was the thing that really kept us coming back. Insanely huge with insane flavor and texture to match. Melt in your mouth. The best ribeye we ever had. Now why only three stars? On our forth visit we were upset to find they took the Côte de boeuf off the menu. We scrambled and tried two other choices but they couldn't touch the reason why we came here, the ribeye. The sides are fantastic but to go to a steakhouse for just sides not happening for me. I've called a few times to see if they added the ribeye back but no luck.', u'author_name': u'Monica 夏', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110319965619207643361', u'time': 1458927640}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-rP5-DpNZsYk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAL0/6iWdD9pJkIo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The food was fantastic - clam chowder, the wagyu and Ny strip - great cocktails ', u'author_name': u'frank mastromauro', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113509255165200897258', u'time': 1465686171}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-hKZBRVwFMG4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAFI/TSzW3GdxUYs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Came early on a Cold a day with snow falling outside. Ordered two of the house cocktails- the M Wells Manhattan and the Maple Sideboob.The Sideboob won out with a smooth Mix of sweet & Sour. However, for a Kentucky boy, the Manhattan was adequate but nothing to write house about. On to food! Started really strong with Onion and Bone Marrow soup, which was amazing. Then we added a "straight from Montreal" poutine to the mix and the cold weather was all but forgotten. Tried a jar of three steamed clams in vinegar. Very nice if a bit subtle taste for the other powerhouses on our table. Entrees were a tasty huge braised short rib and a petite filet that was medium rare perfection( well seasoned without being overpowering. We ordered a side of excellently fried Brussel sprouts to keep the meat company. Our only misstep was dessert - the sundae, It was unremarkable- we felt ike we could have put together a similar result at home. Still can't figure how we passed over such intriguing options like Maple Pie, baled Alaska and a Chocolate crusted coconut pie. Oh well, next time, because there will definitely be a next time! {u'lat': 40.74367779999999, u'lng': -73.95397295000001}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.74332380000001, u'lng': -73.95503155}}}, u'adr_address': u'5-48 49th Ave, Long Island City, NY 11101, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 347-448-6040', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Fantastic food, cozy venue and reasonably priced. The Tostadas de Jaiba (crab), Enchiladas de Mole and the Tres leches dessert are really good.', u'author_name': u'Alfonso CA', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105605843722353239020', u'time': 1464612061}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-0M7oj_SmzQI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAo/yUw9zQMdJ84/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I've been here twice for restaurant week and have enjoyed it both times, but had a much better experience the first time. The first time I went, the service was spot on, the food was excellent, and they offered both the restaurant week menu, the drink menu, and the regular menu. I love the over the top decor at this place, green and red and gold everything! The second time was odd. Coat check was MIA, and the hostess took our coats and said the waiter would bring us our coat check number and never did (amazingly the coat check lady somehow knew exactly what coats were ours so crisis averted). We were only handed the RW menu, and had to hunt down a waiter for get the drink menu. It was kinda like the restaurant said 'screw it, RESTAURANT WEEK FOR ALL' and just began mass producing its food without much care. The wait staff seemed harried and were not attentive. The borscht was amazing as always. The chicken was overcooked and tough to chew. This was the worst part of the meal, I should have gotten the steak because I stole some off my boyfriends dish and it was perfectly prepared. And the chocolate mousse pyramid, well, chocolate mousse pyramid, need I say more?', u'author_name': u'ru yi li', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103772686386980536225', u'time': 1464191421}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WWeyHAfMa_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/cn3jjZFnhzA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great place for Mexican food. Staffs are friendly and nice. Atmosphere is cozy and laid back. I suggest getting the enchilada Verde de mole so good, fantastic flavor and well balanced. Overall great experience and any Mexican food lover will love this restaurant. ', u'author_name': u'Rafael Yau', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107744062940210293013', u'time': 1466289917}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I feel saying this is the best Mexican Restaurant in the North East does not give Casa Enrique justice. It is superb not merely compared to the competition (which is quite poor in this part of the country to be honest), but excellent in its own right. Fully worthy of its Michelin Star rating.', u'author_name': u'Mac Carr', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116537524219553592799', u'time': 1461345048}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-6EenwNIaN_0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAACMr8/JZrvRA7KGtc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great food, great service. I love this place. I go there several times a month. u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Zm3M0h3HMbE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABXI/OB3sxeChajM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'"All steak houses are the same"... Not so fast my friends. I have to say Peter Luger's did live up to the hype the steak is above what you might get at a Capital Grille, Ruth's Chris, etc. The wine list is brief but manageable. It is a unique experience that every New Yorker should try and if you are in the mood for a great steak look no farther. If you are looking for a complete dining experience you may want to try somewhere else. The decor is unapologetically plain and the menu is limited. Many guests don't even need to look at it. These things are part of the charm of the restaurant but good things to know.', u'author_name': u'Michael Samaroo', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108957989918005844461', u'time': 1466521899}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Wow - AMAZING!!!! I loved everything about my experience. The steak wasn't like anything I'd ever had before. You have to try it if you haven't already - even the service is perfect. It's such a classic New York steak house. ', u'author_name': u'Louise DeMartin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107099605939555143397', u'time': 1459904536}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-6mYoDnNEzbQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAkU/TZ9iQeHU_uI/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Best steak anywhere. To start, go for the sliced tomatoes & onions and hearts of lettuce, and enjoy with salt, pepper and a smattering of Luger's sauce to taste. Then with your steak get German potatoes and creamed spinach on the side. Done. Perfection. After your last bite, relax your belt one or two notches so you can stand up and go home. ', u'author_name': u'Sy Aryeh', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106603684058103204295', u'time': 1461792192}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-NSmu4_kmgkg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABQg/y_KFTJqJWZQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Mehhhh... just a little overrated. The steak was solid and the butter on top was a nice touch. For the price, I've had better though. As for the sides, I thought the potatoes and the creamed spinach were pretty mediocre. The bread and the shrimp were very good though. Decent beer selection as well. As for the service, it was a little pushy but not rude. I've heard others complain about rude servers, but I didn't see it. Maybe I'm just used to NYC service and attitude.', u'author_name': u'Michael N', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116079407214484183950', u'time': 1463752026}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-UrCoCA72_vg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAB7U/Tas2Ut1ye54/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Warm inviting atmosphere. With great staff and food. Pricey but worth it!', u'author_name': u'Dawn Narry', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112683255289891864471', u'time': 1462737086}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 387-7400', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'178', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'178'}, {u'long_name': u'Broadway', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Broadway'}, {u'long_name': u'Williamsburg', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Williamsburg'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11211', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11211'}]}

{u'lat': 40.71432844999999, u'lng': -73.95601555}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.71406705, u'lng': -73.95619975000001}}}, u'adr_address': u'355 Metropolitan Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11211, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 718-384-5054', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-GsFGzU6VJ-A/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABWk/WAB7hVarqXg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is a must visit- the meat is incredible and so fairly priced. The appetizers and sides are 100% unforgettable. There is a bar next door that you should probably get familiar with because there will be a wait and likely a long one. There's a shared back patio so it's not all bad. I can see why some people perceive the hostess staff as uninviting but they're dealing with hoards of "unhappy with the wait" people. Once you get to a table, everything is super. Try the butcher steak, burrata, mashed potatoes, and sheep cheese walnut bread! ', u'author_name': u'Frances Angulo', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101794985347503816479', u'time': 1464268637}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-hz_Q64YbQi0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABL8/w8CaylPb8xU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Remains one of the great locavore carnivore nouvelle american restaurants in Williamsburg. The ax handle steak for two (or 3 or 4 depending on the size of your stomach) is always a great bet and they have a dependably solid red wine list to accompany that steak. One thing I really appreciate is that while waiting, you can hang next door inside or in the lovely back yard of Spuyten Duyvil where they have a constantly rotating selection of excellent craft beer.', u'author_name': u'Yves Jaques', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108280583760081494828', u'time': 1464812175}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great steak... one of the best i have had in years. A large group of us popped in here on a Monday night and had to wait next door as it was so busy. One quick pint in there sister bar and they were able to make room for a table of 9. Seafood appetizers particularly the grilled monster prawns were amazing and the steaks were unbelievable. Particular mention to the Ax Handle and the NY strip. Next time I'm in NY will definitely be coming back.', u'author_name': u'Nigel O'Connell', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111330731290358664303', u'time': 1463743265}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-tN9p-RqIKK0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAER4/iAfXZvHLthM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'So delicious! The food is amazing and the decor is adorable. The restaurant is pretty small so there can be a long wait time during peak hours. The pan fried mash potatoes with truffle oil are sooo good. The steak is reasonably priced and delicious!', u'author_name': u'Alexa G.', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111527650644566248430', u'time': 1453213759}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Superb - Peerless ! I took what remained of the axe handle home in a doggie bag (for the dog, a large brown male newfie). Well, the dog never even had a chance to lay eyes on it. Please refrain from mentioning it when he's around, it's still a sore subject.', u'author_name': u'Tom Jakab', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101190730272236204880', u'time': 1458974038}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 384-5054', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'355', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'355'}, {u'long_name': u'Metropolitan Avenue', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Metropolitan Ave'}, {u'long_name': u'Williamsburg', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Williamsburg'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11211', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11211'}]}

u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-et0JX9mVMj4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAV4/jO7MBT0PlYQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Having been to Torst many times, I have heard a lot about Luksus and have wanted to try it. After finally taking the plunge, I can say that it is definitely worth it. Luksus delivers a fine dining experience in a relaxed atmosphere. It's also the only high end restaurant I've ever been to that takes beer seriously. If you're going to go, you must do the beer pairing. It is setup with a tasting menu. The food was impressive. Luksus is a must visit for any foodie or beer lover. ', u'author_name': u'Mickey Luongo', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106068332779167701737', u'time': 1462828990}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-nX4oJeFwCv0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAHOg/Sch1ZyBJKmA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'First 1 star restaurant I ever went to and it didn't disappoint. Best meal I've ever eaten and the beer pairings went exceedingly well with everything! We even had the best seats in the house being seated at the bar right in front of the kitchen so that we could see everything being made. The chefs were also very friendly and happy to talk about their food.', u'author_name': u'Martin Lloyd', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114030594686247856893', u'time': 1449061970}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Z-2h_tf9V8U/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACcQ/StdmL3oVAIo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'A fun experience with the beer pairing. Lovely to have the courses introduced by Burns himself. A very humble and genuine restaurant.', u'author_name': u'Linn Lundgren', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108163055014327609594', u'time': 1464729297}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-SREyRpZ4hsA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAA1A/Ar-TjmRhMIU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Behind the inconspicuous sliding white door in Tørst hides another revelation. This one Michelin star eatery offers only beer as pairings, which is genius when it is done this well. The food was playful, intricate, but not fussy; featuring modern reimaginings of traditional danish foods. The pairings worked perfectly. If you arena foodie or a beer nerd or both, this place is a must visit.', u'author_name': u'James McFadyen', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/118329153629342267924', u'time': 1452785075}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-i6fVvGbYN0o/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAADFk/ySMXBwxFB4s/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Highly overpriced and the food is simply not good enough', u'author_name': u'Geir Hegre Romundset', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109986337990222335081', u'time': 1466089132}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 389-6034', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'615', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'615'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan Avenue', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan Ave'}, {u'long_name': u'Williamsburg', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Williamsburg'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11222', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11222'}]}

u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Wny46Gyn0z0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAJ5M/aXQ4L5KUfFw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Awesome food, amazing cultural experience. Couldn't be happier.', u'author_name': u'Alex Guyton', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108550325492765251109', u'time': 1448248098}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-7RCCL3dDkBA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAA4Ec/QqhQmDqkHkU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Food: 4/5 Service: 5/5 Ambiance: 3/5 Noise Level: Moderate-Low The restaurant itself is very unassuming and can be easily missed, since there is not a single visible sign pointing to Aska. The front portion is a garage-style bar, which operates separately from Aska (as in they serve different menu, though bills can be carried over from the bar to the "restaurant"), though the bar does offer food item and shares the same kitchen with Aska. The "restaurant" itself (technically it's just a small sitting area in the back of the bar) seats about 20 max, and serves only tasting menu (7-or 10-course). To be honest, the seats here are somewhat uncomfortable - the chair is too low to the table, and the bench is a bit too high and shallow. Several of my friends and I had to get up and stretch a few times over the 4.5-hour dinner service. Food-wise, there were some very creative dish here. We went for the 10-course tasting menu, but counting all the amuse bouche and complimentary sides, it ended up more like a 15-course menu. While the portion is typically bite-size, save for a few bigger-portion meat courses, there are certainly enough food that you will not leave hungry. Each dish offers some unique mix of flavors (and most dish pack some heavy flavors) or texture. The cauliflower + skate and onion, oates and rapeseed dish were two of my favorites. If you have any dietary concern (we had a vegetarian in our group), they will substitute the course with something else that is equally tasty and creative (granted the price will remain the same). Oh, and don't skip over their bread basket! The house-made butter and the salted chips were absolutely delicious! Service here is top notch. The staffs are very friendly and courteous. The chefs will also come to table-side to put in some finishing touches and explain the course (I had trouble understanding them most of the time through the accent, but that's probably just me). Although the bar got very lively at around midnight, the noise level for the most part is moderate-to-low, and you can easily carry out a conversation at the table.', u'author_name': u'Charlie Shay', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116218922709794678656', u'time': 1382166012}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-SQ2NJqugOJU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAC8/aX-t_CDmeq8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Seriously one of the most amazing meals I've ever had... ever. The 7-couse tasting is so unique. It's Scandinavian food that seems very simple, but they pair flavor in unexpected ways, and when paired with their wine list, it's mind blowingly good. Get a cocktail too. I tried an Aquavit-Molasses-Kombucha mixture that was fab. ', u'author_name': u'Caitlin Heikkila', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117903000049084894177', u'time': 1369244184}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Xz829P8ZCSg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAC8k/C24SLNvwvd4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Wonderful creative and almost surreal Scandinavian foraging experience. u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-DccdmwE3CnY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABfY/PW6F0UoJlxQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Hands down one of the best meals I've ever had! We did the $50 pp chef's choice menu which included 8 courses. You don't get to see what's in the Chef's menu but our waitress asked if we had any favorites or hesitations from the full menu items so that they could try to accommodate. Food was spectacular! Highlights were the tuna tartar, cinnamon strawberry ribs and key lime pie, though you can't go wrong. Service was top-notch and drinks were on point. The bill was higher than what I usually pay for a night out, but well worth it--save this place for a special date! ', u'author_name': u'Juan Parra', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109564473719076784536', u'time': 1459951521}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Delicious tasting menu - Modern American with Asian influences. Rather generous too! Nice casual atmosphere. Excellent drink selection. NB: Tasting menu for 2s only available midweek. Menu is exhaustive so chef selection is the easy way out. ', u'author_name': u'Renee Bartsch', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116689366030300792388', u'time': 1463106881}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-uh2RWSp4ej8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFUs/Tgeq_Mw9v30/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Five stars just for the name!!! "Traif" means not kosher in yiddish.... And the food theme "bacon" is not kosher at all! Not to mention that the food wasn't bad at all. Interesting fact: the chefs wife opened a restaurant 2 houses down called shiksa (xixa) which means "not Jewish female" in Yiddish, (BTW shiksa is a derogatory word amongst the jews) So he is the "traif" jew; and she is the shiksa wife! Very clever marketing... ', u'author_name': u'Flynn R', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109085999558298289263', u'time': 1454061667}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-GfVBpZKF5wk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAADs/lsRCNdtwuEs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'lot of pork based dishes. the strawberry chops were delicious. also has bacon infused drinks, which are special. recommended!', u'author_name': u'Nir Golan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101962017862900110557', u'time': 1461923474}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Needed a venue to celebrate a special occasion that would accommodate a big group. After having a great experience at Xixa we decided to try Traif. Reservations are highly recommended and they accept them 30 days in advance. We opted in for the tasting menu which was really good and the wait staff accommodated all our requests. We tried several of the cocktails- all of which were interesting but I would recommend wine for the tasting menu. Between Xixa and Traif I preferred Xixa but that could have been because of the menu they were offering when we ate there. Remember when Diners catered to customers instead of the other way around, way to many phonies who think there cool for me. Way to many nerds from the suburbs who's parents pay there rent but now there living in BROOKlyn they think there Frank Serpico or Lenny Bruce.', u'author_name': u'Tom Hayes', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109598022480041473261', u'time': 1457741970}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-B10UJGNOrAw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAJWM/f1fIM9x8OUY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Terrible service, they didn't even know how to mix their own drinks or what the drinks were when they came out. u'+1 718-858-5641', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'La Cigogne is a fantastic French restaurant that can host large parties or just simply have a romantic dinner for two. The beautifully designed cocktails and the homemade French cuisine makes for a wonderful experience. Their fireplace adds a nice touch for the chilly evenings to relax and enjoy the company of the regulars and staff. By the way, one of the best burgers in all the boroughs!', u'author_name': u'Franchesca Green', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117056030097914813585', u'time': 1458763822}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-whUOgWNuYXM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAYw/Ecp4urzeVew/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I was quite disappointed with our Friday breakfast at this establishment. I Googled breakfast spots in Downtown Brooklyn and this spot came up as a suggestion. Sure enough I looked up their menu and they had a decent breakfast/brunch menu. Here's where it goes wrong. On their website the "brunch" items are lumped into the same category as everything else so it's quite unclear that during the week they do not have a brunch menu. We found that out when our waiter brought our menus and I see it's a lunch menu. When I asked him if they have breakfast items he said no. Well, we didn't want to waste our time and have to look for another spot so we skimmed the menu and ordered. Note it was 11am and the restaurant was empty. We waited a while before he took our order. When he did come to our table we ordered coffee, salad Nicoise, steak frites and some wine. We ordered the steak medium rare. We got a medium well steak that was chewy, hard to cut and quite bland. The fries were OK. The salad was soaked in dressing. Literally so drenched, I couldn't finish it. I really wanted something sweet to end this rather disasterous meal so I ordered the chocolate mousse. It barely passed as good. Some things look great in writing but when it comes to the table it's nothing like you imagine. We finally are done and ask for the bill. Lo and behold, they charge us for refills on regular coffee. That really took the cake. I'm over this place and do not suggest going either. It's a true disappointment.', u'author_name': u'Rebecca Appel', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106782353247582225465', u'time': 1464380990}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Wonderful restaurant, my experience was just perfect; if you want travel to the heart of France in just a visit and have some delicious authentic French cuisine this is the place to be. The staff is warm, professional and welcoming. Food is superbe and the wine selection is meticulously well made. I felt home and well taking care, can't wait to be back to try the rest of the menu...', u'author_name': u'Thomas Caron', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110343484216329049203', u'time': 1458957780}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is a wonderful French restaurant not far from my apartment. Their menu and cocktails seem to change with the season, never disappointing! During the winter I had mulled wine, brought me back to the time my husband and I were strolling around the Marché de Noël in France. Now that the weather is warm we enjoy having our tarte flambé out on the deck. I highly recommend The Chèvre its my favorite and always on the menu.', u'author_name': u'Leslie Frey', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102136620222390107919', u'time': 1459037455}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Everytime I visit New York I have to stop at my favorite french restaurant . From the moment you arrive it's nothing but a pleasent experience . The staff is incredibly friendly. The place itself is impeccably clean. The food is amazing. The tarte flambee and the steak frites are my among my personal favorites. The fire place during the winter really adds to the relaxed warm ambience . I give it 5 stars .', u'author_name': u'Keith Kanner', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105599579051157367268', u'time': 1458945387}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 858-5641', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'213-215', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'213-215'}, {u'long_name': u'Union Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Union St'}, {u'long_name': u'Carroll Gardens', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Carroll Gardens'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11231', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11231'}]}

u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U4IBRWcWvhA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABB3c/KSohftLJ008/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Jamming spot with delicious and inventive pizzas and a burger that's only available in a limited quantity each evening. We thoroughly enjoyed everything, ramp pizza, the burger, and the iceberg salad. I thought $26.00 was STEEP for the burger. It's good, but there are better or just as good ones for less money. Stick to the pizzas and the wings if they have them. The wings are a cross cultural mash up with Korean based sauce and Italian pecorino sprinkled on top. If there's a wait, you can put your name on the list and they will text you when your table is ready. It's a little loud for my tastes, but definitely worth a visit ', u'author_name': u'Jackie Gordon Singing Chef', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109673791694826464177', u'time': 1461931209}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-8WYXEr3wqXg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAVQE/bpPwPi0NKBk/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Place had been on my list for a couple months but living in Manhattan, was unsure when I'd ever get to it. Well tonight was that night with a buddy in town and staying in that neighborhood. Menu was pretty manageable but hard to get excited about the spartan descriptions, so we looked around and picked one that looked good (the colony) and the namesake that sounded good (emily). Both were fantastic and the charred octopus we got to start was also done very nicely as well if not a bit over priced. Can't say I'd drag people off the island for it, but if you're in the hood, this and a stroll to Ample Hills for dessert is a pretty great, if not the most healthy, outting.', u'author_name': u'Jason Mather', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108266811036611997447', u'time': 1464838749}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-NaD0JhJeNDI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAfeQ/CllGnsqlMxQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Came by for an early dinner on Sunday and had the best of times. The service was friendly and quick. Can't seem to go wrong with the food selection. We love the pizza (obviously), particularly The Colony, but was surprised at how much we love the Emmy Burger (oh that Emmy sauce) and the banana pudding. Emily also offers great selections of local craft beers - Other Half and Finback were offered during my visit.', u'author_name': u'Albert Oeswadi', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105822920391209886733', u'time': 1459249652}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-6SH3gTvYc7k/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAWY0/VPhUZKJKYHA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'My friend wanted to go here for dinner; I guess he saw it on TV. I was pretty disappointed. He told me the burgers were featured and supposed to be great. Well they didn't have any of those. The couple sitting next to us said they only sell 25 a night. There's no other meat supplier that can sell that blend? I ended up with one of the red sauce pizzas and the sauce was terrible. It had zero flavor at all. When I want sweet red sauce I go to a certain pizza place. When I want acidic sauce I go to another. But I am not even kidding you literally couldn't taste the red sauce - like it was spooned out of a Hunts can. I also found the wine pour to be less than generous, maybe because it was served in a kiddie cup. Anyway, $90 for two people, one drink each and two 12" mediocre pizzas. One star for ambiance as there was a fight in the bar area while we were there. Total bust. ', u'author_name': u'Christina', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112596999638649809158', u'time': 1455329361}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Every item we had was excellent. The Emily white pizza was the favorite, closely followed by the Vodka pie. Start to finish, zero complaints. Also, the burger is fantastic, and yes, you will need to get there early for it. Reading other reviews here it's prob worth noting, Emily running out of this burger is less about ruining your experience and generating 2-star reviews, but more about offering the highest possible and freshest quality burger. In doing so, they likely dont use day(s) old meat. To avoid throwing out high quality (expensive) meat, the burger is limited. The important thing here is not to take it personal and allow it to soil the rest of what is guaranteed to be a great dinner. Place to be!', u'author_name': u'Tom Puls', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108088816422866676196', u'time': 1449952857}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-ZFhy-EZPCjw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAANvk/TEXrn--qkzQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Since moving to Brooklyn two years ago, I have heard of a few pizza places that should be priorities to visit. Franny's is one of them. I am a bit surprised by the 3.7 rating because I found Franny's to be very good; it met our expectations. Things got off to a bumpy start though. When I entered the restaurant I indicated there were three people in our party and asked how long the wait would be. The hostess (who may have been filling in) looked at me with a confused look, which confused me. She indicated our party wasn't complete (my wife had just stepped away to find a bathroom). I was so confused that at one point I asked if something was wrong. That awkward interaction aside, the rest of our experience was positive. We were told there would be a 45-minute wait but it ended up being only 30 minutes. We asked our server about ways to remove meat and dairy from the pizzas. Usually this is easy. It was a bit of a challenge at Franny's but nothing too bad. He indicated the chefs are particular about which pizzas they make changes to. It seemed easy enough to us to not include pieces of sausage and throw on asparagus but I digress. We ended up with two great pizzas for three of us. They skimped on the basil but otherwise, the pizzas were excellent. Very good flavor and the crust was very nice. It was thin yet crisp. It didn't get soggy from the toppings. If there weren't so many other pizza places to try in Brooklyn I would definitely return. Fries are some of the best in NYC.', u'author_name': u'Michael Correia', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108485254872394049372', u'time': 1460054399}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-whUOgWNuYXM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAYw/Ecp4urzeVew/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I've always heard such amazing reviews of Prime Meats so I came here for dinner with a couple of friends. It's a German style restaurant/bar with nice wooden decor. We were seated right away and our waiter quickly came over with menus. Slight issue with our waiter. His accent was super thick and truly hard to understand what he was saying. E.G. he was telling us about this amazing ribs special and we were at the point of ordering it. One of us replied back something about the ribs, it took us about 5 minutes to realize he was saying shrimp. It would have sucked if we did order it because we don't eat shrimp. Ordered a bunch of dishes.. And all of them, seriously, all of them were so very fabulous. I was amazed at the burger I ordered. Cooked to a perfect medium rare. So juicy and full of flavor. The steak too, was ah-mazing. I absolutely enjoyed the vibe at the restaurant and the food was top notch. A couple of tweaks and they could definitely get 5 stars.', u'author_name': u'Rebecca Appel', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106782353247582225465', u'time': 1460239873}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-HjTLuyNNO_I/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABiU/_BDClZl0pHQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'One of my favorite meals of all time is from here. u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-MYS9cPOdaTc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACU/k_ifIwqA9v8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I am happy that I discovered Roberta’s. It is little far from where I live, but when you discover something unique, it worth the drive. I had a mission to find the best Pizza in NYC few years ago, and for some reason Roberta’s went bellow my Radar. Not anymore. Special Pizza that bring respect to Pizza in New York.', u'author_name': u'Robert White', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103499768777188473024', u'time': 1462930251}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Pizza in Brooklyn hipster twist style. The pizza here is very fresh and the Robertas team has very unique flavor combinations. I opted for the beastmaster, lil' stinker, and cheesus Christ. Out of the three the best one seemed to be the lil' stinker overall. We did miss meat in terms of getting more than veggies although the beastmaster has sausage. The beastmaster had a sour bite to it that wasn't so appetizing. The cheesus Christ was a bit bland once your taste buds became accustomed to the first bite. I wanted to pour hot sauce on all three. My dinner buddies hated the community bench seating. I found it appropriate for the neighborhood and fitting for the Robertas experience. Overall I'd say fresh pizza, over priced appetizers, ok drinks. Go on a weekday so you don't wait crazy hours because time is precious and no one should wait 3 hours for pizza that isn't even classic NY style.', u'author_name': u'mt mt', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102589716808009764384', u'time': 1465859955}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Zm3M0h3HMbE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABXI/OB3sxeChajM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Really good pizza. A little over hyped but worth a short wait. The portions are kinda hard to gauge. The only way it really works is if you do three pizzas for four people. Definitely worth checking out', u'author_name': u'Michael Samaroo', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108957989918005844461', u'time': 1465961737}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-zVNSB7yUCI0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAARjk/6vkVEMQvjOw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Nice cozy atmosphere - with an entrance door that is not really revealing of what to expect behind it. One of the best pizzas you can find in Brooklyn and possibly the entire city. Prices are reasonable, maybe only service could be improved (the person who served our table looked in a bad mood and was far from warm and welcoming).', u'author_name': u'Stefano Durden', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108320022078031603700', u'time': 1459878990}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-7O3sQwpL9lg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAADCE/eBSXRhTDU7w/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Roberta's is great! I've heard stories of two hour waits. But, we showed up at 11:30am on a Friday and were seated in their super cute indoor courtyard area immediately. The service was spot on. Everyone was extremely attentive. And our waters never less than half full. Our server was very knowledgeable about the menu (wtf is sorell?) and gave great recommendations. The food was phenomenal. We started with the beer and avocado salad, which was really refreshing (although don't expect a typical leafy green salad). We even saved the bowl for dipping our pizza crust. Speaking of pizza, it was a perfect Neapolitan style crust with great toppings. We got a lil' stinker and an original. Both were delicious! And their chili infused oil at each table really took things over the top!! If you can avoid the alleged wait that they are known for, Roberta's is definitely a place to keep going back to!', u'author_name': u'Matthew Klein', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107653957577740623160', u'time': 1463665858}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 417-1118', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'261', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'261'}, {u'long_name': u'Moore Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Moore St'}, {u'long_name': u'East Williamsburg', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'East Williamsburg'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11206', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11206'}, {u'long_name': u'3816', u'types': [u'postal_code_suffix'], u'short_name': u'3816'}]}

u'ChIJq7ijyFxZwokRHmhIYot48d0', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 718-218-7500', u'vicinity': u'160 North 12th Street, Brooklyn', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Review of Little Elm: Amazing culinary experience. 8 flavorful, inventive courses, perfectly prepared. Fois gras ravioli w/ chicken & celery infused consommé and white truffle one of the best dishes I've ever had. Wine pairing also excellent. Dark seductive ambience in hip Williamsburg setting was fun and not overly pretentious. Chefs extremely knowledgeable and engaging. Highly recommend.', u'author_name': u'James Wiley', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106652421851149840485', u'time': 1416760709}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-g7zvg8B7V_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAB2M/vPuL7qlg97c/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Love this restaurant. I went the first time for my wedding anniversary, after make reservation I was informed that they were doing a private event, so I re-schedule because my wife's birthday is two weeks after. They cater us for the inconvenience with a great dessert and a glass of wine. The food is delicious, fish and chips, the burger, duck are excellent. The ambiance is perfect for a romantic dinner and also for a celebration.', u'author_name': u'gustavo bernal', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114545942736553894568', u'time': 1415714231}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-gftKWB9o2UU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAB-U/AeAsfDT0CUA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Breakfast review: Arrived at 9am on a overcast Sunday to an empty restaurant. Though the dining area is sunken below street level windows at street level bathe the room in light. In conjunction with what appeared to be a faux living wall, this created a sleek yet amiable ambiance. Started with Black coffee. Server clarified if I wanted cream (no) and still brought sugar. Coffee tasted very burnt. For 5 bucks, I'd typically expect a single brew as well. Ordered the breakfast sandwich. It arrived on a depressingly large plate. 'Brioche' felt more like a hamburger bun. Eggs were nice and creamy but bacon was sliced amazingly thin akin to McDonald's. Stilton cheese was the highlight. Though perhaps they shine for dinner, I was not impressed with my breakfast at the elm. egg or diner blow this out of the water any day. ', u'author_name': u'Beck Kloss', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104691438595584254062', u'time': 1415547240}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-n4RfaGzHTXo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEg/mX-hDgQqI1M/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I've so missed Paul Liebrandt's artistry at Corton and we were not disappointed at The Elm tonight. All of the dishes had the finesse and attention to detail that we love. I hate to sound snobbish, but I think many of the negative reviewers have expectations that are misaligned with this chef and his new playground. We throughly enjoyed each bite and will venture out again from Lower Manhattan to Williamsburg again. So much fun. ', u'author_name': u'Jim F', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100547086832719240614', u'time': 1399891274}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-qW_AOj5Okbk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABnYo/j64RO0gnJ4c/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Amazing food and wine. Beautiful space. The vegetable "pot" is amazing. {u'lat': 40.68074854999999, u'lng': -73.9942669}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.68054275000001, u'lng': -73.99464369999998}}}, u'adr_address': u'329 Smith St, Brooklyn, NY 11231, USA', u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-GjBYevqB8Sk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAKLY/IL9p8uiRJpU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I did not expect this place to be authentic but I was curious to try it since I had not seen Cha Ca on a menu before. The pho broth lacked depth and just tasted really salty. I salt my food well so I was surprised. The Cha Ca was okay, worth a try if you've never had before. I left disappointed with a large bill. ', u'author_name': u'Anna Nguyen', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100512790600961416787', u'time': 1462500579}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U4IBRWcWvhA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABB3c/KSohftLJ008/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I want this place to be amazing since I don't always want to go to the city for good Vietnamese or Asian. It's not authentic and I don't expect it to be. I found myself chewing on the tough-ish green papaya salad that was cut into ribbons instead of shredded wondering why they prepared it that way. It looks cool on the plate, but it's not great in your mouth. It's traditionally shredded for ease of chew. I did like the addition of Malaysian jerky. The dressing lacked punch. The sea bass was a riff on the Vietnamese dish Chả Cá Thăng Long with turmeric and dill. Their version was innocuous, but seemed to be gutted flavor-wise. It couldn't hold a candle to other versions I've had. I liked the pressed rice noodles on the dish. Again, it was certainly not a bad dish. The few times I've eaten here I always leave wishing the flavor of the food was more on the authentic or at an interpretation or spin on the traditional dish that improved it. The service was friendly and efficient.', u'author_name': u'Jackie Gordon Singing Chef', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109673791694826464177', u'time': 1456774310}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-HjTLuyNNO_I/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABiU/_BDClZl0pHQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Love this place. I have never been disappointed with anything I have ordered...except for this spicy lemonade thing I ordered one time. Spicy Lemonade is nasty. ', u'author_name': u'Aaron Monson', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115066853869970032919', u'time': 1452491047}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-A7Lpv9-5ARo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAEns/L2Y5E89jeeE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Love the food and it has a super cozy ambiance. The cocktails are great too. ', u'author_name': u'Isabel Barrera', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100861161920583803356', u'time': 1449456118}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ldUam56Jmgk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABAY/yyU4oFNNeNQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The food was just alright, I kind of regret walking all the way here and not just going to Hanco's. We started with the spring rolls. They didn't have too much filling or flavor. For my main I had the lobster pho special. It has a tomato seafood broth with 3 full lobster claw pieces as well as a small amount of tail meat, it also had tomatoes and pork meatballs. I enjoyed my dish though it was very fishy tasting which turned off my friends. The 2 people I went with got the chicken and beef pho so I was able to try those as well. I'm not sure what exactly was in them but the broth had a flavor that just didn't agree with me. We had the brussels sprouts with out dinners which were delicious, definitely the highlight of our meal. I think we were all pretty meh at the end of the meal, it wasn't bad but there are much better options for pho in the city. Service was pretty good for the most part but towards the end we sat without water for a good 15 minutes.', u'author_name': u'Matthew R', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109564894570570374797', u'time': 1426524507}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(347) 689-4699', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'329', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'329'}, {u'long_name': u'Smith Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Smith St'}, {u'long_name': u'Carroll Gardens', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Carroll Gardens'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11231', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11231'}]}

u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Kekp5v8jous/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAl8/syUOiQC1rcQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'There's a ton of good, modern pizza in New York these days, and Marta's no exception. That said, the best things on this menu don't necessarily have dough. Give the entrees a shot and you won't be disappointed.', u'author_name': u'Dean Praetorius', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103347174328293237566', u'time': 1464923338}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-hL_QGreRwwQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGoc/Kk9cBhd1rIo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great pizza, fantastic staff! Pretty good selection of wines by the glass. It's not Neapolitan pizza but it's just as good. Though one pro-tip is to eat it while it's hot. We only got pizzas and wine but I'd come back for anything here. Salsiccia: Sausage and mushroom, perfectly balanced. The mushrooms outshone the sausage ... and the sausage was some of the best I've had. Patate alla Carbonara: Potatoes and guanciale. Wow! Very close to perfection. The only knock is that it's expensive. That said, though, you're definitely getting what you paid for.', u'author_name': u'Johnny Tan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102728581437805238916', u'time': 1463319197}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-WNP-4Xw2v5Q/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACU8/1CDmeGjBsl4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The special pizza was unreal, and the Cocktails are a revelation. Literally, small changes to Cocktail Bar staples take them above and beyond, and they bar-tender really knew her stuff. A great night, I am looking forward to coming back again and again!', u'author_name': u'Abe Rudy', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113989223638665394858', u'time': 1465249368}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Probably one of the only pizzerias in the city classy enough for a business line, Marta has thin, crisp pies and a slew of wonderful little antipasto. We were a party of six, and with the slight encouragement of our waiter we went for six pies. We wandered our way through smoked meats, crisp vegetables and even some old fashioned cheese on the way to 1,000 calories or more. Before we got there was nice broccoli with chili flakes, chicken meatballs and other treats not exactly needed with the feast to come. I'd been meaning to come here since this place opened, but it took nearly two years to get around to it. I wasn't disappointed. I will say this place looks bigger in photographs, so when coming a peak time a reservation is probably a good idea. For those who happen to be staying in the hotel, that's pretty good luck; this is a nice place.', u'author_name': u'YU ER', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101298514089007651078', u'time': 1466462460}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Good cracker thin pizza, tried the funghi and salsiccia. Both were tasty, and the funghi surprisingly good even though I'm not a huge mushroom fan. Wait wasn't very long. ', u'author_name': u'Leon Lin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103299504307574664914', u'time': 1461192835}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 651-3800', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'The Redbury Hotel', u'types': [u'premise'], u'short_name': u'The Redbury Hotel'}, {u'long_name': u'29', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'29'}, {u'long_name': u'East 29th Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'E 29th St'}, {u'long_name': u'Midtown', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Midtown'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10016', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10016'}]}

u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-DhmPfr23FWI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAo/iYEXCKrHj3g/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'We got there almost right after they opened, so there were only few people in the inside, but it quickly got busy. The inside is rather small, they have nice counter seating on one side, and large picnic style tables on the other side. The tables are large, and are meant to share with other customers. The entrance side of the wall have large windows from floor to ceiling, flooding the inside with natural light, illuminating their simple, sleek interior. We started off with a nice cup of coffee. We wanted milk to go with the coffee, and it took as asking 2 different servers 2-3 times for it, before they finally brought the milk... The service was not consistent, it was ok at the beginning, but quickly became the game of catch. It was not easy to get their attention, even though it was not packed. I guess it was a bit more relaxed atmosphere, which we were ok with, but when we needed milk for our coffee, or refill of water, or wanted to get a check, it took more than enough effort and time. Other than that, they were very nice and helpful (once you catch them). The food was very good, even though a bit more pricey than I prefer, but they do come with high quality food. I have not had any disappointing food from any of their location, so you know I will be going back for some more soon! Read my full review of this restaurant and food on my food blog, foodlovergirl.', u'author_name': u'Foodlover Girl', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116328682135597130625', u'time': 1463267654}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-0eoq-EmiuCM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAKo/JiU904s17RQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Had a Reuben and a falafel salad pita. They have good menu options plus some yummy mimosas, so it's definitely somewhere to sit and try a few different plates.', u'author_name': u'Lucy Orozco', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115904344658598419865', u'time': 1462061212}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U4IBRWcWvhA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABB3c/KSohftLJ008/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The flanken with cabbage and turnips was divine. It was a comfort food FLAVA BOMB! The boyfriend said the Hoyt Dog aka hot dog was the best dish, but he's a dude. Nice mix of textures and tastes in the beet fattoush salad. Loved the pickle plate! We had the duck chopped liver which was a special and nicely adorned with gribenes and pickles. Since we're both native New Yorkers, I was surprised that my dining companion had not ever heard of Orwasher's Bakery as he was cooking over their pumpernickel bread. The potato pancakes were oddly oxidized in the middle, which was a tad unsightly, but we enjoyed them. Points for serving them with both nice thick sour cream and applesauce. 40.68782795, u'lng': -73.99546724999999}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.68772215, u'lng': -73.99584905}}}, u'adr_address': u'268 Clinton St, Brooklyn, NY 11201, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 718-422-0065', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Superb restaurant. Absolutely worthy of its Michelin Star rating for both its service and food. The dishes, while on the surface don't seem too expensive (~$12-24), but they quickly add up as they are quite small. Expect to spend $50-75 per head before drinks.', u'author_name': u'Mac Carr', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116537524219553592799', u'time': 1461355760}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Brought here my family with two kids to celebrate Valentines and to give ides to my husband on Spanish food. Best time for us was lunch time to avoid croud and not to be nervous. Plus I read Zagat that name la Vara on of the best. On arrival we were given menu that contained famose Spanish dishes. Then we found out that it was wrong menu and lunch did not contain much of "spanish", so we had to eat baked potatoes, hamburger (would say this is international,not Spanish). My last hope was for famose churros which I were two days taking about to my kid. But we were told they run out of all sweets (just one left,but not churros). And this is not the end of the day yet! They shall preview that on Valentines they shall order more! So we were very much dissupointed and my family did not have taste of "spanish". Being lot in Europe and knowing about Michelin star restaurants I could never belive it had one before.Just a regular place with nice small expensive dishes. ', u'author_name': u'Katerina Litvinovska', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115931105747217350264', u'time': 1455500637}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-5pgQULuRLP0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABFnQ/NkO1nEMGxJ4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is pretty much the most expensive Tapas you can find, and it is totally worth it. Everything we ate was phenomenal. Flavor combinations that I could not have imagined. Phenomenal drinks. Sherry menu. The wait staff was super friendly, quick, and responsive.', u'author_name': u'Bryan Carroll', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101059867336514035179', u'time': 1447963340}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-uPVQi5bGFXI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAH8/HqCezF3EuVg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Excellent dinner. Food was really impressive. Loved our cocktails. Only complaint is super tight quarters. One long table in the middle and a few other two and four tops. Probably seats 40 plus bar. We were two people seated at the long table which is actually five two tops pushed together without even the pretense of separation between them, so be prepared to sit with your neighbors. Still, worth it for the food.', u'author_name': u'Kate Kosche', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107535386740478019534', u'time': 1449363870}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U4IBRWcWvhA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABB3c/KSohftLJ008/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'One of my favorite food places in my neighborhood! I prefer going for brunch only because the noise level at dinner which is often busy, is deafening. Brunch is more chilled out and the food is sooooo good! Recommend: Huevos A La Flamenca, Patatas Bravas', u'author_name': u'Jackie Gordon Singing Chef', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109673791694826464177', u'time': 1450112619}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 422-0065', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'268', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'268'}, {u'long_name': u'Clinton Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Clinton St'}, {u'long_name': u'Cobble Hill', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Cobble Hill'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11201', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11201'}]}

u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-254-3000', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Visited for Sunday brunch. 5 stars for food. 3 for a painfully slow service. Had a great duck hash, the trout and eggs Benedict were superb. Loved the art and decor. Just let down by the waiting around.', u'author_name': u'Nick Edwards', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103707122988859596407', u'time': 1462198424}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Just had dinner there at 6pm 6/27/2016. 3* for your house bread. 1* for your food... Guys, please low some of your sodium...your sauce is way to salty. Your appitetize (the green pea leave sauce), main dish (COD with hazelnut sauce) , and side dish (green peas and bacons) are all salty.', u'author_name': u'Chanren C', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100126580376362625003', u'time': 1467075695}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-DsZ1eteypY8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAA8/hZCNFhNqCso/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Initially the vibe of this eatery was excellent, the atmosphere was welcoming, staff were attentive and all around: this was until the last time we ate there (about two months ago) as we were leaving, we held hands out the door. And we overheard the hostess sarcastically make a comment about us to a server: "oh is this place turning into another gar bar" We stopped dead in our tracks and looked back at her, she noticed and quickly walked away. So did we, no matter how good the place is, one snarky comment like that can kill a committed customer. We later tried to contact the management, to no avail there was not a response.', u'author_name': u'Jesse Perrin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106325967622151570551', u'time': 1464273936}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-TqDpQK1x4jA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABk/SSUYUwupWwo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Explosive flavours and traditional combinations. Try the chicken and crepes, with tarragon and cream, mint and radishes... Atmosphere was welcoming also. Sommelier made the evening memorable.', u'author_name': u'Jamie Mabilat', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103190710462412132478', u'time': 1463535958}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-9AxVtBsdKQM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAYU/AA8yY6TRxeg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The lamb carpaccio. Holy f***. Spices sprinkled on top. Get this. Their bread service is excellent as well. I want a tub of whatever the spread is they give you. Grab a seat at the bar and hang out. (It will get loud.) Edited to just say holy sh*t their brussels sprouts with bits of bacon and whatever dressing or vinaigrette my God.', u'author_name': u'Dennis Malabunga', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114355445597409586144', u'time': 1457072587}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 254-3000', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'180', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'180'}, {u'long_name': u'Ludlow Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Ludlow St'}, {u'long_name': u'Lower East Side', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lower East Side'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10002', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10002'}]}

u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-1toxVaDxHcs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAhI/_KXiN1GxcOc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I went here for my birthday, and I can't say enough positive things about it. The staff is mind-glowingly friendly and attentive, and not in a pestering way. Everyone is well-spoken, well-informed, and the service is outstanding. The decor is modern and classy, while also being accessible, but the food is an immersive experience using simple flavors in elegant ways. For their new spring menu, there was strong emphasis on peas, artichokes, fresh seafood, and mushrooms. This is not the kind of tasting menu you go home afterwards and bemoan because your insides hurt; it's a lovely, just-apt journey of food.', u'author_name': u'Carolyn De Melo', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106494382477571149346', u'time': 1462824823}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-sk_X3T5i_Og/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAlk/veKfUMy_y-M/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great upscale restaurant. Go there with good friends to celebrate, bring your better half for a romantic dinner, you won't be disappointed.', u'author_name': u'Glenn S. u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-srlxLnE6NFc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAADZw/J-28eGoG2A0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'My family at first ventured to Quality Meats (just around the corner), but as a walk-in, couldn't find a table, so the lovely lady arrange for a table for us at Quality Italian instead. Sat down and our server who was amazingly excellent with the recommendations. The decor is really nice, the server's service was really good. But what I wasn't prepared for was the food. The seafood platter was really awesome, and when my steak arrived, honestly, was the best i have ever tasted. And I've tasted my share of meat and this is by far the best. Of course, this is just my opinion and I like how my meat is a little charred on the outside, making it really crispy, while my knife cut through the meat like butter on the insider where it is so amazingly tender. On my next trip back to NYC, I'll definitely make my stop here. But be warned; the price matched the quality.', u'author_name': u'Jui Hong Teoh', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104902586026265303304', u'time': 1461949247}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Easily one of the best meals and dining experiences I've had. Everything is so well done and tasteful, from the bar area in the front where they make an excellent Old Fashioned, to the hostess and servers and sommelier, they simply are all great at what they do. And the food is out of this world. Braised veal shank that literally falls off the bone when you stick your knife into it. Homemade pasta that's cooked to a perfect consistency. Their "bread" is actually these little garlic balls that are puffy and crunchy at the same time (we actually asked for a second round of those). And the desserts were delicious as well. The steaks are well seasoned and delicious as well. The worst part about this place is deciding between which dish to order. It's on the expensive side, but absolutely worth it.', u'author_name': u'Chris Albanese', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116295983314508366194', u'time': 1462545095}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-tOVfVDLXdHQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAaA/vXhr9dK7VMU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Happy 1 year anniversary baby!!! Started at the bar with an amazing Cosmo for me And Long Island for my love. Service is amazing. Thank you to our waiter Andy. You helped make it a great experience. Music is that chill kind of soul/romance. Just puts you in the right mood, love. Had an amazing time watching my husband enjoy the best aged rib bone in steak ever. Don't think I can find a place to top it. My filet was perfectly cooked. Juicy juicy juicy. Kudos to the chef I highly recommend and I will definitely visit again. My husbands input is umm umm umm. Fork drops! Skipped dessert for a show. ', u'author_name': u'Jennifer Asencio', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105647183099001576086', u'time': 1455578895}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-fzn--ie60xk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAu4/Tsds66L4B6E/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Solid quality food, but not worth the price in my opinion. A bit loud, but otherwise a pleasant experience. ', u'author_name': u'Ishita Aloni', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117600620661968637796', u'time': 1460510697}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Such a classy environment. The service was outstanding, the waiters were very attentive and knowledgeable on the restaurant and menu. The food is to die for every bite was better than the last. I highly recommend this restaurant. And Don't even get me started on how jaw dropping amazing the dessert was at the end. The only bad part was that is was over with at the end of the night.
