u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-f6zk77Lucqc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAD_o/u3kBS9JkARc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Go to the bar, THE BAR!One of the most wonderful bars in the city, both aesthetically and quality of drinks. Joey Mesina will give you not only the best Manhattan of your existence but he will pair it with hospitality second to none. It's a quiet space to actually hold a conversation with someone without battling the music and other elements that bars can often force upon you. With your choice of sitting at the bar or a few tables that have lounge chairs in which the bartenders will come around and offer to make and bring you drinks!The food, seriously, the FOOD! The Swedish meatballs are a must so soft and moist, paired perfectly with lingonberries and mushroom. Then move on to the shrimp skagen, I would eat jars of that without the bread...forever. It's worth your time and worth your money. Make a trip out there!', u'author_name': u'Austin Bonk', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114575973523327868119', u'time': 1465829021}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-FQXKCRlwsSw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAs/IAP4A9dsVJo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Michelin two star rated. I personally don't have much experience in dining Scandinavian food, hence would not be so sure on the exact criteria. However I indeed enjoyed myself here, with their delicate presentation as well as delicious seafood. Chef's tasting was my choice and my favorite dishes were king crab, lamb meat as well as the final dessert - the bird nest. In my opinion, many courses were a bit too sour in taste and hard for me to digest the flavor...towards the end, a menu with complimentary chocolate babka was brought to us so as to remember all the tastes! Out server was very attentive and kept coming to us and checking on our status. Atmosphere was also simple and relax. A strong suggest to anyone who is interested in exotic food.', u'author_name': u'Monica 夏', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110319965619207643361', u'time': 1458873974}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The atmosphere is great. The presentation of the food is superb. Matjes herring tartare was great (must have). The rest of the food was really good, but nothing jumped out at me that would make me come back.', u'author_name': u'Hansel M.', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101924179346976510823', u'time': 1457149016}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-SEpj_FNuka0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAMIk/Gx3vksmL5jg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Wonderful Scandinavian cuisine with a fresh approach. Service A+ go there and enjoy!', u'author_name': u'Pamela Laity', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113188188386983848911', u'time': 1463432288}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Had a work event 12 of us that dined in - phenomenal service for a large party! We literally got 3 of everything on the menu and they structured it to come out in a beautifully timed way! The cocktails were amazing -- amazing service. Highly recommend.', u'author_name': u'Sales Inquiries', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114839807889032381711', u'time': 1463432359}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This place was so amazing!!! One of my favorite meals of 2016 so far. We also had a groupon for a four course tasting but they were nice enough to give us some extra stuff. Everything we tried beat my expectations. The real surprise was the black bean tartare - It didn't sound that exciting but it was shockingly good. The music was fun and the staff was so nice and helpful. I can't wait to go back! The reason we went was for the grilled glazed donut (which comes with the tasting) because we saw a photo on Instagram and it was even better than it looks. The cocktails weren't the best I've ever had but we did have a martini made with some local gin we'd never tried before that was sooo good and their wine list is also impressive. 👍💯', u'author_name': u'Louise DeMartin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107099605939555143397', u'time': 1460297652}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-cuZC3baP-E4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAM0/bJZwe4Pe9CE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Bought a groupon for a 4-course tasting with my girlfriend. It included a glass of prosecco and a dessert. They ended up giving us 5 courses, politely catering to my gf's dietary restrictions, our server was so kind, attentive, and humorous. The Meals: Everything was perfect. Not only was each dish extremely delectable, but they were arranged and presented beautifully. It was like eating delicious food art, and in perfect portions. Atmosphere: Dimly lit, not too crowded, no loud weird music. Over all it's a fantastic new place. A really good replacement of the old sushi place that used to be there. ', u'author_name': u'Lily Olsen-Ecker', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117319443338441461699', u'time': 1459097433}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-beTBNK_kiK8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABk/Qg4MXB_pr88/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Amazing menu, beautiful craft cocktails, phenomenal wine list and beautiful intimate space. u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Kekp5v8jous/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAl8/syUOiQC1rcQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Lunch or dinner, Upland is always a go-to if you've got the cash. With the exception of the burger on the lunch menu (who doesn't have a burger on their menu these days?) everything seems like a unique take on an Italian cuisine. It's light and refreshing without being unsubstantial. Always a well-balanced meal in a cozy environment. You have to try the giant mushroom, and the beef tartare is an experience in and of itself.', u'author_name': u'Dean Praetorius', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103347174328293237566', u'time': 1464877641}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-NkQuqkClw0A/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFEM/EnOHgKVWnAw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'One of the best burgers in town! If you're a burger lover, don't forget to try this place. Also, not too hard to get reservations for lunch so that's a plus for NYC. The porchetta sandwich was also quite good but the burger definitely one-upped the other sandwiches we tried. The ambiance of the place is casual and comfortable with high ceilings and floor to ceiling windows so it lets the light in. Good place to bring your parents who are visiting from outta town!', u'author_name': u'Rohenne Lee', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105603284385958429156', u'time': 1463268407}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-XA1DWQbGbGg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAA1oE/m_yY2wFAd6g/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Amazing food. Literally every dish was superb: kale sausage pizza, chicken liver pasta, grilled hen if he woods, lamb neck — all straight amazing. Can't wait to come back.', u'author_name': u'Ivan Vovnenko', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102172401918858106420', u'time': 1461952000}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-OJRy4LPqaKg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACo/j2FPW3VVZZ4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Pretty rude staff, especially the host and hostess. Super smug, and seem very delighted to turn you away even when you try reserving weeks in advance. Even 2 weeks out apparently there is no room unless you want to eat lunch at 3pm. They act as if they had a michelin star and that their food is enough to keep them in business. Can't wait to see this yuppy unoriginal trash close down in a year, like every other one in NYC before it.', u'author_name': u'Danny Ferraro', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108391584002664557534', u'time': 1462123791}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Our food was horrible! The mushroom appetizer tasted like a skunk, the chicken had little flavor! Way over priced and disappointing! We had to go eat after we left. Also very loud atmosphere!', u'author_name': u'Joan Johnson', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107870977822992750734', u'time': 1467138266}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 686-1006', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'345', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'345'}, {u'long_name': u'Park Avenue South', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Park Ave S'}, {u'long_name': u'Flatiron District', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Flatiron District'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10010', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10010'}]}

is that is as good as the one you buy from your local big store- that is the $8 dollar whole ready baked chicken. The menu has about 5 or 6 items [differences of sauces-all baked the same]- sounds like a joke, maybe OK for a fast food joint. Other people like it, judging by the others comments and that the place was crowded. We had to wait for a while, but it was busy, so it is understandable. If you cannot visit the restaurant, visit your local store, in fact in our local store the chicken is slightly better [juicier], but I will skip the name, not to think this is a hidden ad. suggestion to the restaurant- maybe you should think starting to offer boiled eggs, say for $5 a piece.', u'author_name': u'stoyan petkov', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114721515986549273200', u'time': 1460576288}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Wsyy1Oj8hLc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAuk/Zo1dQ0ZK3kU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Do you like rotisserie chicken? If so, prepare to have some of the best you can find. The birds are juicy and tender and, although the restaurant claims to offer much more than "just" chicken, this is really the star, along with its delicious rotisserie potatoes. Other main courses are perfectly well executed but nothing special, and the other sides are nothing about which to write home. Salads are quite nice, and the taste Tatin is delicious in its simplicity. Tip: each chicken comes in a variety of preparations and with a choice of sauces (though the birds themselves are all roasted in the same manner, not actually in the sauces). Go for the simple versions, which I have found outdo the "fancier" options. Same goes for the sides. Started by a Boulud alum who really knows what she is doing when it comes to the hospitality side of things, you will not be left wanting for attentive yet efficient service. An excellent option for very well executed, if not exactly adventurous, classics in lively and pleasant surroundings. A quick note on my rating scale: 5 stars = exceptional food & service; 4 stars = excellent food & service; 3 stars = decent to good (top-of-the-line for fast service restaurants); 2 stars = mediocre; 1 star = not recommended. u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-6-v5QsH94hk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAFQ/zcxtoMQxA5o/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'a few weeks back I wanted to take out my GF to celebrate her birthday, so I booked this restaurant once I discovered it. It came highly recommended with its Michelin Stars. We went all out with their Tasting Menu. Problem was, she thought I was going to pop-the-question :-D The dishes were nothing but superb!! With an excellently paired wine. By the way, they wouldn't accept our tip; even though our waiter deserved it. He was nice enough to allow us to try three different wines, where the 3rd was perfect. Interested to try out their Private Dining Room which gives you a birds-eye view of the dining area. I just need to get my friends in on such a venture. This is one of my top 3 restaurant picks for special dinners. My girlfriend and I were very happy with all the dishes. Everything from the spacious dinner settings, presentation, and flavor-profiles, - makes this well worth the cost. I highly recommend you reserve a table here.', u'author_name': u'James Andersonn', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100434214033228938259', u'time': 1464164906}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-n7OQk-JOGBo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABOM/jBhvb69uPEU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Located in Manhattan, NY, this is a French-styled Michelin 3 star restaurant and it is all about creativity. A 3-hour lunch seemed to pass by really fast, that's how enjoyable it was. Very different style from Blue Hill, but the attention to details and the choosing of top ingredients were the same and the dishes were all so delicious and visually pleasing. The caviar, foie gras, lobster, duck, even the at-table-side-freshly-grinded carrots were just wonderful. Of course, seeing how they braised the asparagus inside a pig's bladder (very few places in the U.S. do that) was definitely an eye-opener (I thought it was a melon from far away). The restaurant is nicely decorated with high high ceiling and big windows which I loved.', u'author_name': u'Tammy Liu', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102127816559576392189', u'time': 1466511045}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-GmqUwCe1NYM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABn4/vMHf2tcuSCk/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Not having any expectations going to dine here I was pleasantly surprised. Had been trying to get a reservation for awhile and was finding it harder to get than Per Se! Hadn't realised at the time it had gotten higher ratings than Per Se. But going to both within the space of a week I felt the experience and food was more interesting and enjoyable at Eleven Madison. Quick tip, go hungry, the tasting course has a huge number of dishes. Even small plates add up after about the 15th one! But having said that the price was actually quite reasonable for this quantity, quality and inventiveness of the dishes. Again much more so than Per Se. As someone else mentioned Eleven Madison didn't feel the need to add supplemental charges on the tasting menu. Found the staff to be pretty easy going and not full of themselves, which is always nice at a high end restaurant. It was also interesting to have the kitchen tour as well, where we were served some shaved ice cones as we watched the staff go about their business. Amusingly, the goody bag given to you at the end of your visit contained some of the granola that we had in one of the dishes. It was pretty good for breakfast. 8) Do note that the tasting menu changes every quarter, so what we had has changed since we had the fall menu in 2015. And having only been once I don't know how many main stay dishes they keep through the seasons. So, a fun experience for high end dining. ', u'author_name': u'Denby Liu', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110366529853017658201', u'time': 1461981479}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-llyFKPaqux0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAHs/5THZQNpZuUI/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I feel obligated to give this establishment the prestigious Google 5-star award. Every aspect of this meal was perfect from the service to the ambiance and, of course, the food. Absolutely stunning. 10/10 would eat again. ', u'author_name': u'Seth McIntosh', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110146586266003379340', u'time': 1463373580}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-cVZU7xVC6PE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAadA/NpIYCgDsDM8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'A unique dining experience with impeccable service. The drinks are fabulous and the ambiance is perfect. u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-gCecp0V7GFI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAlR8/bve42PHXsoE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Salvation Taco, the restaurant within Pod 39, is one of the latest creations of the same owner as 'The Spotted Pig' in the West Village. Though fairly spacious by NYC standards, it's UBER trendy (there was a line to get in on a Tuesday evening at 6:30pm). Their menu is an upscale take on Mexican fare. The pork tamarind taco is spectacular. A huge hunk of pork on the bone with crisped skin will arrive on an iron skillet for you to rip apart and eat with warm soft taco shells. The spicy meatballs are sublime (although a few more wouldn't hurt). The also have speciality drinks and a small, but decent beer craft beer menu. The rooftop lounge is amazing and affords a gorgeous view of midtown, but it too is packed to the gills. You can get a great fresh margherita up there.', u'author_name': u'Sotirios Gountas', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116447827677640383696', u'time': 1466614687}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Wt5bKG-Op-o/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABLZ8/Bi1ydwO7l4k/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Though the food at Salvation Taco is good, don’t expect much beyond average and the bro scene can be quite a turn off. The experience at Salvation Taco is drastically different before 6:30 and after. The former is a nice relaxed almost local bar feeling with quick and responsive service. The later is a stressful affair in which you must compete with the large number of dudes flowing in for the staff’s attention. The cocktail menu is awesome, the beer menu less so but still decent. The tacos are pretty good, but I didn't find them outstanding. The lamb one on roti was excellent but for the price and size I didn't think it measured up. The al pastor tacos were also good, but fairly forgettable and considering the price and that they aren't quite enough for a meal, are problematic. Make sure to come right at opening to avoid the dude crowd. ', u'author_name': u'Tyler Lund', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112896824394656273445', u'time': 1466818638}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Really cool rooftop bar. Super trendy crowd up there. Beautiful views. $9 Negra Modelos served in a faux glass. The Al Pastor tacos were delicious yet a small portion of 3 tiny tacos. Line out the door and around the block at 515pm on a Thursday. Trendy atmosphere, expect swanky prices. ', u'author_name': u'Bob Smith', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108705777644968827906', u'time': 1465558368}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Interesting, eclectic food and drink. Everything was good - the guacamole was very fresh and simple - really just mashed perfect avocados and not overloaded with other ingredients. The cocktail was complex with a bit of heat. The taco (pork belly, pigs ears, ...) was also a nice, complex combination of flavors and textures that worked well together. The bar was loud and raucous, a millennial vortex. The menu linked to from Google Maps is not current or accurate. I had hoped to be able to sample several different tacos, but they now only come in full dinner-sized portions of 3 of the same taco. That's disappointing, as there were many interesting things I wanted to sample on the menu. And the menu is not as eclectic now as it was when the Google version was published. But it's still a nice find, if also a bit more expensive. Such is the price of success I guess.', u'author_name': u'Peter Wharton', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115010125680294336214', u'time': 1466041573}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The rooftop bar and atmospher are cool. The ping pong table is awesome! However, the food was probably the worst Mexican food I have ever eaten. Being from the south, I know what is good and that was not! The service is also terrible. I would recommend for a few drinks but not food.', u'author_name': u'Eva Allen', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102634243564461408203', u'time': 1466995362}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 865-5800', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'145', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'145'}, {u'long_name': u'East 39th Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'E 39th St'}, {u'long_name': u'Murray Hill', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Murray Hill'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10016', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10016'}]}

They do have a very good Bourbon menu and Rye selection. Their beer selection is weak but what they do offer will go.done okay. ', u'author_name': u'M Garcia', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116197501261495988080', u'time': 1465598182}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Came here for lunch with a friend. It's cool because (a) you have to go downstairs to get in (b) the whole thing is like being on the inside of a ship, (c) it has those old-school curved bench seats that wrap around a round table, and (d) they use retro-styled "reserved" metal tent signs on the table to let the riff raff know that the primo seats are not for you (except today, it was for me!). My friend had the cobb salad with shrimp. It looked AMAZING. I had the tuna burger. I ordered it medium rare but got it more like medium (but that could be we talked a bit before I bit into it). But it was just the tuna patty (I think it was chopped - a la "ground" tuna) with lettuce and tomato with a side of julienned zucchini (ugh?) but with a tangy dressing (yum!) - that's it. The service was very good, but again, I could be because my friend comes often. It is a bit pricey but hey, it's SOHO!', u'author_name': u'Danny Kim', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117184510049151399323', u'time': 1463111580}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-XnpsAU05hR8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABoak/p3crX9nrrbs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'These people don't care about their customers at all. The food quality has gone down significantly in the last year. I'm pretty sure it must be a union staff because I think if it was privately run they would have cared more. Much of the food was inedible if they even have it in stock', u'author_name': u'Marna Howard', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110052976154865355395', u'time': 1462930007}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I have to say the service was the worst I've ever experienced in a restaurant the waitress was very inattentive. The food was great. It was my girlfriend bday and I wanted to be the best for her. First of all there was a crack on my girlfriend glass drink while she was driving it thank god I notice it, but u have to say the Asian manger took care of it the proper way. The waitress didn't even come and check up on us when we were some with app, dinner, and She forgot about or bday dessert WOW. Think twice about coming here because if you have that waitress trust me it won't be a good experience.', u'author_name': u'JerezJoshua', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105487153120596201205', u'time': 1460293037}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 431-7676', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'142', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'142'}, {u'long_name': u'Mercer Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Mercer St'}, {u'long_name': u'Lower Manhattan', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lower Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10012', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10012'}]}

u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ZdzIi3pSlu4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGRg/7oRxPddRZUg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'As part of a burger crawl we tried out the Umami burger and the Truffle burger. Both burgers were tasty and cooked exactly as requested. We sat at the bar and also ordered drinks. Our server was quick to get our order in and helped ensure everyone had what they needed.', u'author_name': u'Erin Knight', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107552759642521144775', u'time': 1461539118}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-8MDPhnwj1sg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEo/z46O-SLsFHw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The signature Umami Burger definitely plays with flavor and texture: the ground beef is flavored with Asian seasonings (a mixture of soy, seaweed, miso, among many others), the tomato is roasted and slightly squishy, and the cheese is in the form of a parmesan wafer. It's not a premium burger, and should not be compared to one, but it's definitely got a niche in the upscale fast food market. The fries are a little too thin for my taste (just a personal preference), but the Umami ketchup is a nice change of pace. If you're looking for a burger with a twist, this is a good one to try.', u'author_name': u'Lynn S', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104818080376066887124', u'time': 1464982797}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-D4lgAUGP-8E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAMoY/DHPbMgZt9c4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Burgers burgers burgers!!! If Sepu really want to pack a punch go for the manly burger featuring bacon cheese and a couple of other extra treats. All combined that will make your mouth salivate even of you're dehydrated. Ask for some strong fries to go right next to it and you'll just be ready to have the best post meal nap of your life. The green tea goes very smoothly with it; just a tad sweet making it the perfect drink to go with your burger. ', u'author_name': u'Andres Uribe', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104198200608644623279', u'time': 1463967694}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-tKKt8YW8EUA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABk/Lq7jZWTxHM8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Love this restaurant! The burgers are delicious. They have interesting sauces. The drinks are great as well. The bar always has room and the service is great. The staff is very friendly and genuine. ', u'author_name': u'haya f', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/118431554166924383663', u'time': 1463107413}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WWeyHAfMa_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/cn3jjZFnhzA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Who ever loves burgers and haven't tried umami burger get yourself there now. ', u'author_name': u'Rafael Yau', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107744062940210293013', u'time': 1466416053}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-aTd6qQPE23w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAP4/aH1Pr0h03VU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Eleven Madison Park is not always in the budget. peak times. ', u'author_name': u'Kevin Cabral', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103612062459546747277', u'time': 1465534666}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-p8c-HRDS3-A/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGbo/8v5reGujvVI/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Classy to the max, if you're trying to impress someone, bring them here. Prices definitely match the upscale looks of the place, so just make sure you're ready to pay for the experience ', u'author_name': u'Matt Grierson', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106871581410077257303', u'time': 1466104864}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Amazing complex cocktails. Yes, everyone is trying to make great cocktails, but this place is actually doing it. Ingredients and mixology that you won't see elsewhere. Spicy, smoky? Hard to find these things well done. But, you can here. Take your time and enjoy all the flavors and every drop. ', u'author_name': u'Jason Sevilla', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101494342480460784152', u'time': 1465884599}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-nV0OZDw-wpw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAA3cM/Y7XS4JmPtWg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Just ok. This place has gone down hill a bit. A year ago I would have given it a 4. I'm a big fan of Daniel Humm and Eleven Madison is one of my favorite restaurants. The food at the Nomad Bar isn't bad however it is forgettable. The "special" Kostow menu was underwhelming as was the regular menu's tuna, burger, and flatbread. The only thing that was above par was the selection of cocktails. I would eat elsewhere especially compared to Humm's other establishments. Good service and ambiance but doesn't warrant the mediocre food. ', u'author_name': u'Bart Rosenthal', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107078943029702416824', u'time': 1460602540}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The chicken burger is delicious. It's rich but there is a complexity in flavors. The frisée cuts some of the richness. The crispy skin is a nice surprise when you take a bite. It is so crispy but still has so much flavor. The service is top notch. They are attentive but not over bearing. If you can get a seat upstairs, do it. You can look down on the bar. ', u'author_name': u'Eve Chou', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113502468435250629023', u'time': 1459471132}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(347) 472-5660', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'10', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'10'}, {u'long_name': u'West 28th Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'W 28th St'}, {u'long_name': u'Midtown', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Midtown'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10001', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10001'}]}

{u'lat': 40.73323654999999, u'lng': -73.99564965}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.73306195, u'lng': -73.99607304999999}}}, u'adr_address': u'24 5th Ave, New York, NY 10011, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-868-2424', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Ambiance Claudette has a very charming decor. I felt like I walked into a local restaurant located somewhere in the countryside of Paris. It is a nice dining ambiance especially if you want to get away from the daily New York City bustle. Food Our table ordered about 10 dishes but the three that really stood out were the steak, skate, and the grilled octopus. The octopus was served on a bed of chickpea puree and the steak was cooked exactly how we requested. The best dish we had was the skate. The waitress informed us that it is seasonal but if you see it on the menu, don't hesitate to order it! Desert was decent but limited and cocktails were strong.', u'author_name': u'myself hello', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102540293155019589839', u'time': 1465859842}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-eLXNlTe4two/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAF0/sOzx6iEm_7w/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Love Claudette, but can't go there. Love it because the food is excellent and creative, the service is superb, and the atmosphere is wonderful. I can't go there because it's filled with the white linen perfect skin monied Hamptons crowd that is really loud and entitled (similar to the crowd that dominates their wonderful sister restaurant, Rosemary's). But the crowd isn't their fault, so five stars for them.', u'author_name': u'Kurt Brown', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110966664627349178939', u'time': 1466786730}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I love the truffle hummus!! u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-S7-HJH4XEd8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAJBU/5aIr8YvVenk/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Been wanting to check this place out, since its very popular and when I read in the paper it supposedly had one of the best burgers in NYC, I went the very next day. It was very underwhelming. I got the burger, one of my friends got the Coq au Vin, and another got a third dish I can't remember. None of it was bad, mind you, but considering the hype, nothing was amazing. The ingredients were good quality, but, at least for my friends and myself, there was nothing to make us come back. ', u'author_name': u'Roman A.', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115005023497824000702', u'time': 1466156912}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-bJFnx6feNUc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAmI/87kynYa-Qzc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Certainly a bit more relaxed than the other Boulud outposts (more in line with DBGB); the location is great, the food pretty good if you stick to the charcuterie/cold plates, the service - maybe a little lacking. The atmosphere and layout are nice, though maybe the acoustics are a little off in some places - but overall, it's quite clean and pleasant. The wine/alcohol offerings are great, and as a wine bar exclusively, it's a great spot to start the night. The actual full food service and wait staff are a little lacking, based on the brand name and the price point. Service can be meandering, and the full menu is a but unfocused.', u'author_name': u'Adam Van Grover', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117884036826386052000', u'time': 1461800763}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-iqDNHjsEGnY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGxY/XIpjBGfltAQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The staff at Bar Boulud are so helpful. Very kind, welcoming and pleasant to interact with. I've worked two events here during NYFW and only have positive memories. Food was pretty good too :) ', u'author_name': u'wendy chan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103276883307631259483', u'time': 1458182475}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Very quiet Monday night, very good service, food was lacking spark. Escargot (fine), small charcuterie plate (good), duck (very good), pork shank special (OK, pork overcooked), chocolate mint mousse (good). ', u'author_name': u'Jack Bloom', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/118075250105818094301', u'time': 1455636109}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-mD1w1ELUZq4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAATE/0LjSBWO2eug/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Bar Boulud serves small portions of decent food at inflated prices. For a place that is supposedly known for its coq au vin, it was surprisingly mediocre and underseasoned. It's also rather annoying to have busboys circling the table like vultures looking to snatch your half-full plate away if you stop eating for a moment to talk to your date. There are better choices in the neighborhood. ', u'author_name': u'Alan Babbitt', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103144736677272590567', u'time': 1453383033}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 595-0303', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'1900', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'1900'}, {u'long_name': u'Broadway', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Broadway'}, {u'long_name': u'Lincoln Square', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lincoln Square'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10023', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10023'}]}

{u'lat': 40.68765610000001, u'lng': -74.00115639999999}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.68757809999999, u'lng': -74.0015356}}}, u'adr_address': u'117 Columbia St, Brooklyn, NY 11231, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 718-923-9322', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-PU_KlKCEErg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABf8/A4tJlMl5-A4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great unique Thai food to find in the US. The kai yang (grilled young chicken) was amazing, and the som tam refreshing and spicy. I was disappointed in the lack of wheelchair accessibility of their location. There are steps to get pretty much everywhere in the restaurant, but at least its just a few smaller ones. Their entrance vestibule is the hardest part. Otherwise, decent service and delicious food are easy to find here. They've got some competition with Katoi in Detroit, but the more places I can find Khao Soi and other northern thai dishes, the better!', u'author_name': u'Alan Hejl', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102235738201099337064', u'time': 1462906295}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-hL_QGreRwwQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGoc/Kk9cBhd1rIo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Pok Pok consistently delivers. This is my 4th visit over the years, and it remains pretty solid. In contrast, SriPraPhai in Queens is not quite as consistent (at least not in the past couple years), but I would say that when SriPraPhai is on, it's a notch above Pok Pok. You can't go wrong with most dishes. Some of the highlights in our most recent visit: the whole roasted chicken, mussel crepe (hoi thawt), the head-on prawns.', u'author_name': u'Johnny Tan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102728581437805238916', u'time': 1461441029}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'as advertised... not as good as pdx location. fish sauce wings (excellent), special salad with pork cracklings super spicy (ok), Hoi Thawt (very good), Kaeng Hang Leh (very good)', u'author_name': u'Jack Bloom', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/118075250105818094301', u'time': 1459867085}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-vScZafotukE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAARh8/vsY2wtZpZ5o/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Best Thai places in Brooklyn or the city. The food leans on the spicy side but its irresistible. It's a sharing based experience so get a lot of different dishes. Our server was knowledgable and helped us understand some of the more obscure things on the menu. Great experience and it wasn't nearly as expensive as it probably should be.', u'author_name': u'Rohan Kusre', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110137441707677932447', u'time': 1460751440}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-6Mz-KCyDk6k/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAxo/W0ikRQKvA28/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great good and great service. Chicken wings are not overhyped, they are the real deal.', u'author_name': u'Alyson Paige', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104528792296428338177', u'time': 1466210076}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 923-9322', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'117', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'117'}, {u'long_name': u'Columbia Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Columbia St'}, {u'long_name': u'Columbia Street Waterfront District', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Columbia Street Waterfront District'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11231', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11231'}]}

u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-4r9fEsEiihw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAKiU/cZhLVoG4qGg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'One of NYC's best BBQ spots with a variety of meats, so go with a group and get a taste of everything! Highly recommend the brisket, beef rib, and the Jamaican Jerk baby back ribs. The lamb belly was tasty but very oily, so you don't need to order too much of it. The whiskey sour pickles are a nice palate cleanse from all the heaviness of the meats. The smoked beans were also great, with good chunks of burnt ends. The lines can be long on the weekends, but it'll give you an opportunity to form a strategic plan with friends while you wait. Solid selection of whiskeys, beers, and cocktails at the 2 bars. ', u'author_name': u'Lawrence Yu', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100341112941572762806', u'time': 1463795617}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-NRGIvYEapl0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABg/zBGv6wtk8_k/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The brisket and beef rib get MVP of the meal- Sides like mac n cheese and chili are a zesty and delicious addition to any spread. The chicken, honestly, might have been the only thing that left me unimpressed- But it'd be insane to expect everything to be the same high caliber of the aforementioned options. Lots of seating but it gets busy fast on weekends. Left the place and smelled nice and smoky all day. HIGHLY recommend.', u'author_name': u'Noelle Quanci', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100735284257208043059', u'time': 1461093293}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-BZutUPqkScQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAASe8/8cbXWgMLyOQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Bring a friend. Get the beef rib. Only one. Feel like Fred Flintstone. Add a banana pudding for your sweet tooth. The rest of the BBQ is amazing, but the beef rib will change your life.', u'author_name': u'Zach Jump', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109205162695486006219', u'time': 1467054507}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-lRH_BPEHels/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFZg/Onc0PFWu4EY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Everything was great. The Brisket, to die for. Now, I usually love home made potato salad, but Hometown potato salad was very tasty. Great atmosphere, line was pretty long, but who cares. So get your butt to Hometown, and enjoy some good BBQ.', u'author_name': u'Abraham Holguin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101482458878125642836', u'time': 1462684351}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-T_wu3-p7MvM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAVI0/zcL1WqeK2cQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Loved the BBQ here. Took me back to my time in Austin. Nostalgic. We tried the Brisket, Smoked Turkey, and Chicken. Great success and the banana cream pudding is satisfying as well. ', u'author_name': u'Diniece Peters', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101462541873321175761', u'time': 1466354100}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(347) 294-4644', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'454', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'454'}, {u'long_name': u'Van Brunt Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Van Brunt St'}, {u'long_name': u'Red Hook', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Red Hook'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11231', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11231'}]}

40.76519325, u'lng': -73.98701505000001}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.76498785, u'lng': -73.98721765}}}, u'adr_address': u'362 W 53rd St, New York, NY 10019, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-757-0108', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-TRwo2HUnJGs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAACIEw/MmJHx0WzB34/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'As a Japanese and as a person who enjoy yakitori very often and at various places the quality of food at this place was disappointing. To begin with it was way too salty. When I ordered Takenoko, bamboo root, they already added much salt on it when they grilled it but they also placed salt on the dish. There was no way I could enjoy the subtle flavor of the original material by that. They also over grilled the meat. Some yakitori had blackened source covering the meat and I even felt it would not be good for health. And most importantly meat itself did not have much flavor. I do not know where they are getting the chicken but I do believe this is nothing more than what we can get at any shop like Whole-foods. However there are several good things. One was the people working there. They were nice and friendly. The other was the decoration in the restaurant. It was very beautifully made and has genuine high quality. Very well done for that part.', u'author_name': u'Takuya Shimomura', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111260286181082129564', u'time': 1460128403}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-38KwoYtfOlo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAKxI/DEzl2P1uH6I/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Had a great dinner here. We had the $75ish omakase and was able to tailor the items that were selected for it to avoid anything we didn't like. Some in my party didn't want any cartilage, so our orders did not include any. Also had a special duck and chicken meatball (tsukune), but have to say that my favorite had to be either the chicken wing or chicken shoulder. Finished the dinner with the roe ochazuke and thought it was a good amount of food. The other two diners were too full to for the last dish but I think it was just the right amount and wasn't sure if I could finish the last dish too. Wine by the glass selection was not big, but then again this is a Japanese restaurant. Good selection of sake.', u'author_name': u'Winston S.', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105495849982301482307', u'time': 1458081241}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-4RrB_qUeQ0s/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAEI4/gWtgNGXueQg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I have been to Japan 16 times. I have rarely felt that flavors in the West. Tori Shin is an exception. Very impressive. High prices, but the restaurant has a Michelin star. Second, are not so high for New York, around the city there are restaurants that pretend to be Japanese and cost little less by offering a much lower quality of food.', u'author_name': u'Jaime D'alessandro', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107150395546925861622', u'time': 1451321394}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-tQCc6uWm1Jw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABYto/ROiIpkddCZc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'From the moment you enter to the moment you leave Tori Shin is all about customer service, the experience and the meal. It is all about the chicken here. The posh interior greets you has you enter the door. The intimate setting is great for a group of four or two. Our table did the Omakase and just let the chef do the picking for us tonight. Everything comes out is well presented. Well, seasoned and delicious. Even though each item looks dainty but it packs a punch. Eating slowly, enjoying, savoring. You think it isn’t filling but it is. If you want less go for the 10 skewer set but you might end up ordering more. Tori Shin is for that fancy night out cause it doesn't come cheap.', u'author_name': u'D Nguyễn', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115933623080364545130', u'time': 1444420690}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ipLa9dAIvuc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABto/JRoJPu4Qmzw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'never had such a wide selection of delicious chicken parts, very sleek and zen ambiance as well', u'author_name': u'Dave Fan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100554918267181642353', u'time': 1466172067}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 757-0108', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'362', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'362'}, {u'long_name': u'West 53rd Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'W 53rd St'}, {u'long_name': u'Hell's Kitchen', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Hell's Kitchen'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10019', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10019'}]}

u'ChIJYRiXqgpZwokRTD7-XXgHSqo', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-505-8500', u'vicinity': u'327 2nd Avenue, New York', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-yFEqVDLg-3g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAVAY/p23dtIFuVck/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The food is outstanding: super-fresh ingredients with attention to unique presentations (but, thankfully, nothing too pretentious or cutesy ). Check the specials out - they change regularly and feature the best of what's in season. They really think out of the box with the wine selection, including wines from Hungary and Georgia (the country, of course) - and they're good! All wines are available by the glass. Beer selection is small but excellent (one night, all but one beer was from NY State). The cocktails use fresh, housemade ingredients and change seasonally. Lastly, as if my love for Midwinter weren't already clear, the entire staff is top-notch: attentive, friendly, and down-to-earth. Thank the gods this restaurant has come to our neighborhood!', u'author_name': u'Laura Lutz', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111069218170024415535', u'time': 1462713699}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-2REtwWIVU3Q/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABIY/OwlW4t7X8ao/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I have literally had everything on the menu and it is all amazeballs. This is the best food for 10 blocks in any direction. One of the only places next to Gramercy tavern with great food, beer, wine, and cocktails.', u'author_name': u'Adam Lutz', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106623377083458748226', u'time': 1462713547}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-8Zy1cc2uHCk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAnU/uudCVtO6Xt0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Truly fresh, just-picked-from-the-farm food. Might sound cliché, but definitely get the Farm Salad! 🙌', u'author_name': u'Miachel Breton', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110971522227347573149', u'time': 1466300416}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Definitely a new favorite restaurant! I can't wait to see what summer brings to Midwinter Kitchen. The cocktails are phenomenal and you can really tell how fresh all of the ingredients are in every dish.', u'author_name': u'Katherine McNamara', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111292442904049139827', u'time': 1457965535}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Unt51j741yM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABaA/3eXsVkSt9v4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'My husband and i met friends for dinner there last night. Food was fabulous! Service was impeccable, and the atmosphere in this great, down-to-earth restaurant is exactly what we hoped for in a night out with friends. They had two specials last night, steak&frits and a kale salad, both were wonderful, so based on our experience, i would advise to always check what their specials are. I had the branzino with lentils chimichurri and arugula salad - it was a master piece! u'international_phone_number': u'+1 646-201-5529', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WWeyHAfMa_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/cn3jjZFnhzA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Finally came here to see what all the hype is about. I waited 30 minutes to be seated. The food was amazing, the momosan Ramen was heaven broth had great flavor and was well balanced. I was tried the pig ears and pork buns that was good too. I suggest getting the Ramen, it puts momofuku Ramen to shame. Get the pork buns too. ', u'author_name': u'Rafael Yau', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107744062940210293013', u'time': 1465004376}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-tC-mRVkSiH8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAVQ/qBZUm8t5XBw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Came here for lunch on a Friday at 12:30pm and there was a 30 minute wait. Since this place is fairly new, the service wasn't great. Our waitress kept on getting confused about our orders. I had the kakuni bao, which was nothing special. However, the 4 star goes to the noodles! The noodles were chewy, thick and just perfect. The ramen broth was just okay. I didn't feel that it was that flavorful.', u'author_name': u'Ashley Yang', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101684445834851722416', u'time': 1464010357}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-LQh3AYwshu4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEY/0ym3dXXshSk/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Tonkatsu, tsukemen, and beers. They were out of Asahi, broke a glass, and the noise level was high - allbailments of a new and popular place. That being said, we enjoyed the food and the price point. Waited in the line out the door 20 min before opening and were seated around 5:05. The egg was my favorite part. We weren't a fan of the pork on the tsukemen or on the tonkotsu as much as the type in the tsukemen dipping sauce.', u'author_name': u'Melanie Wahl', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108810178035667041258', u'time': 1464400351}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Good for lunch. Been twice... Did not wait either time. Lunch set is good. Tuna poke bowl and tonkotsu ramen were a good combo.', u'author_name': u'Dang Truong', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108380978560051323167', u'time': 1465005726}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-sTkUItpJD4g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAVII/VaGOVUBJhmg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Tonkotsu Ramen was very very rich but I loved it. The tantan was also good but by no means traditional in any sense, and again, rich. We had a ton of sake as well plus some apps, divine. ', u'author_name': u'Samantha Abramson', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103153252553956235577', u'time': 1461403671}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The service is atrocious.This place is all about arrogant, brainless and condescending wannabes, who have not understood that their only job is to keep customers happy and accommodate them. Their prices are crazy for what they offer. You ask for sparkling water and they charge you $6 per person - $18 for one bottle of sparkling water. I can see $10,$12 even $15 for an omelette, but almost $20 is insane. More so with just two toppings. Scallops cost $9 each! Tables crowded together with music blasting so it's impossible to have a conversation and just a steady flow of clueless tourists hanging around walking in and out thinking it is part of the Whitney Museum or something. Skip this place since there are better choices in the neighborhood. A tourist trap. Two blocks away there are fabulous restaurants in West Village - The Whitney, The Standard, Bar Balonat, High Street on Hudson, Barbuto, Spotted Pig... all very near and much better.', u'author_name': u'LKLA LKLA', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104836942148321124797', u'time': 1463496431}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-3p0ezsEKUpE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAGg/mLeTN0I-M_8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Good vibe, friendly staff, ample street parking depending on when you arrive. food is mainly South Indian. I like their dosas. 3) Also try the Indian beverages like the mango lassi, Madras coffee, lychee juice, etc.', u'author_name': u'Jason Jian', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107085774896988240166', u'time': 1465110642}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-MbII4AES8YE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAiKE/G3JTyCIVbC8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'If you are looking for a nice looking place, this is not it. If you are looking for good food, this is it. It gets pretty crowded and finding a table might require some hunting, but the rotation is relatively fast. Minimum purchase with credit card is $15, with the low prices, one person's meal might not be enough to reach that minimum. ', u'author_name': u'C. I. Shinzato', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115887881811527199201', u'time': 1457058731}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-0M7oj_SmzQI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAo/yUw9zQMdJ84/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Amazing to the core!! I love this place and had such a fabulous experience! The service is above and beyond and the tea is exquisite!! The little sandwiches, caviar, champagne, desserts and all accompaniments make my bucket list dream of having a proper tea experience better than I could have imagined! The interior is so awesome I cannot take it!! Oh and they also have vodka flights and full meals too!! Different rooms for events and a little gift shop too!! I will definitely come back!!!', u'author_name': u'ru yi li', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103772686386980536225', u'time': 1464117004}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is one of the great food values in NYC, hence the five stars. We discovered this place when we went to visit the Temple gift shop for a statuette after eating at Dosa Hutt. The canteen is located in the basement of the Temple and has all the ambiance of your high school gymnasium. The crowd seem to be mostly local, with the odd lot of hipsters. You order cafeteria style, and the process is somewhat confusing. There's a video menu, but there are specials posted on handbills, so if it's not too crowded, give all of the menus a good perusing before making your choice. You pay, get your number, find a table and approach for your grub when the number's called. It's well organized, for the most part. We went with a ghee roast, the Hyderabadi dosa, and a vegetable uttapam. Also tried a masala chai, and halwa. The dosa was filled with a spicy green chutney. Masala was a $1 add on, sambar and coconut chutney were included. The dosa was crisp and delicious, the sambar was thicker and tastier than Dosa Hutt's, and the green coconut chutney had more zest. I had ordered a ghee roast on the basis of favorable Yelp reviews, not knowing exactly what it was. Here it is a buttery dosa, folded into a pyramid, with the same masala, sambar and the chutney on the side. For some reason the uttapam was delayed, but it arrived large, fluffy, tasty and greasy, more ample than the ones I have had in the City. The halwa was so rich and sweet we could not quite finish. The tea was on the mild side, with a bit of milk. All this provender for $23.00. You won't need much dinner if you lunch here.', u'author_name': u'us Amy', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112000974606249722767', u'time': 1462235215}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-m9mTT7PgTjQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABnA/PhIrO1dINSs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'What a wonderful place! 100% vegetarian and fresh. The samosas were cold, which was not ideal, but the onion dosa, paper dosa, and the desserts are all addicting and the portions are huge for the price ($5-8 a dish). Huge space, and generally a line, but the food comes out within a minute or two. Highly recommended. u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-cycqpA0vOT4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAI0U/Id6sNlS3htY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'After having some amazing food at Mission Chinese in San Fran, I was expecting more of the same but with some more Mexican thrown in the mix. What you get here is bland in comparison , the burnt orange margarita was good, fish tacos where boring, the Kung pao cauliflower was just ok ', u'author_name': u'Adam Crick', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106490482306121680463', u'time': 1464366724}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-97GfWODFdmg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAWbI/2H0PtzZ1FFk/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Mission Cantina is exemplary of many of the businesses and establishments that dot the Lower East Side, in that it has a palpable cool factor. In its case, it is the super trendy and whimsical decor and ambiance, a colorful and nearly glowing assortment of furnishings where New York's vintage Chinese restaurant meets the local taqueria. The menu, is minimal in its presentation as well as its selection, to my appreciation. The items on the list are classic and modest popular Tex Mex and Chinese American dishes, except they are prepared and executed deliciously. The vegetarian burrito was simple, large in serving and portion and just very savory. Though pricey at first glance, the large portions (it is impossible to finish an order of Chicken-fried rice alone for instance) justify the cost. Our waitress was also very pleasing and attentive. ', u'author_name': u'Brennan Ortiz', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104203390292958075208', u'time': 1459687333}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Will never go back. Premixed sugar water margaritas. Fish tacos - don't even think about getting these, came out cold and nearly crusted with salty paprika. The waitress was nice and took this off the bill. Mongolian beef - better yet known as a plate of sautéed onions, uncooked red pepper, and a few pieces of tough meat that you can barely cut through. Seriously, what is enjoyable about this place?', u'author_name': u'Danielle Deckler', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100847742996020320965', u'time': 1456578746}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Y86YeQGo53k/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAANos/d5IC5Z0xuYQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'food is delicious. Last time the portions were a little small. I think in order to keep the prices same, they are shrinking the portions :(', u'author_name': u'Kivanc Kose', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102206256589117673011', u'time': 1465246660}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Yc2HOE3vopY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABQ0/pLuJ9CJMXIg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The Chinese food burrito was a weird mixture of tastes. The waitress warned me it wasn't for everyone and that turned out to be very true. The all-meat burrito was also really strange tasting mostly because of the inclusion of lechon. Every bite was just overwhelmingly pig skin. But service was great as were the free chips. u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-fDT9z_r_og4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAANRY/sbTk0XBQQEc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Quality Korean BBQ with a fun huddled vibe. The beef combo is incredible, but the pork belly is way too fatty. I'd recommend the prawns (they're huge) and the beef stew. I also really love the egg that cooks on the side of the plate. I wish they came with rice for the meals. Scallion seafood pancake was so-so. Not thin enough and slightly burnt. All in all, it came to around $70 per person for a table of 4, which is a bit much, but we did drink a lot of sake and soju. I'd definitely go again and bring more friends. ', u'author_name': u'Clemens Wan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109331593848788039624', u'time': 1462878259}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-yvt0RwAJ4ag/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAADEA/2eFulXBxJIo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Pleasant surprise for 32nd street. Bit noisy and there's often a line. Worth the wait if you're not into venturing out to Queens.', u'author_name': u'Peter Kelly', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113016014358417181245', u'time': 1466398008}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-J2mvFBH8Bv8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABAI/Q154NWRytkU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Bi Bim Bop it’s a traditional dish served on a hot stone plate the main ingredients are rice assorted vegetables, meat and a semi cooked egg if wanted. ', u'author_name': u'Harry Galyon', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113978876382595038909', u'time': 1455036525}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-p2wBkKic51A/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAA0Q/koZ5ReJT_Fk/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'very upscale, very expensive...quite the experience though', u'author_name': u'Steve Heflin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109111797023286393539', u'time': 1463072236}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-XvydnhWb9Nk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAH0/1t9auq41pak/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Update on 07/07/2015: Lunch was not as impressive as dinner for sure. We were there with another table, and the chef was too busy spoiling them. It felt like a really huge snub since we had already ordered a ton in drinks alone. The summer offerings were not as good as the spring menu. The chicken appetizer had a strange sauce and an unappetizing plating. The duck had a nice sear but the skin was soggy and the vegetables were extremely bitter. The chocolate nest dessert was the best part of the meal, but it just wasn't enough. --- 05/07/2015: Everything was perfect. The restaurant was very elegant and quiet, situated inside Hotel Chandler, which has a spectacular restroom. I was extremely excited about the warm olive breads, a rarity even in fine dining these days. Sometimes, it's the little things in life. The menu is certainly unique. For the four course route, pick one appetizer from the first two sections, one dessert from the last section, and any two courses. There were 8 amuse bouches, bite-sized treats, before the appetizer. I ordered prawns as the appetizer, halibut and veal tenderloin for the main courses, and toffee-coffee for the dessert. My mom ordered the frog as the appetizer, and cod and rabbit for her main courses, and mango-jalapeno for dessert. The prawns came with fiddlehead ferns, which I haven't had in a while, and the combination was amazing. The veal tenderloin was a bit salty, but the halibut was perfect. My mom's dishes were also very flavorful. She is usually very picky but she enjoyed the experience very much. I would be proud to take her here again. The waiters were consistently attentive and incredibly friendly. We ordered wines and liquors, and both were much better than expected and also reasonably priced. Overall, it was a phenomenal experience and because Juni is still has a personal touch, I dare to say it's even better than Jean Georges.', u'author_name': u'Iris Yung', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101325675294068392357', u'time': 1436578120}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ha1-X-ONKQ8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAATXc/tcH30xyZ_o8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Excellent food and service. Perfect setting to celebrate my wife's special birthday. Will definitely return in the future. ', u'author_name': u'Andres Uribe', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104198200608644623279', u'time': 1464346596}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-9VCYnMP9np8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAo8/FdluF4uxJVQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Excellent food. Bar food was decent, Drink and Cocktail list are extensive but expensive. I will definitely be back for a Whiskey class or 2.', u'author_name': u'Jeffrey Lahens', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104736942072258963567', u'time': 1464105769}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-W28uX5DfB2I/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAvR4/pxYbVDp0WR4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I came here for brunch and was pleasantly surprised by how good the food was here. The place was quite large for NYC standards. We ordered the brunch items but the one item that was really good was the fried grits. In the appetizer version, the grits are individual cubes topped with ham. In the entree version, the grits are one large block topped with gravy, fried brussels sprouts, and chunks of ham. I like the entree version better since the gravy makes it less dry. The service was good as well, attentive and courteous.', u'author_name': u'Julie Xiao', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114918897175635007309', u'time': 1452107675}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-9Wm66gh_3Z0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABCE/lNx4yMcn-lE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Citrus glazed donut, crispy grits with ham and Brussels sprouts were great. u'text': u'So happy after I left this spot. It was so great! Came here on a Friday night with my girl, she had been here a few weeks before me and brought me after tasting some of the amazing food they have here. The place was really cool everyone there really made you feel at home and like a regular. We started with some beers and appetizers and for the main dish I had to get the Benson Burger. It was so freakin good. My gosh I can't even describe how good it was. If you're ever in NY I definitely would make a stop here.', u'author_name': u'joey santana', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110502872443880194605', u'time': 1464889919}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-pWiNggMKXQc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABE/Wzi_EnojeV8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'It was OK but to me it didn't live up to the hype of an almost perfect score on google. The place is tiny so you are cramped especially if the bar is crowded, the front door opens directly into the cold street, and the was barely anyplace to hang our coats so we wound up sitting on them. My medium rare burger was undercooked. My sister breakfast sandwich seemed to be a better choice. At $4 for a cup of nothing special coffee and the server never asked if we wanted a refill, added to my disappointment. My sense is that it is the bar scene and not the food that is the attraction here. Even at 1PM on a Saturday the bar was very crowded.', u'author_name': u'Travis Thompson', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115920843096244713805', u'time': 1461212675}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Uu4jsgkImcE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABC8/E5caprxV9-k/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great beer and mouthwatering burgers - the real deal, towers of organic meat and fresh veg cooked to perfection and served on artisan bread. This is place is great for brunch, lunch, dinner and drinks. It's relaxed in the lunchtime/afternoon and gets bustling after dinner. The owners are often there behind the bar too which is cool.', u'author_name': u'Rowan Day', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111504804483361724996', u'time': 1456056952}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Friendly staff. A quick note on my rating scale: 5 stars = exceptional food & service; 4 stars = excellent food & service; 3 stars = decent to good (top-of-the-line for fast service restaurants); 2 stars = mediocre; 1 star = not recommended. Y.', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114315063586251012230', u'time': 1463533168}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The food was fine, nothing remarkable. Which is not a good recommendation for a place like this. The shrimp was pretty good, the tenderloin was too salty, the guacamole was utterly average. Also, beyond food: we had a table at eight that they said they needed by nine thirty. That seemed manageable. But they held up one dish for a weirdly long time, half an hour after everything else was served and eaten. So it was getting late by the time they brought out the dessert menus. At which point they had a change of heart, said it was exactly nine thirty, and actually took the dessert menus out of our hands and replaced them with the check. This is not how a reputable restaurant operates.', u'author_name': u'Seth Kleinerman', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112601116502080011510', u'time': 1450629765}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-TKfWetftO-8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAEm4/Efjp1E3PNy0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Amazing!
