I have been here several times since I moved in across the street. The menu is very different than anything else in the neighborhood, which is a relief because I was getting a little tired of Italian food and diners. The space is beautifully designed and pays homage to the former glass factory that once occupied the space. Definitely work a try.', u'author_name': u'Steven Matt', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115329619801756648943', u'time': 1461625924}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/--Is6EIix6PM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABc4/aC5IqErWefo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The very best meal we've ever had. Every bite was delicious and interesting. All parts of the experience from the ambiance to the plating to the food itself was beautifully conceived and absolutely perfect.', u'author_name': u'Jessica Schumacher', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106769559153591295950', u'time': 1463880567}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-aLL-fWMqCm4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABA/o0GNIC1wtS8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'We were shopping and walked by this restaurant, thought the review was excellent and decided to try it out. We tried the fixed course meal for two. The food was excellent but dessert was just so so. The service we received was excellent. recommended this place for dinner.', u'author_name': u'Joseph Lusk', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117369988528822405012', u'time': 1448518027}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'An ode to the too-short reign of Sara Karmer and her time as cook at this sewage-treatment adjacent gem. For anyone with a car or the patience to walk all the way up here, you're rewarded by comforting fare with heavy Arab accents. My parents and I came for brunch on a recent visit - they were visiting from upstate and brought their car - and left converts. The waitstaff did a good job of salvaging a borderline disastrous kitchen experience. It took more than an hour for our entrees to arrive, but their errors meant we got to sample even more of the menu that we ordered. One freebie, a cardamom sugar bun, balanced the sweetness with spice in a way that reminded me of why I like kheer so much. Any of the baked goods, including the house bread, cheese pastries or flaky bread, would make good smaller breakfasts on weekdays - if this were available close to a subway station. The entrees didn't disappoint either. The lamb and apple sandwich is heartier than you'd expect in such a dainty space, and was hard to finish after the appetizer. The yogurt, mint and apple are here in supporting roles, never overpowering the flavor of the bread and the meat. A spin on a shashuka, here called poached eggs and a spicy tomato stew, is rich and flavorful, another winner. I hope that the new chef retains the now famous rabbit three ways, which unfortunately isn't available at brunch. Perhaps they can rectify that, so we try that on a future visit, no matter the hour.', u'author_name': u'Chris Lee', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109677802200991176757', u'time': 1454295079}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-6EenwNIaN_0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAACMr8/JZrvRA7KGtc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Upside: great tasty interesting food. Downside: high prices.', u'author_name': u'Venera Varbanova', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110476424879621127699', u'time': 1464825065}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 389-0640', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'95', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'95'}, {u'long_name': u'Commercial Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Commercial St'}, {u'long_name': u'Greenpoint', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Greenpoint'}, {u'long_name': u'Brooklyn', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Brooklyn'}, {u'long_name': u'Kings County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Kings County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11222', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11222'}]}

u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-EtpIyKVUteI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAA4c/riPrz4_6j-s/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'First brunch in the city (albeit eaten at 3pm), and, I can honestly say it was among one of my favorite meals in the city. With all (?) Sunday brunch entrees coming with a complimentary beverage, we ordered the: * Short Rib Benedict - While my friend really liked these, I found that they were just okay, lacking a bit in flavor complexity: something like a bright citrus highlight would have paired really well here. * Vanilla Bean French Toast - Now, this, was probably the best french toast I've ever encountered. With thick cut toast that's only pan fried and browned on the sides, leaving the insides moist and gooey * Side of Bacon - Not particularly fancy bacon, but fried to just the right level of crispness, and great when eaten with the french toast. And the two drinks we got (apple champagne cocktail and white peach bellini) were both tasty as well. ***Accessibility Info*** Venue - Jane itself is up a single step, but they have a folding metal ramp that they keep inside for such purposes, so just have a friend ask (or call in, barring that)! As for the interior, while the tabling arrangements are fairly close, there are plenty of tables where the seats aren't situated back to back, making seating accessibility not terrible. Bathroom - Located down on the lower level, so they weren't accessible at all.', u'author_name': u'Johnny Wang', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103379264202553362035', u'time': 1465160748}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'There are so many options from dairy & dairy free ice cream flavors to gluten-free/dairy-free cones. It have options to serve all type of people. Even those that are lactose intolerant can come here to enjoy ice cream with a cone. As a result, I had a hard time choosing what to get. However, the employees were great! They allowed me to try different samples and even recommended a few options, which definitely helped me in my decision making. I ended up getting cappuccino ice cream with the birthday cake cone. This was my first time trying the birthday cake cone and I throughly enjoyed it. The cone itself has a sweet flavor to it, which left my satisfied with what I bought.', u'author_name': u'mt mt', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102589716808009764384', u'time': 1465785543}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-whUOgWNuYXM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAYw/Ecp4urzeVew/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'On a beautiful Saturday afternoon, I made my way to the city for brunch. Looking at my list of must try's, Jane Restaurant popped up. So off we go. It was 3:30ish so heavy brunch crowd had already left which made the meal all that more pleasant. We were greeted right away and were seated at a quiet corner table with a waiter quickly rushing over with menus and water. As I'm browsing the menu, I looked around the restaurant. Super trendy and modern decor, very pleasant to the eyes. We ordered some mimosas and coffee to start with and they readily refilled our coffees on demand. My friend ordered the Jane Burger and I the Nicoise salad. She said the burger was wonderful -- well she licked the plate dry. My nicoise salad was good but I felt the tuna, although seared perfectly, was a little dry. The rest of the salad was tasty. I've definitely had better nicoise salads. We then ordered a tiramisu and a fig panna cotta. The tiramisu was wow! Phenomenal. Soaked strongly in espresso, the taste definitely hit you where it counts, but in a good way. The panna cotta was a different. Interesting taste and pudding like texture, I don't think I'd order it again. Overall, we definitely had a rather pleasant experience and I'd love to come back and try the dinner service.', u'author_name': u'Rebecca Appel', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106782353247582225465', u'time': 1462679237}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Definitely a spot to check out. Went here for a few drinks on a date. Great prices and a great atmosphere. My only complaint is that the bartending staff were not as knowledgable as I would like them to be. I definitely recommend their huevos rancheros also! Best brunch I've had in Williamsburg!', u'author_name': u'Lynn Lan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112325306401090496442', u'time': 1461789361}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-eIjL9D6frUA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACx8/EJZkJdZgDsc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'It's famous, a sister restaurant of the Smith, and at a good location around SoHo. We went to dinner, which it was pretty good, nothing amazing or memorable. This place is first and foremost a brunch spot, so I hope to go back for brunch. One tip: make sure to make a reservation or you will be waiting.', u'author_name': u'Robert Lurie', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113223639195356999845', u'time': 1460040803}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 254-7000', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'100', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'100'}, {u'long_name': u'West Houston Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'W Houston St'}, {u'long_name': u'Lower Manhattan', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lower Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10012', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10012'}]}

40.7280006, u'lng': -74.0000404}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.72790060000001, u'lng': -74.00027879999999}}}, u'adr_address': u'181 Thompson St, New York, NY 10012, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-254-3000', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'To whom it may concern(and I hope you read this): Last evening after numerous failed attempts to secure a reservation at Carbone, we were able to secure a table at 5:30 PM. By the way, No thanks to your reservation system which advised us that nothing was available at that hour. What happened to make this reservation possible is that we found ourselves in Lower Manhattan yesterday at 4 PM (on our way from Philadelphia Pa to a wake in Queens). On a lark, we drove by the restaurant and decided to see if in fact something might be available at 5:30 PM. We have desperately wanted to dine with you for some time and since we have planned a New York City visit with friends in October thought that after what we have heard about "CARBONE" it would be a perfect place to dine for all 8 of us. One of your employees advised us that in fact there would be room for us and we were thrilled. We were most graciously greeted, seated and made welcome by your accommodating staff. Your Sommelier, Tehria(sp), discussed the wine offerings and we settled upon a very nice Valpolicella Ripasso by the glass(would have had more if we weren't driving). Your Waiter "A" was very attentive and made a number of suggestions to us. While we weren't necessarily looking to order as much food as we did, we wanted to get the most from this experience so we followed his suggestions to the letter. What happened after that was almost surreal. With the exception of the Bread(Grand Daisy I suspect), Wine(delicious), Cheese, and Olive Oil (Puglia Region I believe we were told), (and none of which your kitchen had anything to with), the evening slowly fell apart. The House Salad was rendered almost inedible by the amount of oil that had been included as part of the dressing. Next up the Penne Pasta with Vodka was inundated with Salt. Same for the Meatballs. The Veal Parmigiana was nothing more than a butterflied Veal Chop pounded and breaded and hardly what I was expecting for $65 dollars. When I order this dish I don't expect to be consuming fat that is still in evidence on a veal chop! Ah, I save the best for last, when my wife asked "A" which of the fish dishes(MP) might be best. He asked when was the last time she had Dover Sole and we told him about a month ago. He said to have it. So she ordered it. Suffice it to say it was in keeping with everything else, overly salted and hardly edible. We took what we didn't finish home with us although God only knows what we will do with it. By the way $95 dollars is an insult given the quality of what we were expecting and essentially what we were hoping you to deliver. Shame on me (after the fact given the quality) for not asking what the market price was for any of the items not on the menu. We thought we were going to need dialysis. Finally, lest you think my wife and I are "Rubes" from out of town, I was born and raised in NYC and we have family living in Manhattan and Larchmont New York and as such we are regulars to the New York City area. But, maybe I am a "Rube" for having paid $363 dollars(tip included) for this DISAPPOINTING (UNDERSTATEMENT) meal. It is almost as if someone consciously set out to ruin ingredients that should almost cook themselves. Oh and here's something else for you to consider, stop hiding behind email as the only method of communicating. Never Again for the Slattery Family.', u'author_name': u'Gerald Slattery', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100735018530447691751', u'time': 1467151640}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-fr8GmCMKsHs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAk/B7C42eaUMHo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'5 stars for the acting! Are you kidding? The 3 Stooges are hilarious. Up-sell at the table.. Charming and flirty they will make you think you are in some sort of SoHoFaBuLo restaurant that you get to tell your southern girlfriends about. Dont fall for any of the hype, go in and show what real charm looks like, then cross the street to Lupa and order the brisket. YUM!', u'author_name': u'Barbara Joubert', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114599451450364723790', u'time': 1466651379}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-GGWusOHiTe0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAADQ/yU4Q-qJAdjY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Oh my deliciousness is all I can say! Best Italian food I've had thus far. Ambiance, the wine selection, food super fresh and Sal was a great host. Definitely a must.', u'author_name': u'Susan Nunez', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114742178912611875701', u'time': 1466707253}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Food was good, the music was loud. I was very disappointed with the wine "bait and switch"... they advertised a certain style/vintage and we were served something different. Once we explained the issue to the wine steward and to the owner afterwards; there was no followup. Basically, we were over charged several hundred dollars at our meal with ZERO consideration, follow up or resolution from the owner. They stole from us. They are (obviously) doing great now, but if they keep taking advantage of the clientele, they will fade in time.', u'author_name': u'Larry Segebarth', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102992098087635059818', u'time': 1462556968}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Since it's lunch time, i wish for a fast food that is good and healthy. When I was in New York, i went inside this place and my dreams came true. The food was fresh, looked good and tasted great. The prices good too. I will be the first one in Line when they open one up in San Francisco. SF can use one of these for lunch crowds or shopping on the go.. I really wish one would open up now. If your in NY , please try this, I took two sandwiches to go and ate them on the plane... Good.', u'author_name': u'Lynn Lan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112325306401090496442', u'time': 1461789426}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 254-3000', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'181', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'181'}, {u'long_name': u'Thompson Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Thompson St'}, {u'long_name': u'Lower Manhattan', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lower Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10012', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10012'}]}

u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-JdGttP-Hbns/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAKg/bRSrDil1_JQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Very authentic feel to the restaurant. There are a lot of photos and signatures of celebrities who have eaten here. They don't take reservations so try to get there early for dinner time. I was there on a Monday evening at around pm and it was almost empty. Food is good, but not as great as it's hyped to be in my opinion. The tagliatelle bolognese is heralded to be amazing here, but after eating it, I was disappointed. It wasn't bad, just not the pinnacle of Italian food in NYC.', u'author_name': u'Eric Kim', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110691300044441735616', u'time': 1463159433}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-YlJ65qg2Wv4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAByo/xTR4H-FVheQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'great old school italian. veal parm and milanese can't be beat. special ambiance..', u'author_name': u'Jack Feuer', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104923065114598943962', u'time': 1464056576}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-A5fmxWw13h0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAChk/3FqmLfYuIos/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Good Italian food. Plain and simple. Even with the trend for trendy and modern decor and fusion flavors this place strikes a balance of old world Italian with a current flair. We got whisked away to the back room where we were taken care of by an Italian who really new his menu. We got a blend of the stereotype NYC service and attentiveness. He really knew his menu and wines. He even knew the ratio of the different types of grapes. Excellent service. On to the food! Or first taste of their food was their focaccia and oil. I don't know how but their Olive Oil was fantastic. Simple and rich. It went well with slightly crusty and fluffy focaccia. The Caeser salad look sad when it arrived. Baby hearts of romain uncut on the plate. By surprisingly the dressing was a perfect balance of taste and texture. I should note here that the salad was 16.00 dollars and it was small. My wife ordered the spaghetti and meatballs since that as a special and i ordered the fettuccine amatriciana. Once again the balance of rich sauce to the "al dente" pasta was perfection. Every bite was a delight. On a side note the meatball was incredible. It was so good that it might be better than the pasta. Judge for yourself. For dessert we had a cannoli. The filling was super smooth and not sweet with the slight accent of chocolate. They were not pre made. The waiter made us the cannoli on the spot. So what is the downside? Price. All this amazing food was expensive. We ordered a salad, 2 entrees, glass of wine and 1 dessert and we spent 120.00. The cannoli was 8.50. If you can save up the money for a special date here then you must go. ', u'author_name': u'Bronson Kurtz', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115907149127057429996', u'time': 1462449576}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-8jzuIlNnspQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAB5g/GuefpO1yH2c/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is the best pasta I've ever had. u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WWeyHAfMa_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/cn3jjZFnhzA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Love this place great people working here, they are attentive, friendly and caring. The best pancake in the city is right here cooked to perfection. Usually there is a wait because this place is pretty popular among locals that come here. Overall great experience and food was amazing. ', u'author_name': u'Rafael Yau', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107744062940210293013', u'time': 1466393132}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-bb4_bU2T9bg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAjM/OgPOaXFiVkQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'One of my favorite places for brunch! Not only is the food amazing, but so is the hospitality. I made a reservation and asked for a booth in the notes, even though we were only two. They gave us the best corner seat booth by the window! I highly recommend the banana coconut croissant (not always displayed but they have it)! It's the most delicious croissant I've ever had!', u'author_name': u'Victoria Petersen', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106026482139030787362', u'time': 1456232228}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U4IBRWcWvhA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABB3c/KSohftLJ008/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Loved the service! The frisee salad was perfect. Thoroughly enjoyed the asparagus Polonaise dish for spring. The trout roe, crispy breadcrumbs, and grated hard boiled eggs on top of the asparagus was delicious. Wonderful beef tartare! Nice and spicy. BF loved the white gazpacho. The cheese course was nice and generous! We had the dessert with the rhubarb ice cream and pistachios cream and pistachio cake. It was gorgeous looking and quite yummy. The main courses were the only weak dishes. The trout with morels and ramps should have been amazing, but was pretty bland. BF's burger was very unevenly cooked. Parts were medium rare which is what he asked for and other parts were almost black and blue. This is great spot for people watching!', u'author_name': u'Jackie Gordon Singing Chef', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109673791694826464177', u'time': 1462212164}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-tRlEAD_YBcA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAASDg/2Zle2cq0sIs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Love this place! The bartender Antonio (I think that's his name) is always super nice. The bar is full service so I like to come in for a nice drink and some awesome food and oysters! ', u'author_name': u'Alexandria Johnson', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109651552011583600246', u'time': 1461638780}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Fancy french-style restaurant in Noho, where lots of beautiful people dine and brunch. They used to have an amazing ham and cheese croissant with egg, but unfortunately it was discontinued. Their fries are really good, and if you go for brunch try the lemon pancakes or the omelette.', u'author_name': u'Nicola Benatti', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103333165009759599473', u'time': 1466738542}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 533-3000', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'380', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'380'}, {u'long_name': u'Lafayette Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Lafayette St'}, {u'long_name': u'NoHo', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NoHo'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10003', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10003'}]}

u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-Z96KOPZ1WF8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/O5PxfEr1GPA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This might be the best dining experience a person can have in New York City. Tina is the most gracious, generous, warm and caring person who will do everything in her power to make sure you have an amazing night. Her husband Chip is a masterful chef and pastry guru. Together they are a powerful force and delightful in their humility and ability to entertain.', u'author_name': u'Chance Hart', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100110190225948313910', u'time': 1457530325}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-FQXKCRlwsSw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAs/IAP4A9dsVJo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Was looking for a special place to take my lady, and we had decided on French. I needed some place near our hotel or near Radio City where we were seeing a show, and out of the limited options, this looked like the best. Unfortunately, when I called at the end of November for a reservation, their outgoing message said they were booked for the entire month of December. Well, I knew I chose right at that point, but what to do? I left a message hoping there would be a cancellation, and they called me the next day to tell me they could squeeze me in at 5:45 for a pre-theater dinner (meaning they knew we'd be out in an hour or so). Score! This is a very small restaurant - only a handful of tables. Very minimalist decorations, but extremely classy and a dress code that if they don't need to enforce, because the patrons know better. Our waitress knew the menu inside and out - i was thoroughly impressed with the breadth of her knowledge. She was extremely helpful in making our choices as we were both a bit stuck between a couple of items.', u'author_name': u'Monica 夏', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110319965619207643361', u'time': 1458788920}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Sif8SeQel2Q/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAMoI/tnHuoD_Ut0E/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I'm almost embarrassed that I've just learned about The Simone. It's five blocks from my home, and I pass it regularly. In a sea of mediocre $200 NYC meals, The Simone is a shimmering island. Yes, dinner and drinks here is closer to $250, but relatively speaking, The Simone is a genuine bargain. That out of the way, last evening we had the great pleasure of dining here, and everything was ... pretty much perfect. We spent considerable time speaking with one of the owners throughout our meal, and it was apparent that everything runs as it does at The Simone by design. From classic service (serve from the left, clear from the right ... when did you last see THAT?) to the absolute invisibility of water and wine glasses always being refilled and napkins refolded. they're doing everything right at The Simone. Everything. And the food ... well, let's just say that our party of four sampled and shared a wide variety of things and everybody loved everything; and we're kind of an eclectic crew of palettes; that's no small feat. Truly wonderful. If you can get a table, go.', u'author_name': u'Jeff Yablon', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107656876763618847422', u'time': 1412166333}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-OGpOWEFGHt0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAcY/51jizSrIOBY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'My uncle owns this restraint and it is amazing and the food see you there', u'author_name': u'maximilian margolis', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102722977585733971798', u'time': 1453650726}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Uk0P4ZvOVL0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABCBE/45_ibtMivYo/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Confident food and service. u'international_phone_number': u'+1 646-422-7906', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Unparalleled cocktails (nominated the best bar in the world last year!) and really excellent service. The waiters know every detail about every single drink on the menu. I liked the way the old menu booklet looked better (you could buy it), but that's besides the point. Literally any cocktail will leave you satisfied. The food is also good, especially the steak sandwich.', u'author_name': u'Nicola Benatti', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103333165009759599473', u'time': 1466741151}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-VydrkvhzIQQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/wAobXXJKha0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is easily the best pub in NYC and by some the best in the country. You wont find TV's in this pub, just homeland pictures covering the ceilings and walls. They have a great set of regulars that are very friendly. They also have the best Guinness in the city hands down. The mixed drinks are very creative and very good. I recommend the Irish Coffee, the Guinness, and the Whiskey Punch. If you are ever in the area you have to make it a point to visit.', u'author_name': u'Phillip Fernandez', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102972035543818293124', u'time': 1461810500}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-767TyFFYvEc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/L8q1T6yBclA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great 1 oyster happy hour. They serve bluepoints which aren't my favorite but these were incredibly fresh. Good beef and barley soup and excellent fries served with 2 mayo based sauces for dipping. Great drinks. Incredible room. Worth the wait for dining in.', u'author_name': u'carlos borges', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100523151038559903070', u'time': 1463104198}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-DhmPfr23FWI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAo/iYEXCKrHj3g/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'When you enter, you see the old-fashioned pub with sawdust on the floor. It had lots and lots of photos on the antique-looking ceiling, and a large wall paining on the left site. It was a bit narrow, and not really a place for a sit-down meal. If you are just wanting to get some craft beer, bottled punch, and whiskeys of the world, then this is the spot. Since we were there to eat. we went upstairs to the Parlor. The dining space was filled with photos, wall to wall. They were all numbered, so I assume they have a list somewhere that tells us a description of each photo. The furniture other than chairs seemed pretty old, nice thick wood tables. Possibly the original flooring, and very impressive ceiling with exposed wood beam. I liked the darker green wall, that went really well with the rest of decor, and gave nice, relaxing atmosphere. Everything was really good here, even thought the prices are on a bit high side, but the quality was really high. The service was ok, but not great. As we sat down (without anyone directing us to a table), no one came for a while... until I went to grab a couple of menus, and started to look at them... But other than that, it was ok, the staffs were polite. Overall, we had nice time here, and food and drinks were great. I would love to go back for some other menu items they offer. Read my full review of this restaurant and food on my food blog, foodlovergirl.', u'author_name': u'Foodlover Girl', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116328682135597130625', u'time': 1463267333}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-c1tne3yCWZI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAACKzA/Gzint1JilVU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Really good drinks, the food was good, gotta try the truffle Fry's or chips as they call them. It can get crowded but they help find you a slot on the the other 2 floors if the 1st bar aera is packed. u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-QktxIfV8s80/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAeU/HV1WKtYwgwA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'With hospitality included and an almond ice cream to die for, Huertas is the perfect place to try a distinct cuisine that requires thought to piece the each delicious component together. A start with the chicken liver mousse can put anyone in the mood for a great meal and is only topped by the Arroz and the amazing morsels of flavor it hides.', u'author_name': u'zach ganzarski', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116816221408209447497', u'time': 1464922658}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I went with my girlfriend for my birthday, and found it a fun and palatable way of trying a cuisine (Basque) that isn't very advertised in the city. The chef personally came to our table and explained the particularities of every dish, and the rest of the staff was very approachable, personable and helpful.', u'author_name': u'Nicola Benatti', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103333165009759599473', u'time': 1466535738}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-BYyIyT2LdN0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABDU/R3Rb2KlBRao/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great selection and taste, was a bit disappointed with the chef's special off the menu dish that was barely cooked chorizo with peas, would have to expected something a bit more adventurous. {u'lat': 40.73766125000001, u'lng': -74.00565399999999}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.73764464999999, u'lng': -74.0059236}}}, u'adr_address': u'611 Hudson St, New York, NY 10014, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-390-1545', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-pPLgjVWbkAY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABQo/3Doc_BTMONE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Bar Bolonat is a lovely repsite located in the heart of the village. The food is excellent. It's flavorful and doesn't weigh you down. Highlights include the Everyday Califlower, Fluke Ceviche, Chickpea Gnocchi, Jerusalem Bagel, and the Duck entree that is cooked to perfection, don't pass up on the "Milky" Chocolate Pudding with Tuile Pretzel and the Halva Creme Brule, #nomnomnom. Dishes come out family style and service is friendly and unpretentious. A great spot for a date or a night out with friends. I also appreciate the A.C. on these warm days of summer. If you haven't tried out this gem of a village restaurant. You're definitely missing out!', u'author_name': u'Aaron Salazar', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106875076921188577314', u'time': 1465705029}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-ZUtveLTGzF8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAw0/l4rnhjdrT8A/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The food here is good but the server we had was a pretentious jerk who ruined our entire meal by making us feel uncomfortable through his confrontational attitude. Stating the plates are "family style" is a blatant lie when you get no more than a mere spoonful to share. We had the fried olives, Japanese eggplant, fattoush salad, kibbeh, ceviche, ribs, and sea bass. The ribs were juicy but if you're sharing, you get a sniff, a taste and the plate is empty. The salad, kibbeh and sea bass were average and nothing to write home about. Tiny portions, not suitable for sharing unless you're a petite bulimic. The server insisted that we place the entire order at once and stubbornly did not allow us to consider ordering more food later in the meal. The horrid attitude, the tiny plates and elevated price tag mean that you are left feeling hungry and resentful which is a pity because you really want to enjoy the place. We ended up getting a slice of pizza around the corner afterwards. We love Balaboosta. We are severely underwhelmed by Bolonat.', u'author_name': u'Anokhee Shah', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101969429136444865525', u'time': 1459205667}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I loved that Bar Bolonat allowed me to make a reservation, and we were seated right on time on a recent Monday night.The restaurant has awesome ambience, and it was packed with small parties at the tiny tables - get ready to get close to your neighbors. I love Taim, and was really excited to try out another restaurant from Einat Admony. Bar Balonat definitely fits in with the surrounding tony West Village - portions are teeny and prices are not. However, if you can get past this, the food was tasty and surprisingly filling, I actually took part of my Green Fatoush salad (served with avocado, mint and feta - amazing) to go since we filled up on the roasted cauliflower served with peanut tahini. Service was also great and though there wasn't many options for wine by the glass, the Sangiovese I enjoyed ($13) was a nice complement to the flavors of the food.', u'author_name': u'Chris Lee', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109677802200991176757', u'time': 1453483934}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-1tLCmCKgQMw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABQ8/dWlT3QidhpY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Good service. Food is o-kay. I actually find Taim (sister restaurant) is better and much cheaper', u'author_name': u'Elana Chan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114197551294289345525', u'time': 1453948963}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-9pxbJDkyIZY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAOk/z5ZVDfqYGgw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Food was delish and they had goldstar beer!! u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-S6HSnHHc4Mk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFkg/MhoBgQl68Sc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Two small plates was lots to eat for dinner. Loved the chicken sausage with star fruit and the crunchy coconut balls. Everything was a little spicy. The bangbang sauce was way too spicy for me, but the eggplant sauce was delicious. There service was attentive and the fog came out fresh and fast. Small plates are about $15, large plates are mostly double that or more. We spent $110 with tip for three people. ', u'author_name': u'Leah Hanson', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111824381782005927477', u'time': 1462820615}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-wNxqNZFLJ6E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACMs/nRiTpnxrfxQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Authentic Laotian food in a very industrial chic atmosphere. Lunch is phenomenal - get the crunchy Brussel sprouts with sweet peppers and the best banh mi in Manhattan. I prefer the coconut crusted shrimp but all are satisfying. You will crave food from here and wish you could get it delivered while slaving away in midtown. ', u'author_name': u'Phanessa Perez', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115521086333032835622', u'time': 1460271084}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'As a single guest you won't be seated on a table; the waitress absolutely wanted me to have dinner at the bar ... inacceptable (you might as well eat inside a loudspeaker, by the way). Laos ... still "terra incognita". ', u'author_name': u'JUERG 56', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117561693288079925468', u'time': 1465086548}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-IKSNctydZlM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAPPA/VFuGQEeY8nQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Legit Laos. On my last trip here, I enjoyed a tasting menu for the Laos new year: from the sticky rice to the duck salad to the pork belly, every bite was as good as Laos eateries I've been to in Paris and Philadelphia. Yes, it can get noisy in here with the TriBeCa crowd, but you'll barely notice while you savor their beef jerky. And damn, that jerky reminds me of Cambodian jerky. Yum. Thirsty? They've got a fully-stocked bar to keep your liver busy. Looking to romance a date? The combo of their crafted cocktails and attentive service will do the trick. And if it doesn't? Lean into shots, enjoy that liquor, and prepare for a ratchet night.', u'author_name': u'Dave Hong', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108637954815310549865', u'time': 1460691917}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-VlNZtwClx0Y/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACfA/dX-WiNAZwTU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This place is amazing. Very attentive wait staff and one of the most unique and delicious menus. {u'northeast': {u'lat': 40.71665015, u'lng': -74.00883805000001}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.71661235, u'lng': -74.00926544999999}}}, u'adr_address': u'30 Hudson St, New York, NY 10013, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-791-3771', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Dined here with a few girlfriends earlier this week and City Winery was great! As we waited for our final friend to show, the hostess brought us samples of their 'famous sauvignon blanc." It was definitely delicious and we even decided to order a bottle for the table. The food was great! We ordered the spread of the day + the cheese board to start. I had the burger while my friends had the steak, chicken, grilled cheese + soup and fish of the day. We were all pleasantly surprised with our food and continued to try different wines. The space itself was fairly small (we sat in the Barrel room, not the concert area) however, we had plenty of space on the table. I can't stand when they crowd everyone in and try to smush. Overall - City Winery receives 4 out of 5 stars in my book. They get docked a star for the slow service. I think sometimes they forgot about us!', u'author_name': u'Krist Lime', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117671878581041475111', u'time': 1461781627}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-LRc3L-u9npk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAADA/GbaZlgx3bCY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Ichimura Sensei has done an outstanding job on overcoming the limit of sourcing particular ingredients.His personality and techniques will deeply impress customers who love and respect sushi culture. But I have to mention that some waiters lack the knowledge of tea("......all the green tea just taste the same to me" .This just lmaf) and therefore might not able to bring people what they expect from the tea selection. In addition, there is probably a chance to dine with those who behave without basic fine dinning courtesy,and it may affect others' dining experience (Sushi Bar is not a bar, after all. So please don't drink like you just reach the age of 21yesterday and then make the counter loud like a party). I will go five starts to Ichimura San himself as a Sushi chef.But the team of the sushi bar really need to level up the rest aspects. I will still have a strong interest in dining regularly as always, even if the price might increase to some extent, as long as my visits would not lead me to sit with Dbags so often, like I have before.', u'author_name': u'jiacheng lou', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116308844168196101776', u'time': 1458664456}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-OLcXH5WRzOk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABQ/qzd4w3OolDY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'There's no menu here, just the omakase, which is nothing short of incredible. When you make a reservation, make sure it's for Ichimura's omakase - it's different from the Brushstroke restaurant. A secluded sushi nook with only 12 seats. It has no sign on the street, and no door of its own; you enter through Bouley's Brushstroke. Between the first-rate fare, classic Bouley service and dapper Shinto-shrine decor, this Michelin-starred sanctuary earns every dollar of the weekly paycheck you’ll have to fork over. The omakase-only menu is a parade of fluke, Hokkaido ocean trout, toro, and salmon roe, all flawless in composition. This is the kind of sleeper hit that critics dream about. Almost nobody was talking about the little sushi bar inside Brushstroke where Eiji Ichimura was quietly refining the techniques', u'author_name': u'尽力', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110837285894601305564', u'time': 1450890592}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Top quality sushi/sashimi omakase in NYC. This is on par with the other top 10 sushi/sashimi places in NYC. Great atmosphere, even better service. I recommend the deviled horseback for an appetizer, burger for an entree and any of the cocktails. Extensive wine menu, craft beers. No complaints. ', u'author_name': u'Kiersten Gourlay', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107608701942355095996', u'time': 1465651064}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WWeyHAfMa_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/cn3jjZFnhzA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Lovely and romantic place for lunch and dinner. Atmosphere feels laid back and cozy. The no reservations for this restaurant is pretty cool you can go when you want but there might be a 30 minute wait. Food is delicious and amazing. Overall great experience from the service to the food everything was prefect. ', u'author_name': u'Rafael Yau', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107744062940210293013', u'time': 1466821805}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'You can't go wrong with the appetizers: every single one of them is on point and won't make you regret not choosing another one. The burger is famously a must try: arguably one of the best gourmet burgers in NYC. If you don't like Roquefort cheese, don't let that make you refrain from ordering the burger, just scrape it off or ask not to include it. The Cubano sandwich is also great, comparable to Cafe Habana's. For vegetarians go for the Ricotta Gnudi.', u'author_name': u'Nicola Benatti', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103333165009759599473', u'time': 1466736039}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-e2JVvPvdGsA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAJA4/Ev9msGfxsDw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I'd excuse the mediocre food, expensive prices and dirty place. But their hospitality and service were beneath acceptable. There are better places in the neighborhood. u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-AXc95295_h4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/yhJbXuqHpzs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'It's tempting to consider The Clam to be a "seafood shack" but it's really a full fledged creative seafood restaurant. Each plate takes a traditional "shack" dish and kicks it up a notch with oils, spices and seasonal vegetable accompaniment that bring out the best from the sea. Experience is further complimented by a cozy ambience and one of the best wine (and saks)-by-the-glass programs you'll find at a seafood restaurant of its class. ', u'author_name': u'Kevin Cabral', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103612062459546747277', u'time': 1466959183}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-eIjL9D6frUA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACx8/EJZkJdZgDsc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Went here for an early dinner and it's a great seafood place, kind of off the beaten path. Start with the Clam Dip, our waiter described it perfectly as French Onion dip with clams. The homemade chips it comes with pair perfectly with it. My girlfriend and I split the baked clams, lobster and fried clam sliders, and the old bay fries. All of it tasted really great, especially the sliders (although a bit pricey at 2 for $24). Overall, a really great seafood place with good cocktails/beer, and a great ambiance.', u'author_name': u'Robert Lurie', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113223639195356999845', u'time': 1460564185}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-32GZyDpjUC8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAADg/kMC9DUEYv7s/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Excellent experience. The quality of food, even the chicken (surprisingly for a seafood restaurant) was very high, served by our friendly, knowledgeable and efficient server in a pleasant and clean atmosphere with a lively (but not too noisy) vibe. Great west village option. We will definitely return. ', u'author_name': u'Warren Brumel', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109861055461841363278', u'time': 1464657823}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Beautifully balanced, great conceptual combinations....that means ...really good. The steamers were pristinely fresh, and by having the clams in a bowl of broth they stayed hot and, there was a generous cup of broth also. The fried clam and lobster sliders are delicious. Every step is well executed - lovely service, great food and even homemade Parker rolls! I'll be back soon.', u'author_name': u'nancy friedman', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116838821258289171628', u'time': 1460052996}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-qOf63Je27AU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACJQ/heypbDZHzU8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is one of those places where nothing matters besides the food. Staff was friendly and accommodating, although I found our waiter slightly stoned-faced. Oysters: best oysters I've had in a while. So fresh! Fluke crudo: simple, if you want to disassemble the fish, but absolutely divine and inspired. Enough for two people to taste and not awkwardly have to split the last piece. My entree, salmon, was to die for and I don't even go crazy for salmon. I sort of eat it like "medicine", cause it's good for you! But I really liked it this time. Perfectly cooked, perfectly flavored. My boyfriend's dish, pasta with clams was also excellent. The dessert, panna cotta, was also outstanding. Can't wait to go back. And I forgot to mention the rolls they bring you between dishes which were absolutely delicious. Pricey but worthy!', u'author_name': u'Hsa Hopp', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116944491551080511777', u'time': 1458606406}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 242-7420', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'420', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'420'}, {u'long_name': u'Hudson Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Hudson St'}, {u'long_name': u'West Village', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'West Village'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10014', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10014'}]}

u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Mk2Dy3VTb10/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAH4/TrnsLRALSuQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is by far my favorite restaurant in all of Manhattan. We had the seasonal 7-course meal with a wine pairing and everything exceeded expectations. The atmosphere is upbeat and absolutely classy. Service is second to none. There is truly not a better place to dine. ', u'author_name': u'Kiersten Gourlay', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107608701942355095996', u'time': 1465790363}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Booked a large group about a month in advance for a birthday celebration. We all did the chef's tasting menu (one vegetarian). We were greeted with a complimentary bottle of champagne. The menu consisted of a good variety of exciting flavors and textures. My favorite was the lobster dish. The wait staff was almost choreographed they were so swift with serving and clearing dishes. The decor was breathtaking with fresh cherry blossoms spread throughout. Finally we finished with some unforgettable desserts. One of my most memorable meals in NYC!!', u'author_name': u'YU ER', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101298514089007651078', u'time': 1466462356}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-egMyDrnNwt8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAo/eckznzkbbyw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'For my entree I got the Grilled Shrimp & Dumplings, Miso Soup and Bok Choy. For dessert I got the Vanilla Custard Pie, Graham Cracker, Rhubarb, Oat Streusel and Strawberry Sorbet. Both were outstanding Staff was friendly, place was clean. 5/5.', u'author_name': u'Evan Jarrod', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/118074375106355708561', u'time': 1465492336}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-QQfO7Nt1FP0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAFM/fLR6DpBRR8c/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'It was nice enough to try once but I won't be going back. The highlight was probably the service - super attentive and genuinely friendly. The wine selection was quite good. The food was only ok. Tasty enough but not creative at all. I tasted the tartar, spinach linguine and chicken main. Solid rustic style but nothing stood out for me and I opted to go elsewhere for dessert as a result. ', u'author_name': u'Rachel D', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111536671166633368178', u'time': 1460486769}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-0N3JF_-AkWM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAWh0/TeMta2T-HS4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I visited the Gramercy Tavern on Feb 15th 2016, well what can I say....AMAZING! the gin was outstanding, the food out of this world and as my partner couldn't decide which dessert to have they let her have two! We had the three course menu but I wish we'd gone for the more expensive matched wine one....next time for sure. I cannot put into words how truly amazing this place is. Thanks to all the staff.', u'author_name': u'Colin Sutherland', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103081223759820720177', u'time': 1463936774}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 477-0777', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'42', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'42'}, {u'long_name': u'East 20th Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'E 20th St'}, {u'long_name': u'Midtown', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Midtown'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10003', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10003'}]}

u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-647-1818', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Brunch here is great, especially in the summer when the bay doors are open and you feel like you're outside even when you're not. The menu is approachable but innovative. There are dishes for everyone from meat lovers to vegetarians and there are even gluten free options. The staff is professional and helpful. Not fancy, but casual and relaxing. ', u'author_name': u'David Shane', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102339182686381786592', u'time': 1466256499}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-vk5SgwGYYJM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABN0/hmyLs-6Knu0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I laughed when I saw my plate. I get it, the rent is high but... if you got to serve us bird-sized portions, it might be time to fold the seats, snatch the cabinets, utensils, and things, and move it to a cheaper neighborhood. The food wasn't even all that good. The bread looked and tasted like one of Jesus' disciples delivered it from Nazareth. I'm sure it was the one Judas planned to bring to the Last Supper, but The Lord wasn't having it. So I ended up having to eat it with Dead Sea salt and anointing oil. Now I see why it was on my table instead of His.', u'author_name': u'Aaron Hunt', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115013401448290713945', u'time': 1467174509}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-P-yMSXH7nK8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGQY/IMkGs7tWMyw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Went for a brunch. The fresh juices are delicious. A lot of choice. The focaccia is very good and all the dishes we ordered were well made and tasty. You can go with a group as there are big tables', u'author_name': u'Gabrielle Ughetto', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110278659219261435426', u'time': 1463968003}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Y-QIh3RPMxI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABDo/rMtyhSaq84A/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Beautiful space, quite good Italian food. The sicilian salad was great, better than you'd guess from the description. Then, I had the linguine with lemon, which were really well balanced. The tiramisu was a little bit disappointing, but the olive oil cake was delicious. Service was ok, nothing specially good or bad. ', u'author_name': u'Pierre Mégevand', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112590539453571730808', u'time': 1464129836}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-xQZiIdsGeUM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAa8/PYV9NxfDZTI/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Out of this world. Second time having it and it didn't disappoint - Waldorf salad (appetizer) - nothing special - cauliflower side - great side option with an interesting sauce - lemon tart (desert) - nothing special either. Great atmosphere. Upscale cafe that is actually a quieter ambience ( which can be tough to find in NYC) Overall, enjoyable experience but was a slightly disappointed as I had higher expectations coming in ', u'author_name': u'Nick Nohling', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112051946234919749829', u'time': 1464435426}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-mWi1_JtYIzU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAsbI/F2hPFVkQR18/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Pretty nice big cafe atmosphere, great service and delicious food. I'll definitely be coming again. The main floor reminded us a bit of Grand Central Terminal's lower floor, in a good way, probably because of the illumination and faux arches. The black label burger was great, and the french fries on the side were fried right. The ile flottante dessert was like eating a dream.', u'author_name': u'Javier Kohen', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114955250538652050870', u'time': 1462841293}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Ujwpr800KuE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/JwtWg2j9ktw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Amazing restaurant... Amazing steak. We were here for the Thanksgiving meal, and everything was fantastic! Granted, I don't know what is on the menu normally since it was a Thanksgiving special. ', u'author_name': u'Jeffrey Hire', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104313893240150656332', u'time': 1448569624}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'My girlfriend and I eat out 3 meals per day so we feel are somewhat of the NYC restaurant connoisseur group. We enjoy good food, good service and a comfortable setting. This morning for brunch we met friends at Le Pain Quotidien at 861 Lexington. It was nice as always and all organic which we also like. During our brunch our friends kept raving about this place across the street that they eat dinner at weekly so we decided after our breakfast to stop by. It was quaint, clean and had a nice menu. We decided that we would eat dinner there after we hung out in the Park for the day. We entered around 5:30 on a sunny day so we decided to eat on the outside patio. The hostess was the most pleasant person we encountered the entire day as she seemed more like a friend than a staffer. She then introduced us to the bartender who was also just as friendly. We sat outside and they both came out periodically throughout our ordering and meal to chit chat with us which we found extremely refreshing. We were also meeting several other people from the area as well which made our meal that much more fun. We were drinking our typical Sunday Bloody Mary's and decided to take the plunge into ordering some food. We looked, then we ordered some of the most interesting dishes we have ever had in NYC. I had Chicken Kiev with a Risotto that I am still craving for the day after. My girl had a light salad, the Squash Soup and a Scallops entree that was cooked to perfection. This place was not just a great restaurant with great food but it was also a place where we can say we felt at home. Good people, good food, good atmosphere this place has it all... u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-7RCCL3dDkBA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAA4Ec/QqhQmDqkHkU/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Simple menu (choose the burger, lobster roll, steamed or grilled lobster). They also have a combo that comes with two burgers and a lobster. Each order comes with a small salad and fries, both of which were alright but nothing to write home about. While the food is decent, and served quickly, at $20 a pop, it's not the best bang for the bucks in NYC. That said, I really dig the interior design here. Big bar area, spacious seating, nice lighting, and lofty layout. The ambiance is what elevates this place. ', u'author_name': u'Charlie Shay', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116218922709794678656', u'time': 1461812793}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I don't even want to give it 1 star. There were multiple tables open but they took us down to the basement to be seated. It smelled like rats, and was very damp feeling. I was disappointed. Totally. NEVER AGAIN!!!!', u'author_name': u'niquelov D', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116860355862866007106', u'time': 1466032036}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-9VLt2aoZxYY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAwo/WNMbND-iYgM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Burger, lobster, or lobster roll for $20. (Or a $60 combo consisting of 2 burgers, a lobster, and 2 desserts). I think it's the simplicity of the menu that attracts people so if you have that one friend who can never decide what to order, Burger & Lobster is probably the best place to bring him/her. B&L does not accept reservations. They also won't seat you until everyone in your party is there. They won't even accept your name. Everyone in your party has to be present in order to even put your name down to wait for a table. Luckily it wasn't too crowded yet on a Tuesday right before 6 for my party of 5. It started getting crowded around 6:30 and that's when they squeezed randos together at one table. Before coming here, I always thought people were crazy for ordering the burger. It's $20! For a burger!? What's so special about it? That is until I got there and the burgers were starting to look pretty good to me. Plus they were huge! But in the end, I opted for the lobster roll. It's a cold lobster roll made with Japanese kewpie mayo, served with a side of fries and a small salad. It looks kind of small but I was actually pretty full afterwards (but I did also have a beer - their drinks are pretty pricey with beers starting at $8+ and wines at $10+). They give you a good amount of lobster meat and it wasn't chewy at all, unlike some other lobster rolls I've had in my life. My mom ordered the grilled lobster (you have an option of steamed, or steamed and then finished off on the grill) and I thought the meat was tough. Glad I didn't get that but she said she liked it and that's all that matters! Food comes out really quickly. We ordered, and all the food came out about 10 minutes later. I guess that's the good thing about only having three menu items. You can continuously cook those three things - you know that someone will always order one of them! If I decide to come back, I'll be trying out their burger next time. I'll let you know how it goes! ', u'author_name': u'Melanie Tam', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103707591633272033722', u'time': 1466552540}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-aX1rEuHk20s/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAMG0/2xYk8tYM6g8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Simple menus. Easy to order. Food came out quick! Large space. Great for groups. ', u'author_name': u'David Xu', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117985443336936130559', u'time': 1466282459}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-ynjXg2DeZuA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAj5k/BRNcv3hgobs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'A super simple concept - but incredible food for only $20!! There are only a few options at this place, so it takes only moments to order your food and receive it. We came on Easter Sunday and the staff was wearing pink tutus :). I ordered the lobster roll - big chunks of lobster claw delicately dressed in a light dressing. Their bread was outstanding - a thick piece of bread that could withstand the creamy texture. No sogginess at all. Comes with fries - very tasty. The full lobster can be steamed or grilled, and comes with regular butter or garlic butter, both served in a gravy boat. Fantastic. The salads were a nice addition as well. Overall, fantastic meal for the price.', u'author_name': u'Marygrace Ashdown', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113844467672487376421', u'time': 1461684584}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(646) 833-7532', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'39', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'39'}, {u'long_name': u'West 19th Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'W 19th St'}, {u'long_name': u'Midtown', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Midtown'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10011', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10011'}]}

u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-RwwO1mYWiS4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABCg/7fw5TOrRVrg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'My concern when I try a new Thai place is that most Thai places in US serve either too Americanized or too salty plates (sometimes both), which I can say is not a case for this restaurant. You can smell the spices as you enter the space. It's pretty well decorated with right amount of the light and Southeast Asian ambience. In the green mango salad, freshness of the green mango balances out the fishy smell of the fried dried-squid, crunchiness of which delivers nice texture to the dish. Grilled baby octopus is cooked well that it's smoky on the surface and chewy inside. Crab fried rice comes with good amount of real crab (big chunks) and would be a pretty safe choice for Thai food novices. Golden curry is nicely balanced in creaminess of the taste and the thickness, and chicken is pretty tender. I'm not sure if I'd call this an authentic or adventurous menu out of all but again, a pretty safe choice. (Tip: the portion in general is moderate and I order side of jasmine rice to eat with the curry soup.) ', u'author_name': u'HongJoon Jang', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112794189915322451359', u'time': 1466534426}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-4HQR_AxpIlY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABRc/ueZ7hgBXTZ4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Every dish we had was fantastic but what made this experience truly special for me was that the most memorable dishes were not the main courses as it usually is. My jasmine tea chili bourbon was one of the best cocktails I've ever had. The roti was tasty and not overly fried and heavy, with a hint of salt on every bite. The sauces that accompanied a lot of the dishes were heavenly. And last but not least, the coconut sundae was absolute perfection and an excellent topping for the two other desserts we ordered.', u'author_name': u'Faye Xu', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109095752970763299318', u'time': 1462500596}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-rsRonY7aerU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEM/sbU_UwvTrtA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Best restaurant for authentic Thai food in NYC! I have so many favorites: the betel leaf wrap, grilled baby octopus, chicken liver, sweet breads, and blood sausage. Also try their spicy tamarind margarita. Service is always great, and I love the ambiance. The décor, music, and small rooms make you feel transported to another place and time. ', u'author_name': u'Francesca S.', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114808372807923687999', u'time': 1466864475}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Good for a small group dinner, as the place is tiny itself. Got there quite early and waited for two hours before getting our table: we had the khao soy, masaman curry and larb, some of which too spicy for some of us, but nonetheless everything was great. To drink they brought us a large fruit punch-like bowl. Dulcis in fundo, the condensed milk on top of chunky toast slice was mouthwatering.', u'author_name': u'Nicola Benatti', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103333165009759599473', u'time': 1466549878}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-767TyFFYvEc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/L8q1T6yBclA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Everything was super salty. We may have ordered the wrong things. The rib appetizer was a salt fest. Crispy pig ears was a salt fest. The grilled prawns were good. Will have to go back to try out some other things. ', u'author_name': u'carlos borges', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100523151038559903070', u'time': 1465515995}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(646) 370-6650', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'7', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'7'}, {u'long_name': u'Spring Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Spring St'}, {u'long_name': u'Nolita', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Nolita'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10012', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10012'}]}
