From the bread to the rich green olive oil - to the ambience,service & my delectable glass of wine. This place is a surprising gem in the wall - & I cannot wait to go back! They got all the details of my instructions re my very yummy meal - just right!', u'author_name': u'Mary Kennedy', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111573775423048623942', u'time': 1456124528}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-tBcneUpbhzI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAADM/ZE61Ilkw4hQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This is our favorite neighborhood gem. It's warm and cozy and literally just across the street. Chef Roberto take great care with the ingredients. Everything is made fresh. We regularly go for dinner and often go with our favorite dishes such as the "Tagliolini ai Finferli" (Egg Tagliolini with Chanterelles, Crispy Speck, over Parsley Root Purée), the Duck two ways and the Vitello Tonnato. We just started going for brunch yesterday and it was delightful. Freshly baked bread basket and a 'pumpkin capuchino' aperitief. Loved the Brioche French Toast and saffron risotto with Veal Cheek in a deep savory vegetable reduction. The staff is always courteous and kind and Giselle Deiaco is warm and welcoming. Almost forgot the deserts rock too! The Tiramisu and Semifreddo are heavenly. ', u'author_name': u'Allen Ackerman', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101336325011854538028', u'time': 1445821101}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-w-FWWK-wdhc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAJw/Qe5iAdkT4UE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Lovely atmosphere, great service and excellent food (reasonably priced too). Will definitely be back. ', u'author_name': u'Petra H Wood', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104360448241966328576', u'time': 1449456636}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I don't understand Jan's review. It sounds as though you had a bad experience, and you were so upset that when you went back to complain, perhaps the folks you spoke with were so surprised to hear what you had to say they were, literally, gobsmacked? Let me explain. We've been here many, many times -- it's among our favorite places to go anywhere in the City. This isn't simply yet another, generic Italian restaurant -- it's a fine dining experience, in a relaxed atmosphere and at a reasonable price. The food is terrific -- Roberto DeArco is really doing something special here. Whether you start with his really good take on Vitello Tonnato, a Lobster Caprese Salad or a more straightforward Fritto di Mare that is as light as anything fried could be, go on to have his Ricotta Ravioli Stuffed with Quail Egg, Zucchini Blossom Pesto and Black Truffles, or the Maialino or the Branzino, it's all just so light and tasty. I haven't yet tried the Veal Milanese, but I will -- I saw someone at another table the other night being served theirs, and the size of it alone made me want to reconsider what I'd ordered for my main course! It was so big it merited its own zip code! All the pastas here are made in house, as are the breads and even the breadsticks. While I'm generally not a fan of desserts, and tiramisu in particular, this place's take on that dish is something else. It's so light, it's almost ethereal -- first, you get the custardy, creamy deliciousness that isn't cloying or heavy, and then that hit of espresso. In short, what this place does is bring really good Italian food to a part of the City that really doesn't have it, and it does so in a way and at a price that is so much more affordable than say, Carbone or Costata or your typical Michael White establishment. Don't misunderstand me -- those places all do a very good job -- most of the time. I've eaten at Marea twice and left utterly underwhelmed -- perhaps the kitchen was having a bad night on both occasions. But I would try it again. Perhaps, Jan, you might want to do the same with East12th Osteria, particularly if you are a local, as you say. While I agree with you that there are indeed "plenty of other Italian restaurants in the area" to patronize, I can't think of one that attempts to do with Italian food what this place does, and at this price-point, anywhere in the City, let alone in the East Village.', u'author_name': u'Howard Leader', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107218670812703077942', u'time': 1434840866}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This restaurant offers a prix fixe menu between 5:30 and 7 pm. Last Wednesday we walked in at 6:40. One other table was occupied. We were given a regular menu and asked for the prix fixe menu. The very rude waitress told us that we were too late and the kitchen couldn't accommodate us. Needless to say, we walked out. On Sunday we passed the restaurant (where all tables were empty) and I went in and asked for the manager. After I explained what had happened, she had no comment--just stonily stared at us. We live in the neighborhood, and I have told everyone I know not to patronize this business. There are plenty of other good Italian restaurants in the area.', u'author_name': u'Jan Keith', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117880907015792337614', u'time': 1431456191}], u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-duwGdzgipbg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAACWrg/1wtflifzobE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Simply the best of its kind outside of Japan. Great with friends or a small business group. Best suited to 'family style' sharing unless everyone is up for a noodle bowl. Since the place is popular do expect a few minutes wait as a walk in but they take care of you with a drink within seconds. Staff was amazing, above and beyond to accommodate and service our party.', u'author_name': u'Jan-Wouter Arendsen', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105816838108993753284', u'time': 1465245057}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-flmQh5645Ng/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAIeU/h3c9XQ1B76c/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This place lives up to its reputation and delivering excellent Ramen noodles and other dishes. We had the chicken wings and the Momofuku Ramen, both of which were excellent. However, the broth for the ramen was slightly salty. But given the effort that goes into making this broth, one could easily excuse the salt content. Definitely a place to try if you want to have great ramen. ', u'author_name': u'Rono Stinnett', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114491874559761306441', u'time': 1465734847}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-oL2QlSEZ3z8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAALUQ/SRtrgWSZq2s/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Best pork buns anywhere in the city. Unfortunately, the ramen is kind of underwhelming (go to Totto instead). I also wouldn't recommend the special-order fried chicken ($150), which is a bit funny considering that Momofuku has an amazing fried chicken sandwich place down the street (Fuku).', u'author_name': u'cary ang', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108315316918803148463', u'time': 1466609409}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-wtxQgB8nvag/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAzOQ/OCTpsC8IGMM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Smoking hot tasty. Sat at the kitchen bar and watched theses guys at work. Amazing. Gotta tip heavy having watched a team of people work that hard for your food. The shrimp buns are divine, the umami flavours in the rice cake was epic and I loved the huajao notes in the noodle bowl. Could ready here every day.', u'author_name': u'Ewen Bell', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106266240152178137696', u'time': 1464371180}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WWeyHAfMa_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/cn3jjZFnhzA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The Ramen noodles were ok, the broth was tasty. The service was pretty fast, servers were nice and friendly. Honestly I feel momofuku is over rated, you could find better noodle bars In the same area. Overall its worth a visit.', u'author_name': u'Rafael Yau', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107744062940210293013', u'time': 1464750542}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 777-7773', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'171', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'171'}, {u'long_name': u'1st Avenue', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'1st Avenue'}, {u'long_name': u'East Village', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'East Village'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10003', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10003'}]}

u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/--w9hY9HeBtM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAJw/OJANeCl5FIE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Food: Before we go onto the food, there are some issues I have with the experience. My gf and I decided to check out this restaurant on a wed night. Upon speaking to the hostess (which was very sweet) she told us that it would be around an hr wait, so we decided to wait, after about an hr we checked in the hostess again and she had a startled look on her face (probably because she gave our table away) but she stated that it will be a little longer since there was an "old couple" that had the table and we would need to wait a little longer. After 25 more mins of waiting, she comped our drinks which was very nice of her, and we were shown to our table. The table looked like a makeshift table in the middle of the restaurant with staff buzzing around us the whole night and were knocking into my chair multiple times throughout the evening. All this would have been fine but the food was just not worth it. Now onto the food. We ordered: 1. The meatballs Really good meat balls, but it came out kind of cold. 2. Clams casino Very good, very flavorful and the crusty bread crumbs made it really delicious. The only thing I may possibly reorder. 3. Pasta with Uni This is the reason why we decided to come here. I gf loves uni pasta and we have sampled many different ones throughout the city. But this one was not very good. For starters it was MP and it was $35 for about a cup of pasta and bits of uni, not even full pieces. The sauce was very thick and like another yelper noted the consistency of glue. It was not worth the price. 4. Rigatoni with duck ragu It was ok. The pasta was a little over cooked and the sauce was too sweet for my taste. But the duck was cooked well. Brew: Great selection of beers, especially one of my favorites Moretti. Overall I would not return, the food was ok and there are many other Italian restaurants in the city to try.', u'author_name': u'Gerry Soman', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104771156389302364225', u'time': 1461283071}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-p26TpspyH2A/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABtU/pn-Ho-Qg5-A/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Though this was a little out of my comfortable price range, it was well worth it. I had some pan fried chicken breast in a buttery sauce over some braised kale. The table had various appetizers, I had the cheese on polenta chips which were a nice palate cleansing bite, and the meatballs which I could have made a meal of. They were moist and delicious and the salad garnish was amazing and complimented it well. This would be a good place for a date, and if they ever came out with a cookbook, I would definitely give it a try!', u'author_name': u'Vernon Williams', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105901957035756927817', u'time': 1455835219}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Came here for RW Winter 2016... Come with the idea to share everything.. Definitely the best strategy. The decor/service was really nice, relaxed, comfy booths/couches and nice waiters who wear hipster leather aprons... Apps-my favorite being the fluke, really fresh, not swimming in any dressing. The stracciatella cheese tastes just like burrata, and the meatballs were really light! Not all dense and thick, bleh. Dinner- The short ribs. Just do it. HUGE potion, enough for three.. It's cooked medium/medium rare... Really good.. There are some big chunks of fat though that get tough. The bucatini was also very good, came in a very creamy sauce and the pasta is cooked very much on the al dente side. Dessert- the olive oil cake was good! But the ricotta ice cream on the side was much more interesting. The chocolate and vanilla gelato was really creamy and rich and the lemon gelato tasted just like frozen lemonade. Would definitely come back for drinks, they have a small bar down below that looks ~cool~ and definitely a nice option for the area.', u'author_name': u'blue sky', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113261705937987089905', u'time': 1454287379}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ivi5lw5ChR0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAJ9M/Q879M9PBj20/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Yes! This unassuming below-street-level-Venetian restaurant in Flatiron is a gem. Best dishes? Bucatini and the All'onda burger. We ordered the Bucatini, ramen and All'onda burger. Bucatini was delicious. Generous amounts of uni and cream and generous helping of lemon juice to cut into the fattiness of this dish. I wish the uni was more briny but it was still a great dish. And that burger! Surprisingly good considering Venetian cuisine is a pescatarian's dream. Juicy, medium rare burger topped with a thin layer of cheese and caramelized onions. Great burger. The ramen was ok. For the next visit, I want to try their Brussels sprouts, burrata and skate.', u'author_name': u'Doreen Ng', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115232828402274613209', u'time': 1449667346}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Pasta was served ice cold --- sent it back and after many apologies it came back and the meatballs were still frozen on the inside. Food over all was very average as was the atmosphere. Go to perla or any of a number of great italian spots in the hood instead - I don't expect this spot will remain open for much longer anyway.', u'author_name': u'Vinay Kapur', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117807767660638793757', u'time': 1442669849}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 231-2236', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'22', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'22'}, {u'long_name': u'East 13th Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'E 13th St'}, {u'long_name': u'Lower Manhattan', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lower Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10003', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10003'}]}

u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-4wYSvam42V0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAADEA/vKd0V8pUw1o/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Excellent sushi, very fresh and innovativei. More light fusion traditional sushi than a western one. Great experience! They also have a great high end selection of sake. Bottom line: expensive but worth every $', u'author_name': u'yaron wartski', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112538617364071927861', u'time': 1466228456}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-NkQuqkClw0A/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFEM/EnOHgKVWnAw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Make sure you snag a reservation a month before and sit at the sushi bar and enjoy their omakase. The décor is quite nice, girls you can definitely dress up if you want! Why is it a 4 not a 5? Food wise definitely a 5, amazing sushi, the chef's pay super careful attention to detail and impeccable service. I also love that it's located in the West village, makes it an upscale sushi restaurant in a quaint area. If you're ordering by piece, the kinmedai, scallop, yellowtail, cherry salmon are musts! But obviously what's good will also depend on the season of the fish. Don't forget to have the tamago too! The $90 wine pairing was sub-par unfortunately. It didn't enhance the experience of the food (many of the pairings didn't actually go well with the sushi). I would have rather ordered a few wines by the glass that I know I'd enjoy. The positive part about the wine pairing was that they gave very generous pours! Overall, truly enjoyed this place and will be back. ', u'author_name': u'Rohenne Lee', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105603284385958429156', u'time': 1464267296}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Nf7Lz2Wtl-k/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACQI/a1aHELq1zR8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'After eating at Toronto's YASU last summer, and as a long-time fan of Jiro Dreams of Sushi, I was excited beyond words to eat here - and the experience delivered. The fish was uniformly fresh, the rice delightfully aromatic in a way that I've never before experienced, and the tamago as arrestingly light as the movie suggests. Interacting with Jiro is an absolute delight - he is theatrical, excited about what he does, and infectiously enthusiastic. How he does this for three seatings a night, every night, is beyond me, but it's much appreciated. Note that you only get served sushi made by Nakazawa if you sit at the bar. Otherwise, it's sous-chefs who slice and prepare the nigiri, which is then delivered to you via waiter. The upcharge to be personally served by the restaurant's namesake is well worth it. The whole production is a show, and well worth the arduous process of securing reservations. As many have noted, the Sake pairing is a must - at only an additional $45, it's practically a gift. Tasting notes are provided throughout, and the choices complement the fish nicely. Sushi Nakazawa was by some measure, the most expensive meal I've ever paid for myself. Yet it was worth every penny; I would hardly demur at paying a few hundred dollars for a spectacular cultural event - what's the difference in splurging on an extraordinary meal?', u'author_name': u'Kevin Wong', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102615311059680400567', u'time': 1462200146}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-7IsU-iFMHxA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAtu0/RvNV7obYVaA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Service: There appeared to be a high staff to customer ratio, at least for the sushi bar. Since it's situated near the entrance, there's more staff around the area. Food: It is quite simply amazing. The rice vinegar was not excessive, so as to not take away from the flavor of the fish. The tuna and uni were the stand out favorites, but I really liked everything. Decor (sushi bar): A clean white counter top and a nice polished dark granite slab. The sushi bar was brightly lit at the center stage, where Nakazawa-san gets to work. Atmosphere (sushi bar): I don't believe the sushi bar can seat more than 10 people at a time. As such, unless you're seated with a unruly crowd, the ambiance should be on the quieter, more intimate side. It can be a little upscale. Plenty of nicely dressed individuals. Don't come in a t-shirt, polo at minimum.', u'author_name': u'Gary Wong', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116714862657965372689', u'time': 1457764964}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-d8H8ThT85QA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFFM/oIkkhLtqEY4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Most amazing sushi ever! I was a bit skeptical about paying so much for pieces of raw fish, but having watched the Jiro documentary, I was willing to splurge out of curiousity. Nakazawa, who was the senior apprentice in the movie, serves patrons who dine at the bar during weekdays; it is totally worth the $30 surcharge versus eating in the dining room, where your food is prepared by his team. My meal consisted of 21 pieces of amazing sushi, taking around 2 hours to finish, allowing sufficient time in between bites to really savor and enjoy the masterpiece. Chef Nakazawa is jovial and entertaining, and wait staff on the side are always on standby to explain anything about the origins or preparation of the sushi. You can really taste not only the freshness of the ingredients, but the effort that went into making each piece be able to melt in your mouth. Completely worth the money!', u'author_name': u'Karen Hsu', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111860807890848973659', u'time': 1460215931}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 924-2212', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'23', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'23'}, {u'long_name': u'Commerce Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Commerce St'}, {u'long_name': u'West Village', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'West Village'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10014', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10014'}]}

will not only not go back myself but advise other people not to go as well! ', u'author_name': u'Phuong Pham', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110727475564997500321', u'time': 1463931006}, {u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-3UNhmT9kWlc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAKw/4dEd6dUgLHg/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Honestly i dont know how you could give such a high rate to such a place. u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WWeyHAfMa_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/cn3jjZFnhzA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great restaurant to grab lunch or dinner. The staffs were professional and helpful. If you are wondering they do parties and there is a room for parties of 15 or more called the chefs table. They also have a great selection of wines. I suggest trying the gnocchi rosa, bistecca alla fiorentina, grilled octopus, trout belly tartar, olive oil cake and the warm chocolate budino. Overall great experience and food was out of this world. ', u'author_name': u'Rafael Yau', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107744062940210293013', u'time': 1465880321}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-KhcfMieyB8w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAKU/K8wYXe6W-o0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Really interesting choices on the menu and one of my favorite playlists of any restaurant in the area (Old school Hiphop). The Farro salad is a favorite and you can't go wrong with any of the pastas. Most of the plates are sharing menu inspired but I typically get my own food anyway.', u'author_name': u'Kevin Bischoff', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116800607286826024712', u'time': 1465311741}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-L_xiwHUw_w8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABEw/3rJXzLoNsJc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'A mixed bag. Service a little slow and had to wait 10 minutes for our table. After 5, offered a seat at the bar but no sign of anyone to order a drink from. Good on our waiter for taking one of the dishes of the bill. To wit: the beef carpaccio was a huge disappointment - heavy-honestly slathered in some sort of chilli paste. Sprouts decent, octopus v good and the radicchio salad excellent, as was the focaccia. The burrata was plain weird (served with pickled onion and carta musica which had a faint flavour of curry powder) and the fries a little overcooked. Disappointing', u'author_name': u'Ollie Gandy', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110645501779198238582', u'time': 1457324250}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-nJBEk-Ty77E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAFA/Kbvl3rt5slw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Roast chicken is usually a snooze, but somehow it's amazing here. So good!', u'author_name': u'Ryan Bares', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115406962373849908158', u'time': 1456329054}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Walked by here when meeting Alaina league. Looked very solid for drink happy hour spot. $65 for appetizer pasta entree and dessert. Charlie Jonas plans on going here. ', u'author_name': u'Ross Smith', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117268420027585000430', u'time': 1460157624}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-5tBoHrT9biI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAL8/5w9vESSCZqA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Incredible space and ambiance! Food is seriously amazing, I would definetly say 5 star and even michelline star status! Amazing service , love everything about this place.', u'author_name': u'David Haughton', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103406780805512967889', u'time': 1451458066}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-dI9TNCJTlQo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAHSw/Qwp5DoucBO0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Lapin and I came here on Saturday for brunch. We had reservation for 2pm but arrived around 1pm. The place was pretty much empty. We sat in the back area to dine. The decor and ambience was resplendent. Our waiter was polite and efficient but most of the time he left us to ourselves -- sometimes with an empty glass. We ordered the assorted pastry basket ($9) to share. The basket came with 5 different types of mini pastries from scones, cinnabons, muffins, etc. Most of the pastries were tasty but some tasted a bit stale.It would also been nice if they provided an assortment of jams/jellies/preserves, honey or butter as some of the pastries are a bit dry. I ordered a bloody mary, which was okay. It had too much black pepper for my liking. Although, it was very filling and I couldn’t eat most of my entree. Lapin ordered three mimosas, mostly because each one came with a half pour as each glass had more empty space than mimosa. He liked it but wished they pour an actually pour and not a 3 oz pour. Lapin ordered the confit duck hash ($18) and he loved it. He said it was one of the best tasting dishes he had. He was so enthralled with it -- he immediately decided he was going to find places that sell duck. I ordered the mac and cheese (casarecci, buffalo taleggio, mushrooms - $21). I was greatly disappointed when I saw the portion size for this meal. Granted it was tasty and rich but the portions -- I could easily get more mac and cheese from a cup of EZ-Mac. Great tasting food, bit on the pricey side especially with the portion sizes. The reason why The Gander is a four star place instead of a three stars is the effort and attention that was put into each detail. For example, they offer complimentary still or sparkling water. Everywhere that would be $7+ for a bottle. Each bathroom is it’s own private room. Which means, no lines waiting or smelling unpleasant scents while waiting. Which brings me to my next point. The bathrooms were fairly clean and was pleasantly scented. The bathrooms are also stocked with Beekind soap and lotion. Yup, they also included lotion. How awesome is that?', u'author_name': u'Lady Ace', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115208483266342139161', u'time': 1445454232}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 229-9500', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'15', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'15'}, {u'long_name': u'West 18th Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'W 18th St'}, {u'long_name': u'Midtown', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Midtown'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10011', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10011'}]}

u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-fTnN3BLoaNI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAVA/11XiP24SBoI/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I used to come here all the time when it was The Dam, and I do miss that place and the bartenders. But I must say that the space has been completely revamped and has a nice, low key and classy atmosphere. The food is great, including their grilled cheese and their charcuterie and cheese plate. Great selection of cocktails that are at typical Manhattan prices (well, about $3 less than someplace in The Village, which would approach the vibe of this place). So cocktails are $12, very well executed. And the bartenders are generally nice, particularly the good Scottish lad. The crowd and feel has changed since the days of The Dam, and I will cherish the memories I made there. But I am happy to welcome this new spot to my neighborhood. Excellent in my experience. u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-944-8378', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Went there for "The Labrynth" movie screening and dinner. The screening was a nice idea and we enjoyed the movie. It included a $30 prix fixe dinner. I wasnt expecting much from the menu but having read previous reviews on Yelp I figured it would be decent enough. I was wrong - the food was pretty bad. The risotto balls and tomato sauce were not good, the pasta (if I remember correctly) were to have shrimp....well it had the "essence" of shrimp in that it smelled like shrimp but I didn't spot any actual shrimp in the dish. The shepherds pie tasted like a microwaveable TV dinner. The makeshift bar set up was kind of silly where you had to leave your card at the bar because there was no credit card machine to process (they had to run over to the other venue to process the cards) and eventually they would return it to you. The bartender had no change. They were pushing an all the wine you can drink $35 deal. I just wanted one glass - at $14 plus tax for a glass of their City Winery wine that was so so - I could've stuck with water. Not sure what the other venues at the winery are like, the music I heard from the adjacent venue sounded good but I won't be coming back for the food.', u'author_name': u'Krist Lime', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117671878581041475111', u'time': 1461780955}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-3r9e0Y93fAk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABM/raNBRAQhw_k/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This was our third visit to White Street. Each experience thus far has been superb, highlighted by incredibly delicious food, a beautiful ambience, and excellent service. As suggested by our delightful and personable server, we ordered the zucchini chips with garlic aioli sauce, which was a memorable and savory experience in and of itself. We ended up ordering a lot of food, but thankfully each dish was equally delicious. The restaurant is pristine, the staff friendly and charming, and the food satisfying and memorable. Can't wait to return to this wonderful dining establishment.', u'author_name': u'Susan Piazza', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113437394088238443928', u'time': 1460262499}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-1jMPOc3Z_Uc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEk/1SV0PkpO190/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Pretty restaurant, good food, nice ambience. Biscuits and deviled eggs were great snacks to accompany a cocktail.', u'author_name': u'Andrew Duchi', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117034590178289719142', u'time': 1434848277}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-1Dy8fY3p5dI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAApK0/oMWwFfuUgo0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Fancy a retro style diner with well crafted classic cocktails? The Butterfly aims to satisfy that niche of an experience featuring a 50s vibe with a New York chic finish. In terms of food you can expect comfort, things like reuben croquettes that taste like mini fried pastrami nuggets or bratwurst sliders reminiscent of a German pub. One standout is the sweet and savory BLT salad which combines hearty pieces of bacon with kale and a tart sherry vinaigrette. As for the cocktails, can't go wrong with either their Mai Tai or a Tom Collins. Oh and stick around for dessert because the coca-cola ice cream with caramel popcorn will knock your socks off. Bottom line: Nothing too refined but cozy and comfy, delivering classic flavors with a flair for memory lane.', u'author_name': u'Raffi Asdourian', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106111748958700549590', u'time': 1378867192}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-O3bV18J9-gY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAew/aDte822OHWk/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'What a great find in NYC! I had never heard of 'Wisconsin Supper Clubs' but if The Butterfly is any indication of what they are like - sign me up! The drinks are CLASSIC. Best Whiskey Sour I've had in ages. The appetizers - Spinach Artichoke Dip, main course - Meatloaf with Tomato Jam, and the desserts - the table share several - the Chess Pie & Banana Chocolate Chuck Bread. Your surroundings - some classic 1950s kitsch. u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-226-4736', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'It's such a nice place for dating though I didn't go there for a date. I went for one of my favorite singers, Keren Ann's concert's. It's such a sophisticated place with nice audio system - very relaxing and comfy to enjoy the music. Wine was very nice and staff were friendly. Overall, it's a good spot in town I would love to come back or recommend to friends for wine and music. However, there was one thing really really really annoying to me - they said doors open at 6, show starts at 8. But the show didn't start until 8:30... Ok, I blame the delay to Keren Ann since she is French.', u'author_name': u'Krist Lime', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117671878581041475111', u'time': 1461781274}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-XnQvUUoC1rs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAGOw/-_osIS3F_4k/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Swanky, sexy interiors and steakhouse staples, plus a few unexpected menu items make for a great experience, although you may wait for a table even if you have a reservation. Even on a weeknight. Their everything biscuits (a riff on NY's most beloved bagel) are phenomenal. If I could buy them by the dozen, I would. Great cuts of meat treated right, down to the details of perfectly flavored compound butters and sauces. The table next to ours sent back a pastrami-style steak that was too fatty, but our filet mignon and skirt steak were heavenly.', u'author_name': u'Kels H. Murdoch', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107989918662458474722', u'time': 1459185283}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-DU1d1TYhbIY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAqY/mw2rlEsFFGI/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Good service and food, but you are better off to spend a little more cash and goto Wolfgang's', u'author_name': u'Adam Hutt', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111923235196131064382', u'time': 1463180148}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Food was pretty good and I loved the atmosphere but the steak just seemed subpar. We ordered the ribeye with the pastrami spices medium rare and I love a good fatty steak but the fat was very chewy - little bit of a let down! I've had better ribeyes in NYC. ', u'author_name': u'Louise DeMartin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107099605939555143397', u'time': 1456156365}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-fDT9z_r_og4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAANRY/sbTk0XBQQEc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Wow. I brought my gf here for a belated valentines day dinner and we had such an amazing time. I love the corner booth seats that let you stretch out your arms around your significant other between dishes. Decor and overall quality of this place is top notch for a fancy steak house. I think anyone would be impressed by its subtleties and attentive staff. Let's talk about food. Here's what to order: 1) cracker jack sundae. Even though this is dessert, I mention this in the beginning because you should certainly save room for this baby. The caramel bits with popcorn is flavorful and completely infused in the ice cream to give everything a consistent taste and complimentary range of sweetness. 2) steak for two. I've always recommended ordering the larger steak portions because the cut is better and more flavorful. We got the 40 Oz NY strip with the bone marrow topping and it was amazing. I could barely keep my eyes open from the savory flavor. We ordered it raw and it came out exactly the raw I wanted. Their house steak sauce also has a nice tangy and smoky flavor behind it, but I rather taste the natural flavor of murder. 3) mashed potatoes. This isn't just because I love mashed potatoes. Well... Not entirely due to that. It's because they use a tomato puree method that really goes nicely as a side sauce to top on the steak. Of course, I tend to mix mashed potatoes with everything... 4) California cab red wine. Bought a bottle because sometimes you have to go big. Great idea with the honig 2011. Steep, but worth it with pairing. 5) Caesar salad. This is a weird one, but I've always found Caesar salads to be specifically done right at a steakhouse. This one was very fresh, crunch, and delicious. Overall, what a great place for a special night with a special gal.', u'author_name': u'Clemens Wan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109331593848788039624', u'time': 1453732242}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 226-4736', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'363', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'363'}, {u'long_name': u'Greenwich Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Greenwich St'}, {u'long_name': u'Tribeca', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Tribeca'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10013', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10013'}]}

u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-WWeyHAfMa_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEw/cn3jjZFnhzA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Great cozy restaurant, like it when it's not packed with people. When it's packed it's too stuffy to eat in the restaurant. The staffs are nice and helpful. Also knowledgeable in every dishes with ingredients. I suggest trying spicy squid stir fry, spicy soy braised chicken over glass noodles, bbq wagyu short ribs and the Kimchi beef brisket fried rice. Overall great concept and the fusion of cruise are tasty and we'll balanced flavors.', u'author_name': u'Rafael Yau', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107744062940210293013', u'time': 1465768346}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-OoJuF3iXuXc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAn0/XnxWMUDfY8A/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The food here is generally quite good. I prefer the plates where they've perfected traditional Korean dishes (like the dduk bokki) rather than more fusion-y items. Top-notch ingredients + everything homemade + high-level technique makes the slightly higher price versus places in K-town or Flushing well worth it. But the 5 stars are really only for one reason: jjangmyun. Best version I've had anywhere. Including some famous places in Seoul. Really chewy noodles, and bean sauce with just enough of a salty punch, slicked with pork fat. The other Korean-Chinese items are great too (especially the bokkeum bap/fried rice), but the jjangmyun is next level. Seriously, these guys should just open up a jjangmyun shop so I can go a couple times a week.', u'author_name': u'John Ames', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102249249154296723543', u'time': 1462330148}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Q6KvA2Tv0N0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACk/oVGqA_wG7Ig/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The restaurant is really cozy. Its not jammed packed with people so it didnt get loud. The food was amazing quality; I had sweet and sour chicken that was crunchy and sweet, thick noodles with pork belly and black bean sauce that was amazing, and finished with sweet potato ice cream (It is very good!!) Definitely coming back here.', u'author_name': u'Ellen s', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102107984695501278060', u'time': 1454904335}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-bMQxTKOZa3Q/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAkjk/Ltsu0LTFdws/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I was invited by family to visit this unique Korean fine dining restaurant. Korean fine dining? Yes. Regrets. The 5 of us ordered a glorious dish of spicy rice cake, spicy kimchi fried rice, fishcake soup with spicy broth in a stone pot, braised pig feet presented with eloquence, and other misc. dishes. Each dish tasted decent, but not particularly special or different. After our meal (or food tasting), and bill of $100+, all 5 of us were befuddled with an empty stomach. A 4 year old girl could have eaten all the food we ordered, and more. Flabbergasted, we left for K-town to eat. Came hungry and loaded, and left starving and broke. The 2 stars are for the luminous atmosphere and attentive service.', u'author_name': u'Daniel Suh', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103988214297751611200', u'time': 1456604782}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-x85NoKd9YdQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAOo/wyo_g4_YQSY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'High End gourmet korean food. Well worth the higher price. u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-ei2TScoAMNY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAA2_8/qpMUUdS7ihw/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Nice atmosphere,attentive staff and some unique flavour combinations (bone marrow and sea urchin anyone?) make this a nice spot for a dinner. Cocktail list is very small but also features some different mixtures like Miss Robert Cobbler's blending gin, pear jam, lavender an thyme. Very refreshing!', u'author_name': u'Rejane S', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103651153706195020571', u'time': 1392776829}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-1Dy8fY3p5dI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAApK0/oMWwFfuUgo0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'An interesting fusion of Italian and German cuisine, "Top Chef" winner Harold Dieterle's quaint bistro in the West Village is a place worth checking out. I was thoroughly impressed with my cocktail, Miss Roberts’ Cobbler, a not too sweet mixture of pear jam, lavender & thyme cemented with a crisp, clean rum. Dining as part of restaurant week, the 3 course menu was both satisfactory and unique. I started with a decadent, salty scarlet butter lettuce salad with pecorino cheese and mango while my friend has the sunchoke soup which tasted of sunflower seeds. For my main, I was treated to a large and perfectly cooked pork chop over beans and greens with a delectable spicy pepper vinaigrette. We had a side of brussels sprouts that were super yummy. To finish things, a decadent strudel served with caramel ice cream that was the perfect ending to an excellent meal. Bottom Line: This is a great spot for a date with hearty food that offer big flavors.', u'author_name': u'Raffi Asdourian', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106111748958700549590', u'time': 1392737905}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-NICdzx1OnGw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAGY/yb-7Cm6ieSs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Harold Dieterle's best restaurant in my opinion. Great dishes that span between German and Italian. The mushroom entree is surprisingly delicious and the hearty Ginger-Stout cake is definitely one of the best new desserts out there.', u'author_name': u'Bin Yang', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103966169436601350244', u'time': 1366394576}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Brunch review: the burger was good (ordered medium but it came closer to medium rare which is ok by me). ', u'author_name': u'Kevin Wu', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112478077321292017341', u'time': 1366342420}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-PKp0vsTsiB4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAXss/-T8ALLlpj-A/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This new restaurant, interestingly, combines cuisines of Germany and Italy. 646-964-5624', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 1, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'We were refused service so I cannot comment on the food. The manager/ waitress (short, about 5'5" tall, blonde woman) would not sit is because they were holding the table for somebody else. The website says they don't take reservations, but they're were holding TWO different tables for parties who were not yet at the restaurant. The hostess said that the party of 6 would be back "right away", but even after 10 minutes they didn't show up. When we brought this up to her and asked if we could be seated she flat out refuses us service and walked off. In outraged because the restaurants website specifically says they do not take reservations. I gladly would have made a reservation, but instead I was denied service for no good reason. We ended up leaving, and the waitress was laughing at us as we walked off. She told us "Maybe you should go eat somewhere else". tl:dr: rude manager/waitress (short blonde woman), gave a party preference who was not yet at the restaurant, after telling us "it's first come first serve", then flat or refused is service. Maybe she was racist because we were a group of black and Asian people. This restaurant has a false reservation policy, rude and racist staff members who will turn you away and laugh at you. This all happened at 6:30pm on Friday April 15, 2016. Service is 0/5 stars but I cannot comment on the food. I hope the rude waitress is fired from her job because she certainly has no place working in hospitality.', u'author_name': u'Michael Starr', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104582429518410978237', u'time': 1460765842}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Food was all really inventive and tasty! Not an elegant place.', u'author_name': u'Laurel Kenner', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108085949673321266840', u'time': 1463536772}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-K4Urc6Rav0Y/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAbk/kuc4bfk2r_w/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Very good restaurant. I went for my lady's birthday and she was very happy as well.', u'author_name': u'James Tindall', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104162070158948080581', u'time': 1464623398}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-lkJz3NOcei0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAMM/AX0PsIc6Pfc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I've been here twice and the dishes are hit or miss. I've had much better duck at Chinese or French restaurants. ', u'author_name': u'Jana Borer', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103841869171760118472', u'time': 1464360982}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-3QH4sFSx0bU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFZ4/H9i6Tz1LrbE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'An absolutely amazing culinary experience. ', u'author_name': u'Jeff Baldwin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/100162970790612847156', u'time': 1463355184}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Love the atmosphere in the restaurant, not sure how they get perfect lighting above each table although at first glance everywhere seems so dark. Our friends had been raving about it and it did not disappoint. The food was superb, from the charcoal crackers, the scallops, to the desserts, everything! You can tell they use top quality ingredients. Very happy with the service and the atmosphere, will be back for sure!', u'author_name': u'Alex D', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108776169279276281660', u'time': 1465515505}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-M-1YEffC-I0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAxNc/fkTxgoQ8p28/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Outstanding at every turn. Remarkable flavors, incredible ambiance, finely tuned service, three hours later we were left in deep contemplation of the experience.', u'author_name': u'Mitch Kranitz', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113868781798254270390', u'time': 1465559831}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The food in the bar is amazing for an a la carte experience and the dining room experience is just exquisite. This is truly for those with the most discerning taste & style - amazing technique and flavors that unify in beautiful harmony. The room is ethereal in feel & I feel transported from the bustle of NYC. My go-to for entertaining or drinks with friends - the caviar tarte flambe and a glass of champagne in the bar - divine! One of the best!', u'author_name': u'Liza Emile', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112087828216413899084', u'time': 1463756248}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'With family now living in different parts of the country, our times all together are rare, so we decided to treat ourselves and celebrate our daughter’s birthday with dinner at GK. From the time we were seated and our daughter was presented with a personalized menu until we departed several hours later, we enjoyed and savored every moment. The service was stellar, with each member of the team knowledgeable and attentive, yet unobtrusive. Each course, from the amuse-bouche, first, second, third, bread, meat, fish, to dessert, was delicious and created with the freshest of ingredients, plated elegantly and served with synchronicity. The sommelier, after asking about our particular tastes, suggested wines that paired perfectly with our meals. Our thanks to the entire staff for making our evening one to remember.', u'author_name': u'ch bryant', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112597541990062453176', u'time': 1458939015}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'What a special place! Absolutely beautiful restaurant with the food and service to match. I've been multiple times and each time was more perfect than the last. No hesitation to recommend or go back for a special occasion or just a night out.', u'author_name': u'Michael Rubin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102093317410347290266', u'time': 1458234406}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 257-5826', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'41', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'41'}, {u'long_name': u'West 42nd Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'W 42nd St'}, {u'long_name': u'Midtown', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Midtown'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10036', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10036'}]}

My parents and I really enjoyed the linguine with garlic and the black pasta with crab. The appetizers were just okay, we got the rice balls and kale salad. Not outstanding but not bad either. The space is too small for the number of tables they had. I felt like I had no space and kept kicking the person in front of me and if I backed up my chair I wouldn't leave space for the servers. Difficult situation. Overall, id say this is a great choice if you want to just come here for a quick pasta lunch and go back to work. Also love that they serve mochi ice cream for dessert. Delicious!', u'author_name': u'Lauren Cochran', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102653012030578171818', u'time': 1466184971}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-CjNkrT8adTE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAO4/b0r2Vuexvc4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Ramen here is phenomenal and it's evidenced by the long wait times here. One should always expect about an hour or so wait. Highly recommended and definitely worth the wait. I usually go with whatever specials they have as their special ramen circulate. Pro tip: save your soup so you can order another side of ramen if you aren't full from the first bowl! ', u'author_name': u'Wilson Ng', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115103127673078278723', u'time': 1465223035}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-7Q2AAfwy9zw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAQU/vr5evXWNgu0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'One of my favorite restaurants in the city, I always make an effort to come when I'm in the area. We were seated at a table and the staff were not attentive and focused on the patrons at the sushi bar. It took several attempts just to get their attention to give us water. Our sashimi and sushi took an hour and thirty minutes to arrive, and when questioned about it they were unapologetic stating that making sashimi can take a long time. The fish was not as fresh as previously, the slices were smaller, and the sushi rice was subpar. I will not return again. It's such a shame because this place used to be such a gem. u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-eqBwyeTNuc4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABdU/tpdx16LAy_w/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Loved it, loved it, loved it. I'd read about it in a magazine before my first trip to NYC, so this was a planned and much-anticipated visit. And we weren't disappointed! The potato latkes were simply perfect, and my husband was overjoyed to find an egg cream on the drinks menu, which took him back to his childhood. The atmosphere is fabulous and I loved the updated take on the old-style decor of the original store on Houston. Highly recommended.', u'author_name': u'Kathryn Hatfield', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111935074640968533959', u'time': 1462074590}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-JmphqX8PsqI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAB0_o/iUlZw_IBzNM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Some of the best Bloody Marrys in the city - the infused vodkas are great with the fresh ingredients they use. Amazing brunch options - the pastrami lox are truly unique and delicious, the Benedicts are great, and all of the traditional Jewish fare is consistently satisfying. ', u'author_name': u'Matt Jacobs Jr', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109211239342408282067', u'time': 1466352544}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-3N1dM7-Cztk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABkQ/r2bTxl6pGhs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'This a place to hit on a lazy weekday, I can only imagine weekend brunch is a mob scene. Really good Jewish comfort eats, some presented with a twist. I particularly enjoyed the hebster, the herring trio and the chopped liver. The cocktails and sodas also divine. Love the retro feel with all the pics from the old shop. ', u'author_name': u'JeAnne Swinley', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/115154328634129165379', u'time': 1459875541}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'We had dinner there on Wednesday night and the food was very good. We were told the kitchen closed at 10 so we got our order right in. But when it came to ordering a dessert to go, we were told it was too late. We assumed this did not apply to desserts. We asked to speak to the manager. She explained her policy. This would have been acceptable but her manner was very surly and flippant. Then as she left our table she made a comment to one of her staff. The friend I was with agreed, although she apologized it was in a take it or leave it manner. This is not an attitude we would expect from someone representing your business. Myself, an owner of a large pediatric clinic and my friend, a successful comedian, mentioned the incident to several friends and they agreed in our assessment. An otherwise excellent meal was tarnished by the experience.', u'author_name': u'Michael King', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114837474034443729970', u'time': 1458244732}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'one of our favorite breakfast spots in Sunnyside! love their cappuccinos & lattes and very affordable! the menu is simple and good. perfect for a no frills breakfast. great music & ambiance, extremely friendly staff (I spilled coffee on my phone & the owner immediately grabbed it and dried it off in the back)', u'author_name': u'D A', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/104801773778834981945', u'time': 1466983659}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 475-4880', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'127', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'127'}, {u'long_name': u'Orchard Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Orchard St'}, {u'long_name': u'Lower Manhattan', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lower Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10002', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10002'}]}

u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-PDd4jAkVl1w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAHw/iMzwbvQAi_4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'So let me start this out by saying I love Chinese food, and I find it hard to find really really really good Chinese food (and I have been to many). But in all of Queens this is my second favorite Chinese restaurant. I originally came here for the Muslim lamb chops but came back again and again to try the other menu options. Now the lamb chops are good (but expensive for me). But the sesame chicken and pork chops are delicious. Definitely a place i keep going back to', u'author_name': u'Khalid Brown', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117575830013795905251', u'time': 1465348925}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Fu run is amazing like almost review. After searching google, I decided to try! I went there with 3 more friends and we ordered the Green bean jelly with red oil, tiger veg, the orange pork, eggplant hot garlic sauce and Muslim lam chop of course. Oh I really so love what we ordered that I forgot my weight controlled plan! But they worth!', u'author_name': u'Xue Zhou', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102048202223176543548', u'time': 1462994140}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I really liked this place for dim sum (never have been during the dinner hours). This last time we were lucky to have a Mandarin-speaking friend with us, which made things significantly easier, as most staff do not speak any English --- but this latter characteristic only adds to the charm. The lunchtime atmosphere is vibrant and lively - huge hall with giant tables with lots and lots of local families. The cart ladies are very nice (even smile occasionally!) and weren't too pushy with the dishes. Food is wonderful... I have tried pretty much every item on their menu by now, and there has not been a dud yet. I do wish, however, that they had some sauces and condiments available on the table. Instead, they bring these teensy weensy thimbles - definitely not enough. I recommend - and I will be back myself and will take visiting friends here.', u'author_name': u'shirley jing', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101024329324918367164', u'time': 1461791230}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'We ordered the fish fillet in spicy sauce $16 + muslim lamb chop $26. Both were delish and came out relatively quickly. Star of the show was the fish fillet in spicy sauce. There was a generous amount of fish, so soft and tender cooked in the szechuan peppers and hot oil. I was such a huge fan of the flavor I almost took home the leftover broth/oil so I could cook stuff with lol. The muslim lamb chop was a little bit difficult to eat and heavy on the cumin (which I don't mind at all). Personally, I had to scrape off all the seasoning on top because that would've been too much party in my mouth... In the end, there wasn't too much meat. It was a good dish but not one I'd come back for given the price. Rice is like an extra $1.50 for 2 bowls. Even if you're not a huge carb eater, I recommend ordering rice to go with these flavor-heavy dishes. They take both cash and card.. no discount for cash.', u'author_name': u'us Amy', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112000974606249722767', u'time': 1462234367}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/--ZJoQKz-NsY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAPo/OfpOA1Am1G0/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Good restaurant with big portion and reasonable prices. The dishes cost between $10 to 19. They are all delicious. The service, of course in Flushing, in subpar. This place is usually crowded during the weekends. One minor complaint: if you don't like salty food, avoid this place.', u'author_name': u'James Yoh', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108486093540932521003', u'time': 1460395870}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(718) 321-1363', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'40-09', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'40-09'}, {u'long_name': u'Prince Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Prince St'}, {u'long_name': u'Flushing', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Flushing'}, {u'long_name': u'Queens', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Queens'}, {u'long_name': u'Queens County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Queens County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'11354', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'11354'}, {u'long_name': u'5304', u'types': [u'postal_code_suffix'], u'short_name': u'5304'}]}

u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-837-2622', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U4IBRWcWvhA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABB3c/KSohftLJ008/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Went again in March 2016: I have always had outstanding meals here. This time the server was wonderful. He was almost poetic in his descriptions of the specials and he seemed very passionate about the food and wines. We started with the housemade salumi = SO GOOD! The short ribs were stunning. Then we had the figs with lardo which I wasn't sure was going to work, but totally did. The artichokes were good but a couple of my friends don't know how to eat them, so I schooled them. I have recommended this restaurant numerous times. One friend from DC told me she dreams about the Busiate pasta. We had that and the Cacio Pepe which our server told us was there most popular pasta. We shared the panna cotta before heading to Lafayette for more desserts. You cannot go wrong here. One of the best places in NYC and I don't say that lightly. ------------------------------ My old review: Always well done, but never overdone food. The quality of the ingredients always shines through in the food here. We enjoyed the salumi, pasta dishes, artichokes, the large played, etc. I've never had a questionable dish. The first dish I ever had from Il Buco was the panna cotta with balsamic reduction at the Hester Street Fair several years ago. It is always the perfect ending to a meal there.', u'author_name': u'Jackie Gordon Singing Chef', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/109673791694826464177', u'time': 1464014329}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Fqyy_YO6b4w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAKag/A0Frd3DKf1s/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I've been here more than twice. It's excellent most nights. Fresh Pasta order was left out too long by the server to bring it to us, was gluey and killed it. But should be a safe place to visit most nights. Charcuterie is great. ', u'author_name': u'Justin Alexander', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102577832815724318709', u'time': 1462073095}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Came here at 1pm ish on the weekend and it was not crowded? Wow. Then I found out why. This lackluster dim sum place falls flat not due to its second floor, inside the mall location. The food takes the blame, they were on average to mediocre. Chicken Feet: was not cooked long enough. White turnip cake: I found pieces of taro in it. Is this taro or turnip cake? It was barely seared on the pan. Shui Mai: average. Shrimp Dumpling: average. Rice crepes: had better. Sticky rice in lotus leaves: average Pork buns: nothing to write about I was totally surprised when my man told me that there is a guy in the men's bathroom servicing and waiting on tip. Whaaaat? This is the only dim sum place I have ever been to where they don't rush you. The table next to us were actually taking their time and reading newspaper. Yep. Wow.', u'author_name': u'seen jee', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/107681614363383552114', u'time': 1459261783}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-z3auAxPvU_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAA4/1gMYMPTfScE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Food was OK. Limited menu and fresh baked bread was less than hoped for. Our main server was super snooty and quite unpleasant. Another server who actually brought out meals and resulted our drinks was polite and wonderful. But the main server had already fallen the experience by then. Also, as we were leaving employees looked post the first member of our party (female) to thank and farewell only the one male member of our party.', u'author_name': u'Miran Cho', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/113334743592462298196', u'time': 1461409536}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-VldjA_9021w/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAHso/xN5GTOeefHE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Food so good that it touches your soul. Amazingly friendly staff. We really loved this restaurant! u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-1toxVaDxHcs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAhI/_KXiN1GxcOc/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Pleasant experience with unique spins on classic foods. There are quite a few lackluster reviews, making me think the time you get here and the dishes you choose, make all the difference. The staff was very accommodating to me without a reservation and I sat outside, which is a great option, weather permitting. I actually liked the pigs in a blanket because there was a subtle shift to a more Asian flavor instead of a very intense flavor attack. I was most impressed by the pickled beets with coconut ricotta and dried basil and duck was cooked to absolute perfection. So for tapas and drinks, I'd recommend you check this place out. I want to go back. {u'lat': 40.7045595, u'lng': -74.01088085}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.7043855, u'lng': -74.01099745000002}}}, u'adr_address': u'26 S William St, New York, NY 10004, USA', u'international_phone_number': u'+1 212-747-1700', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I visited this place based on the reviews while I am staying in the area. The service was great and they were helpful. Food was good as well since I love seafood i ordered clam chowder ($9 for large, $6 for small) soup and shrimp, lobster, crab rolls and blueberry soda $24). I was happy with my order.', u'author_name': u'Tommy Nguyen', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/105949673472290254155', u'time': 1464146155}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I went to the City Winery once before and had a nice pre-show meal. Food was tasty and reasonable priced. So I decided to go back and to see a concert and also enjoy dinner. Food is still good but the "concert" was a rip-off. The tickets were $40 to see LIzz Wright and she performed for maybe 1 hours. I saw her at Town Hall a couple years back and the show was 2 hours and close in price. Here is the kicker. Our dinner bill for four was close to $400 in addition to $120 concert tickets. For that we received a 1 hour show from the artist we came to see. VERY DISJOINTED. So my suggestion is to go for dinner but not the show or go to the show and not have dinner. Call ahead and ask about the length of the show so you know if it is worth it. When people spend that kinda of money they want to feel value. The staff was excellent and the food great (except for the zucchini cake) but City Winery be reasonable.', u'author_name': u'Krist Lime', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117671878581041475111', u'time': 1461788365}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Overall, their food is 3 stars, but the service knocked them down to 2. Let's start with the food: Pork soup dumplings: decent, skin not as thin as other places and meat filling was a bit bland Crabmeat & pork soup dumplings: OK, but couldn't really taste the crabmeat String beans with pork szechuan style: pretty good, slightly spicy, very flavorful Drunken Crab: served raw!! My first time trying raw crab. It was interesting and actually not bad at all! (and no tummy aches!) They marinade it in wine, and it's sweet. We ordered more soup dumplings after we finished our first batch. It was only 7PM, and the bus boy comes to our table and says "No more soup dumplings." Are you serious?? It's 7PM. The restaurant opens until midnight on Saturdays. There's no way there are no more soup dumplings. Apparently, this is their way to kick people out when there's a line forming for other diners. Fortunately, a nicer waitress came to us and said our soup dumplings are coming. But, how rude is that?! Did you really think we would believe you when you said no more soup dumplings at 7PM????! On a Saturday.', u'author_name': u'Lynn Lan', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/112325306401090496442', u'time': 1461787126}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ZDAQNodeJvw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACh4/3XQJU4oa4JM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Went at night to get some take-out lobster rolls. Wasn't at the level of quality you'd get at the other locations. Was quite disappointed by the sloppy construction of what I think are the best lobster rolls in the city.', u'author_name': u'Kimberly Peng', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/111076853226773258596', u'time': 1464102391}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-wpShoJIEEGQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFoI/dtc3yqR66bI/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The food was delicious, but it's barely enough to consider a meal. Here's my suggestion - try the lobster, get one of the blueberry sodas they sell, and then walk straight over to the nearest food truck and get a street dog to top it off. Your stomach might regret it, but your taste buds surely won't.', u'author_name': u'Nick Brown', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102151485698758392234', u'time': 1464097043}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 747-1700', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'26', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'26'}, {u'long_name': u'South William Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'S William St'}, {u'long_name': u'Financial District', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Financial District'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10004', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10004'}]}
