So spicy you couldn't swallow a bite. Nothing will ever get me to go there again. Worst service and menu. I definitely don't recommend. The decore is terrible.', u'author_name': u'Maranda McAlpin', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/101728664779953505329', u'time': 1462765926}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-S_IpgWDwaS4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABKbA/84nWnEKi0KA/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Some of the best szechuan Chinese food I have ever had! Super spicy and delicious. If you have the cash and the time to wait for it.... please get the Beggar's Duck. It will feed more than 2 people and is the most amazing duck i have ever had but it takes 2 hours to prepare. WORTH IT', u'author_name': u'Joey Riz', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102484722965298902549', u'time': 1462221547}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-cycqpA0vOT4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAI0U/Id6sNlS3htY/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'DO NOT GO HERE .... If you LOVE the original San Fran restaurant. The New York outpost is totally overpriced and the portions are so much smaller. That said I'm addicted to the Mapo Tofu. Don't order the Kale veg dish, give the pickled veg appetiser a miss. ', u'author_name': u'Adam Crick', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106490482306121680463', u'time': 1464654049}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-aswZkWomOwY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAKKs/XjMRy07TNWM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I wanted to dislike this place so hard because it seemed like it was trying way too much to be trendy. And don't get me wrong, it's trendy (or whatever) as hell. And there's always a crazy wait. But I have to give it to the chef because they've done a pretty amazing job with the food and drinks. This is "Chinese fusion" done well, meaning not essentialized Oriental dishes, but thought out dishes that build on regional Chinese cuisine. Execution and consistency, however, could use some work. While the presentation was great, a lot of their dishes are over seasoned and too salty, to the point that you can't distinguish any specific flavors from the ingredients, only white noise in your mouth. Too bad because the prices are high enough that you would expect more attention to flavors, and the menu items themselves seem like they should be delicious (and some are).', u'author_name': u'Keith The bad: tables are tiny and very close to each other, they screwed up when seating us which created an awkward situation with the uppity people whose table we were occupying, the food is quite pricey, portions are pathetic ($17 for 3 of the smallest tacos I've ever seen, for instance), the burgers are almost good, except they are cooked horribly inconsistently (my medium burger was well done, while someone else's medium was rare), the flatbreads are completely lackluster @ $16-$17. The burger situation really killed the food for me. Not only were they prepared poorly, but they are grossly expensive. $17 will get you basically a burger and bun (and fries or small salad). If you want cheese, onions, bacon... Add $2-$3 each. Seriously, $2 for onions. Give me a break. Drinks were typically priced I suppose, starting at $12 for bourbon (which is all I really cared about). u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-CJEa4_e0SOk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAmvI/h62Bgeq5_yM/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Very underwhelmed. Granted, I'm more used to fatty broths so this may not be my cup of tea (or bowl of ramen as it were). Noodles were cooked a little more al dente than I would have liked and the Tokyo shio shoyu broth tasted very much like diluted soy sauce without much additional dimension. My wife's tonkotsu broth (triple pork triple garlic mazeman) was much tastier. Appetizers were perfect. Pork meatballs were very tasty and roasted shrimp were cooked perfectly. Very attentive service (even if the host seemed disinterested).', u'author_name': u'Eric Chang', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106953697585345674229', u'time': 1464629659}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-bkeLouskje8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAA8k/5GC3efSa3hQ/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Stumbled here on a Friday night, didn't have to wait for a table. The staff there are friendly and attentive. Wish I ordered more pieces of Pork Musubi, they are so moist, delicious and addictive (still craving it). Have to say I have quite a high tolerance for heat, and the spicy red chili ramen sure has a nice kick to it - was thoroughly surprise by that as spicy is never spicy to me at all. Service was quick, and the staff didn't rush me out as I took my time finishing my beer.', u'author_name': u'J Liu', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/106357964411685746172', u'time': 1461430635}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-2kROZSEJhs0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAo/rKavTPhgX-4/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Very good pork musubi but the ramen wasn't good. We got the Tokyo shoyu ramen = too salty and the spicy red chili ramen = too spicy Didn't taste like the ramen we eat in Japan', u'author_name': u'ordinary routine', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/110260100966652932599', u'time': 1463543265}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-vp9kn4NFPzA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAEeo/lGit4gneQYE/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Best Ramen I've tried! Me and my buddy tried both the shio and Shia Ramen. One has more of a salty sea foodish taste and the other has a rich soy flavor. I personally liked the salty taste better. Also, make sure you try the pork meat balls. It's like an explosion of flavor! Staff was incredibly helpful and friendly. Highly recommend this place! ', u'author_name': u'Sam Varghese', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/108046260511670314195', u'time': 1464750670}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I don't really get this place. I've visited many ramen places in Tokyo and this isn't a pinch on them. All hype for a so so bowl or ramen. Thin noodles that remind me of instant noodles not true hand made noodles. Very boring plain taste in the broth for the shiso . The standard serve has a tiny piece of pork chasu and spring onions. I opted for Enoki mushrooms and they were just thrown on top raw as a big clump and the base was all woody and hard. I was really disappointed. The service and staff were good though.', u'author_name': u'Wade Stewart', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/117953413761441380817', u'time': 1462264830}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(646) 678-3859', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'25', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'25'}, {u'long_name': u'Clinton Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Clinton St'}, {u'long_name': u'Lower Manhattan', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lower Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10002', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10002'}]}

u'//lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ISGeDBWmqx8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAA_bw/amW5u0njFE8/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'We ventured up to 118th Street and St. Nicholas Avenue and found the neighborhood improved and Cecil a lovely wide open restaurant run by lovely people. It's busy and it's noisy. The menu is "interesting" and staff is very accommodating. We were a group of 3. Two of us liked it better than the third', u'author_name': u'Doug Anderson', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/102843684223721179334', u'time': 1465609211}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh6.googleusercontent.com/-AXc95295_h4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/yhJbXuqHpzs/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Beautifully decorated restaurant with a menu that seems cutting edge but, at heart, it's just an expensive greasy spoon. Perusing the menu, you'll see plenty you'd like to eat but soon enough you'll find the main tastes of everything on the menu tends towards either oily, charred or over-seasoned. Maybe this is fine if you're downing cocktails over Sunday brunch, but given the high expectations that come with an Eater 38 recommendation and main course prices to match sadly The Cecil falls short.', u'author_name': u'Kevin Cabral', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103612062459546747277', u'time': 1465540472}, {u'rating': 3, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 1, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I came The food during brunch was amazing - Mac N cheese was definitely top 5! The free champagne (Paul Cheneau) was pretty good, however the service could be much better. We arrived on time for our reservation, but was seated 20 minutes later. We finally got water 30 minutes after being seated. Once the food came out it was very tasty. ', u'author_name': u'Jay Rome', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116565766419717166801', u'time': 1462047304}, {u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-0M7oj_SmzQI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAo/yUw9zQMdJ84/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I have been wanting to come here since a year and I finally got a chance to visit on Xmas eve with my friends. We had dinner at another restaurant and while looking for a near by place to catch some more drinks we walked into Russian tea room. The cocktails were simply awwsomeeee .... The 8 of us ordered different cocktails and each of us loved ours..., the tea of course is served very well and good. We also ordered tiramisu and creme brûlée which vanished from the plates within mins.....', u'author_name': u'ru yi li', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/103772686386980536225', u'time': 1464115820}, {u'rating': 5, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 3, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh5.googleusercontent.com/-fcdm17GTwOE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAENQ/2wx5f9eZK1E/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'The Cecil Restaurant was a welcomed surprise. Beautiful Afro-Asian decor and really inviting. Mellow neo-soul lowly playing in the background. Received some amazing bread compliments of the chef. To start you must try the Braised Goat Dumplings. I'm yearning for more they were delicious. For my entree I had the Tamarind-Glaze Oxtails which was really delicious (the pickled cabbage was a little strong) but still loved the dish. For my cocktail I had "A Southern Moment"... Sweet and Full. The food is also good. Highly recommend the avocado dip. Only a couple of beers on tap but a nice bottle selection', u'author_name': u'Heather Alaoui-Mamoun', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/116786607400387691845', u'time': 1454027296}, {u'rating': 2, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 0, u'type': u'overall'}], u'profile_photo_url': u'//lh4.googleusercontent.com/-z0Sl1j_hvsU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAmyU/y938JYUcn4Y/photo.jpg', u'language': u'en', u'text': u'I really want to like this place - chill vibe, good drinks, and friendly bartenders. However I've been here a few times over the past few months, only to be greeted by a family of rats who have decided to setup camp right outside of the bar. I know this is New York and sharing the streets with our four legged friends is part of life, but a tipping point was last night when we spotted a mouse inside the bar. I've now seen rats outside of Fresh Salt on three out of four visits. Until they can get a handle on their rodent problem I won't be coming back.', u'author_name': u'Stephen Kliff', u'author_url': u'https://plus.google.com/114963587772328111027', u'time': 1453318962}], u'formatted_phone_number': u'(212) 962-0053', u'address_components': [{u'long_name': u'146', u'types': [u'street_number'], u'short_name': u'146'}, {u'long_name': u'Beekman Street', u'types': [u'route'], u'short_name': u'Beekman St'}, {u'long_name': u'Lower Manhattan', u'types': [u'neighborhood', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Lower Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'Manhattan', u'types': [u'sublocality_level_1', u'sublocality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'Manhattan'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'locality', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York'}, {u'long_name': u'New York County', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_2', u'political'], u'short_name': u'New York County'}, {u'long_name': u'New York', u'types': [u'administrative_area_level_1', u'political'], u'short_name': u'NY'}, {u'long_name': u'United States', u'types': [u'country', u'political'], u'short_name': u'US'}, {u'long_name': u'10038', u'types': [u'postal_code'], u'short_name': u'10038'}, {u'long_name': u'2044', u'types': [u'postal_code_suffix'], u'short_name': u'2044'}]}

info: {u'rating': 4.6, u'utc_offset': -240, u'name': u'Hudson Eats', u'reference': u'CmRfAAAAyW3ghLFVyDwh23b76eiYCElf_RbBjFMnK-PeFHf2R-Zr28_j7OgBePQy7Oxe4XXn5onKx7AL9GlsxPPY35PSFYAsJyoMLrtY1YHoFusZVXNf-RGAG3eMHOQ9yjZwMzNOEhBpsnXzoTz6b58QLOGeF3zQGhTMSEH3xD_1E4xUXZprsXO-tkSMJw', u'price_level': 2, u'geometry': {u'location': {u'lat': 40.7128921, u'lng': -74.015701}, u'viewport': {u'northeast': {u'lat': 40.714648, u'lng': -74.01404004999999}, u'southwest': {u'lat': 40.7123068, u'lng': -74.01625465000001}}}, u'adr_address': u'Brookfield Place, 200 Vesey St, New York, NY 10080, USA', u'place_id': u'ChIJfz_DABtawokRenTAxMoEjdI', u'vicinity': u'Brookfield Place, 200 Vesey Street, New York', u'reviews': [{u'rating': 4, u'aspects': [{u'rating': 2, u'type': u'overall'}], u'language': u'en', u'text': u'Hudson Eats is cool little place to eat lunch with a beautiful view of the Hudson River and the Winter Garden Atrium. There are little spaces where each restaurant can serve all different kinds of food (no nationwide chains). Once you get your food you can sit at little bars or tables that surround the Atrium's second level and the floor-to-ceiling glass windows that look out over the Hudson River.
